99 // static
100 Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::HasProperty(LookupIterator* it) {
101  for (;; it->Next()) {
102  switch (it->state()) {
103  case LookupIterator::TRANSITION:
104  case LookupIterator::STRING_LOOKUP_START_OBJECT:
105  UNREACHABLE();
106  case LookupIterator::JSPROXY:
107  return JSProxy::HasProperty(it->isolate(), it->GetHolder<JSProxy>(),
108  it->GetName());
109  case LookupIterator::WASM_OBJECT:
110  continue; // Continue to the prototype, if present.
111  case LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR: {
112  Maybe<PropertyAttributes> result =
113  JSObject::GetPropertyAttributesWithInterceptor(it);
114  if (result.IsNothing()) return Nothing<bool>();
115  if (result.FromJust() != ABSENT) return Just(true);
116  continue;
117  }
118  case LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK: {
119  if (it->HasAccess()) continue;
120  Maybe<PropertyAttributes> result =
121  JSObject::GetPropertyAttributesWithFailedAccessCheck(it);
122  if (result.IsNothing()) return Nothing<bool>();
123  return Just(result.FromJust() != ABSENT);
124  }
125  case LookupIterator::TYPED_ARRAY_INDEX_NOT_FOUND:
126  // TypedArray out-of-bounds access.
127  return Just(false);
128  case LookupIterator::ACCESSOR:
129  case LookupIterator::DATA:
130  return Just(true);
131  case LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND:
132  return Just(false);
133  }
134  UNREACHABLE();
135  }
136 }
137 
138 // static
139 Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::HasOwnProperty(Isolate* isolate,
140  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> object,
141  DirectHandle<Name> name) {
142  if (IsJSModuleNamespace(*object)) {
143  PropertyDescriptor desc;
144  return JSReceiver::GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(isolate, object, name, &desc);
145  }
146 
147  if (IsJSObject(*object)) { // Shortcut.
148  PropertyKey key(isolate, name);
149  LookupIterator it(isolate, object, key, LookupIterator::OWN);
150  return HasProperty(&it);
151  }
152 
153  Maybe<PropertyAttributes> attributes =
154  JSReceiver::GetOwnPropertyAttributes(isolate, object, name);
155  MAYBE_RETURN(attributes, Nothing<bool>());
156  return Just(attributes.FromJust() != ABSENT);
157 }
158 
159 Handle<Object> JSReceiver::GetDataProperty(LookupIterator* it,
160  AllocationPolicy allocation_policy) {
161  for (;; it->Next()) {
162  switch (it->state()) {
163  case LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR:
164  case LookupIterator::TRANSITION:
165  case LookupIterator::STRING_LOOKUP_START_OBJECT:
166  UNREACHABLE();
167  case LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK:
168  // Support calling this method without an active context, but refuse
169  // access to access-checked objects in that case.
170  if (!it->isolate()->context().is_null() && it->HasAccess()) continue;
171  [[fallthrough]];
172  case LookupIterator::JSPROXY:
173  it->NotFound();
174  return it->isolate()->factory()->undefined_value();
175  case LookupIterator::WASM_OBJECT:
176  continue; // Continue to the prototype, if present.
177  case LookupIterator::ACCESSOR:
178  // TODO(verwaest): For now this doesn't call into AccessorInfo, since
179  // clients don't need it. Update once relevant.
180  it->NotFound();
181  return it->isolate()->factory()->undefined_value();
182  case LookupIterator::TYPED_ARRAY_INDEX_NOT_FOUND:
183  return it->isolate()->factory()->undefined_value();
184  case LookupIterator::DATA:
185  return it->GetDataValue(allocation_policy);
186  case LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND:
187  return it->isolate()->factory()->undefined_value();
188  }
189  UNREACHABLE();
190  }
191 }
192 
193 // static
194 Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::HasInPrototypeChain(Isolate* isolate,
195  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> object,
196  DirectHandle<Object> proto) {
197  PrototypeIterator iter(isolate, object, kStartAtReceiver);
198  while (true) {
199  if (!iter.AdvanceFollowingProxies()) return Nothing<bool>();
200  if (iter.IsAtEnd()) return Just(false);
201  if (PrototypeIterator::GetCurrent(iter).is_identical_to(proto)) {
202  return Just(true);
203  }
204  }
205 }
206 
207 // static
208 Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::CheckPrivateNameStore(LookupIterator* it,
209  bool is_define) {
210  DCHECK(it->GetName()->IsPrivateName());
211  Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
212  DirectHandle<String> name_string(
213  Cast<String>(Cast<Symbol>(it->GetName())->description()), isolate);
214  for (;; it->Next()) {
215  switch (it->state()) {
216  case LookupIterator::TRANSITION:
217  case LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR:
218  case LookupIterator::JSPROXY:
219  case LookupIterator::TYPED_ARRAY_INDEX_NOT_FOUND:
220  case LookupIterator::ACCESSOR:
221  case LookupIterator::STRING_LOOKUP_START_OBJECT:
222  UNREACHABLE();
223  case LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK:
224  if (!it->HasAccess()) {
225  RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate,
226  isolate->ReportFailedAccessCheck(
227  Cast<JSObject>(it->GetReceiver())),
228  Nothing<bool>());
229  UNREACHABLE();
230  }
231  continue;
232  case LookupIterator::DATA:
233  if (is_define) {
234  MessageTemplate message =
235  it->GetName()->IsPrivateBrand()
236  ? MessageTemplate::kInvalidPrivateBrandReinitialization
237  : MessageTemplate::kInvalidPrivateFieldReinitialization;
238  RETURN_FAILURE(isolate,
239  GetShouldThrow(isolate, Nothing<ShouldThrow>()),
240  NewTypeError(message, name_string, it->GetReceiver()));
241  }
242  return Just(true);
243  case LookupIterator::WASM_OBJECT:
244  RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, kThrowOnError,
245  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kWasmObjectsAreOpaque));
246  case LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND:
247  if (!is_define) {
248  RETURN_FAILURE(
249  isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, Nothing<ShouldThrow>()),
250  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kInvalidPrivateMemberWrite,
251  name_string, it->GetReceiver()));
252 
253  } else if (it->ExtendingNonExtensible(
254  it->GetStoreTarget<JSReceiver>())) {
255  RETURN_FAILURE(
256  isolate, kThrowOnError,
257  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kDefineDisallowed, name_string));
258  }
259  return Just(true);
260  }
261  UNREACHABLE();
262  }
263 }

267 bool HasExcludedProperty(base::Vector<DirectHandle<Object>> excluded_properties,
268  DirectHandle<Object> search_element) {
269  // TODO(gsathya): Change this to be a hashtable.
270  for (DirectHandle<Object> object : excluded_properties) {
271  if (Object::SameValue(*search_element, *object)) {
272  return true;
273  }
274  }
275 
276  return false;
277 }
278 
279 // If direct handles are enabled, it is the responsibility of the caller to
280 // ensure that the memory pointed to by `excluded_properties` is scanned
281 // during CSS, e.g., it comes from a `DirectHandleVector<Object>`.
282 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT Maybe<bool> FastAssign(
283  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> target,
284  DirectHandle<Object> source, PropertiesEnumerationMode mode,
285  base::Vector<DirectHandle<Object>> excluded_properties, bool use_set) {
286  // Non-empty strings are the only non-JSReceivers that need to be handled
287  // explicitly by Object.assign.
288  if (!IsJSReceiver(*source)) {
289  return Just(!IsString(*source) || Cast<String>(*source)->length() == 0);
290  }
291 
292  // If the target is deprecated, the object will be updated on first store. If
293  // the source for that store equals the target, this will invalidate the
294  // cached representation of the source. Preventively upgrade the target.
295  // Do this on each iteration since any property load could cause deprecation.
296  if (target->map()->is_deprecated()) {
297  JSObject::MigrateInstance(isolate, Cast<JSObject>(target));
298  }
299 
300  DirectHandle<Map> map(Cast<JSReceiver>(*source)->map(), isolate);
301 
302  if (!IsJSObjectMap(*map)) return Just(false);
303  if (!map->OnlyHasSimpleProperties()) return Just(false);
304 
305  DirectHandle<JSObject> from = Cast<JSObject>(source);
306  if (from->elements() != ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).empty_fixed_array()) {
307  return Just(false);
308  }
309 
310  // We should never try to copy properties from an object itself.
311  CHECK_IMPLIES(!use_set, !target.is_identical_to(from));
312 
313  bool stable = true;
314 
315  // Process symbols last and only do that if we found symbols.
316  bool has_symbol = false;
317  bool process_symbol_only = false;
318  while (true) {
319  for (InternalIndex i : map->IterateOwnDescriptors()) {
320  HandleScope inner_scope(isolate);
321 
322  // The descriptor array is not cached on purpose since it has to stay in
323  // sync with map->instance_descriptors to avoid it from being pruned.
324  DirectHandle<Name> next_key(map->instance_descriptors(isolate)->GetKey(i),
325  isolate);
326  if (mode == PropertiesEnumerationMode::kEnumerationOrder) {
327  if (IsSymbol(*next_key)) {
328  has_symbol = true;
329  if (!process_symbol_only) continue;
330  } else {
331  if (process_symbol_only) continue;
332  }
333  }
334  DirectHandle<Object> prop_value;
335  // Directly decode from the descriptor array if |from| did not change
336  // shape.
337  if (stable) {
338  DCHECK_EQ(from->map(), *map);
339 
340  PropertyDetails details =
341  map->instance_descriptors(isolate)->GetDetails(i);
342  if (!details.IsEnumerable()) continue;
343  if (details.kind() == PropertyKind::kData) {
344  CHECK_EQ(details.location(), PropertyLocation::kField);
345  Representation representation = details.representation();
346  FieldIndex index = FieldIndex::ForPropertyIndex(
347  *map, details.field_index(), representation);
348  prop_value =
349  JSObject::FastPropertyAt(isolate, from, representation, index);
350  } else {
351  LookupIterator it(isolate, from, next_key,
352  LookupIterator::OWN_SKIP_INTERCEPTOR);
353  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
354  isolate, prop_value, Object::GetProperty(&it), Nothing<bool>());
355  stable = from->map() == *map;
356  }
357  } else {
358  // If the map did change, do a slower lookup. We are still guaranteed
359  // that the object has a simple shape, and that the key is a name.
360  LookupIterator it(isolate, from, next_key, from,
361  LookupIterator::OWN_SKIP_INTERCEPTOR);
362  if (!it.IsFound()) continue;
363  DCHECK(it.state() == LookupIterator::DATA ||
364  it.state() == LookupIterator::ACCESSOR);
365  if (!it.IsEnumerable()) continue;
366  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
367  isolate, prop_value, Object::GetProperty(&it), Nothing<bool>());
368  }
369 
370  if (use_set) {
371  // The lookup will walk the prototype chain, so we have to be careful
372  // to treat any key correctly for any receiver/holder.
373  PropertyKey key(isolate, next_key);
374  LookupIterator it(isolate, target, key);
375  Maybe<bool> result =
376  Object::SetProperty(&it, prop_value, StoreOrigin::kNamed,
377  Just(ShouldThrow::kThrowOnError));
378  if (result.IsNothing()) return result;
379  if (stable) {
380  stable = from->map() == *map;
381  }
382  } else {
383  // No element indexes should get here or the exclusion check may
384  // yield false negatives for type mismatch.
385  if (!excluded_properties.empty() &&
386  HasExcludedProperty(excluded_properties, next_key)) {
387  continue;
388  }
389 
390  // 4a ii 2. Perform ? CreateDataProperty(target, nextKey, propValue).
391  // This is an OWN lookup, so constructing a named-mode LookupIterator
392  // from {next_key} is safe.
393  CHECK(JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(isolate, target, next_key,
394  prop_value, Just(kThrowOnError))
395  .FromJust());
396  }
397  }
398  if (mode == PropertiesEnumerationMode::kEnumerationOrder) {
399  if (process_symbol_only || !has_symbol) {
400  return Just(true);
401  }
402  if (has_symbol) {
403  process_symbol_only = true;
404  }
405  } else {
406  DCHECK_EQ(mode, PropertiesEnumerationMode::kPropertyAdditionOrder);
407  return Just(true);
408  }
409  }
410  UNREACHABLE();
411 }
412 } // namespace

414 // static
415 Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::SetOrCopyDataProperties(
416  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> target,
417  DirectHandle<Object> source, PropertiesEnumerationMode mode,
418  base::Vector<DirectHandle<Object>> excluded_properties, bool use_set) {
419  Maybe<bool> fast_assign =
420  FastAssign(isolate, target, source, mode, excluded_properties, use_set);
421  if (fast_assign.IsNothing()) return Nothing<bool>();
422  if (fast_assign.FromJust()) return Just(true);
423 
424  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> from =
425  Object::ToObject(isolate, source).ToHandleChecked();
426 
427  // 3b. Let keys be ? from.[[OwnPropertyKeys]]().
428  DirectHandle<FixedArray> keys;
429  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
430  isolate, keys,
431  KeyAccumulator::GetKeys(isolate, from, KeyCollectionMode::kOwnOnly,
432  ALL_PROPERTIES, GetKeysConversion::kKeepNumbers),
433  Nothing<bool>());
434 
435  if (!from->HasFastProperties() && target->HasFastProperties() &&
436  IsJSObject(*target) && !IsJSGlobalProxy(*target)) {
437  // Convert to slow properties if we're guaranteed to overflow the number of
438  // descriptors.
439  int source_length;
440  if (IsJSGlobalObject(*from)) {
441  source_length = Cast<JSGlobalObject>(*from)
442  ->global_dictionary(kAcquireLoad)
443  ->NumberOfEnumerableProperties();
444  } else if constexpr (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
445  source_length =
446  from->property_dictionary_swiss()->NumberOfEnumerableProperties();
447  } else {
448  source_length =
449  from->property_dictionary()->NumberOfEnumerableProperties();
450  }
451  if (source_length > kMaxNumberOfDescriptors) {
452  JSObject::NormalizeProperties(isolate, Cast<JSObject>(target),
453  CLEAR_INOBJECT_PROPERTIES, source_length,
454  "Copying data properties");
455  }
456  }
457 
458  // 4. Repeat for each element nextKey of keys in List order,
459  for (int i = 0; i < keys->length(); ++i) {
460  DirectHandle<Object> next_key(keys->get(i), isolate);
461  if (!excluded_properties.empty() &&
462  HasExcludedProperty(excluded_properties, next_key)) {
463  continue;
464  }
465 
466  // 4a i. Let desc be ? from.[[GetOwnProperty]](nextKey).
467  PropertyDescriptor desc;
468  Maybe<bool> found =
469  JSReceiver::GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(isolate, from, next_key, &desc);
470  if (found.IsNothing()) return Nothing<bool>();
471  // 4a ii. If desc is not undefined and desc.[[Enumerable]] is true, then
472  if (found.FromJust() && desc.enumerable()) {
473  // 4a ii 1. Let propValue be ? Get(from, nextKey).
474  DirectHandle<Object> prop_value;
475  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
476  isolate, prop_value,
477  Runtime::GetObjectProperty(isolate, from, next_key), Nothing<bool>());
478 
479  if (use_set) {
480  // 4c ii 2. Let status be ? Set(to, nextKey, propValue, true).
481  DirectHandle<Object> status;
482  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
483  isolate, status,
484  Runtime::SetObjectProperty(isolate, target, next_key, prop_value,
485  StoreOrigin::kMaybeKeyed,
486  Just(ShouldThrow::kThrowOnError)),
487  Nothing<bool>());
488  } else {
489  // 4a ii 2. Perform ! CreateDataProperty(target, nextKey, propValue).
490  PropertyKey key(isolate, next_key);
491  CHECK(JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(isolate, target, key, prop_value,
492  Just(kThrowOnError))
493  .FromJust());
494  }
495  }
496  }
497 
498  return Just(true);
499 }
500 
501 Tagged<String> JSReceiver::class_name() {
502  ReadOnlyRoots roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
503  if (IsJSFunctionOrBoundFunctionOrWrappedFunction(*this)) {
504  return roots.Function_string();
505  }
506  if (IsJSArgumentsObject(*this)) return roots.Arguments_string();
507  if (IsJSArray(*this)) return roots.Array_string();
508  if (IsJSArrayBuffer(*this)) {
509  if (Cast<JSArrayBuffer>(*this)->is_shared()) {
510  return roots.SharedArrayBuffer_string();
511  }
512  return roots.ArrayBuffer_string();
513  }
514  if (IsJSArrayIterator(*this)) return roots.ArrayIterator_string();
515  if (IsJSDate(*this)) return roots.Date_string();
516  if (IsJSError(*this)) return roots.Error_string();
517  if (IsJSGeneratorObject(*this)) return roots.Generator_string();
518  if (IsJSMap(*this)) return roots.Map_string();
519  if (IsJSMapIterator(*this)) return roots.MapIterator_string();
520  if (IsJSProxy(*this)) {
521  return map()->is_callable() ? roots.Function_string()
522  : roots.Object_string();
523  }
524  if (IsJSRegExp(*this)) return roots.RegExp_string();
525  if (IsJSSet(*this)) return roots.Set_string();
526  if (IsJSSetIterator(*this)) return roots.SetIterator_string();
527  if (IsJSTypedArray(*this)) {
528 #define SWITCH_KIND(Type, type, TYPE, ctype) \
529  if (map()->elements_kind() == TYPE##_ELEMENTS) { \
530  return roots.Type##Array_string(); \
531  }
532  TYPED_ARRAYS(SWITCH_KIND)
533 #undef SWITCH_KIND
534  }
535  if (IsJSPrimitiveWrapper(*this)) {
536  Tagged<Object> value = Cast<JSPrimitiveWrapper>(*this)->value();
537  if (IsBoolean(value)) return roots.Boolean_string();
538  if (IsString(value)) return roots.String_string();
539  if (IsNumber(value)) return roots.Number_string();
540  if (IsBigInt(value)) return roots.BigInt_string();
541  if (IsSymbol(value)) return roots.Symbol_string();
542  if (IsScript(value)) return roots.Script_string();
543  UNREACHABLE();
544  }
545  if (IsJSWeakMap(*this)) return roots.WeakMap_string();
546  if (IsJSWeakSet(*this)) return roots.WeakSet_string();
547  if (IsJSGlobalProxy(*this)) return roots.global_string();
548  if (IsShared(*this)) {
549  if (IsJSSharedStruct(*this)) return roots.SharedStruct_string();
550  if (IsJSSharedArray(*this)) return roots.SharedArray_string();
551  if (IsJSAtomicsMutex(*this)) return roots.AtomicsMutex_string();
552  if (IsJSAtomicsCondition(*this)) return roots.AtomicsCondition_string();
553  // Other shared values are primitives.
554  UNREACHABLE();
555  }
556 
557  return roots.Object_string();
558 }

560 namespace {
561 std::pair<MaybeDirectHandle<JSFunction>, DirectHandle<String>>
562 GetConstructorHelper(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver) {
563  // If the object was instantiated simply with base == new.target, the
564  // constructor on the map provides the most accurate name.
565  // Don't provide the info for prototypes, since their constructors are
566  // reclaimed and replaced by Object in OptimizeAsPrototype.
567  if (!IsJSProxy(*receiver) && receiver->map()->new_target_is_base() &&
568  !receiver->map()->is_prototype_map()) {
569  DirectHandle<Object> maybe_constructor(receiver->map()->GetConstructor(),
570  isolate);
571  if (IsJSFunction(*maybe_constructor)) {
572  DirectHandle<JSFunction> constructor =
573  Cast<JSFunction>(maybe_constructor);
574  Handle<String> name = SharedFunctionInfo::DebugName(
575  isolate, direct_handle(constructor->shared(), isolate));
576  if (name->length() != 0 &&
577  !name->Equals(ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).Object_string())) {
578  return std::make_pair(indirect_handle(constructor, isolate), name);
579  }
580  } else if (IsFunctionTemplateInfo(*maybe_constructor)) {
581  DirectHandle<FunctionTemplateInfo> function_template =
582  Cast<FunctionTemplateInfo>(maybe_constructor);
583  if (!IsUndefined(function_template->class_name(), isolate)) {
584  return std::make_pair(
585  MaybeHandle<JSFunction>(),
586  handle(Cast<String>(function_template->class_name()), isolate));
587  }
588  }
589  }
590 
591  for (PrototypeIterator it(isolate, receiver, kStartAtReceiver); !it.IsAtEnd();
592  it.AdvanceIgnoringProxies()) {
593  auto current = PrototypeIterator::GetCurrent<JSReceiver>(it);
594 
595  LookupIterator it_to_string_tag(
596  isolate, receiver, isolate->factory()->to_string_tag_symbol(), current,
597  LookupIterator::OWN_SKIP_INTERCEPTOR);
598  auto maybe_to_string_tag = JSReceiver::GetDataProperty(
599  &it_to_string_tag, AllocationPolicy::kAllocationDisallowed);
600  if (IsString(*maybe_to_string_tag)) {
601  return std::make_pair(MaybeHandle<JSFunction>(),
602  Cast<String>(maybe_to_string_tag));
603  }
604 
605  // Consider the following example:
606  //
607  // function A() {}
608  // function B() {}
609  // B.prototype = new A();
610  // B.prototype.constructor = B;
611  //
612  // The constructor name for `B.prototype` must yield "A", so we don't take
613  // "constructor" into account for the receiver itself, but only starting
614  // on the prototype chain.
615  if (!receiver.is_identical_to(current)) {
616  LookupIterator it_constructor(
617  isolate, receiver, isolate->factory()->constructor_string(), current,
618  LookupIterator::OWN_SKIP_INTERCEPTOR);
619  auto maybe_constructor = JSReceiver::GetDataProperty(
620  &it_constructor, AllocationPolicy::kAllocationDisallowed);
621  if (IsJSFunction(*maybe_constructor)) {
622  auto constructor = Cast<JSFunction>(maybe_constructor);
623  auto name = SharedFunctionInfo::DebugName(
624  isolate, direct_handle(constructor->shared(), isolate));
625 
626  if (name->length() != 0 &&
627  !name->Equals(ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).Object_string())) {
628  return std::make_pair(constructor, name);
629  }
630  }
631  }
632  }
633 
634  return std::make_pair(MaybeHandle<JSFunction>(),
635  handle(receiver->class_name(), isolate));
636 }
637 } // anonymous namespace
638 
639 // static
640 MaybeDirectHandle<JSFunction> JSReceiver::GetConstructor(
641  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver) {
642  return GetConstructorHelper(isolate, receiver).first;
643 }
644 
645 // static
646 DirectHandle<String> JSReceiver::GetConstructorName(
647  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver) {
648  return GetConstructorHelper(isolate, receiver).second;
649 }
650 
651 // static
652 MaybeDirectHandle<NativeContext> JSReceiver::GetFunctionRealm(
653  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver) {
654  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::Current();
655  // This is implemented as a loop because it's possible to construct very
656  // long chains of bound functions or proxies where a recursive implementation
657  // would run out of stack space.
658  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
659  Tagged<JSReceiver> current = *receiver;
660  do {
661  DCHECK(current->map()->is_constructor());
662  InstanceType instance_type = current->map()->instance_type();
663  if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSProxy(instance_type)) {
664  Tagged<JSProxy> proxy = Cast<JSProxy>(current);
665  if (proxy->IsRevoked()) {
666  AllowGarbageCollection allow_allocating_errors;
667  THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kProxyRevoked));
668  }
669  current = Cast<JSReceiver>(proxy->target());
670  continue;
671  }
672  if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSFunction(instance_type)) {
673  Tagged<JSFunction> function = Cast<JSFunction>(current);
674  return direct_handle(function->native_context(), isolate);
675  }
676  if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSBoundFunction(instance_type)) {
677  Tagged<JSBoundFunction> function = Cast<JSBoundFunction>(current);
678  current = function->bound_target_function();
679  continue;
680  }
681  if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSWrappedFunction(instance_type)) {
682  Tagged<JSWrappedFunction> function = Cast<JSWrappedFunction>(current);
683  current = function->wrapped_target_function();
684  continue;
685  }
686  Tagged<JSObject> object = Cast<JSObject>(current);
687  DCHECK(!IsJSFunction(object));
688  return object->GetCreationContext(isolate);
689  } while (true);
690 }
691 
692 // static
693 MaybeHandle<NativeContext> JSReceiver::GetContextForMicrotask(
694  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver) {
695  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::Current();
696  while (IsJSBoundFunction(*receiver) || IsJSProxy(*receiver)) {
697  if (IsJSBoundFunction(*receiver)) {
698  receiver = direct_handle(
699  Cast<JSBoundFunction>(receiver)->bound_target_function(), isolate);
700  } else {
701  DCHECK(IsJSProxy(*receiver));
702  DirectHandle<Object> target(Cast<JSProxy>(receiver)->target(), isolate);
703  if (!IsJSReceiver(*target)) return MaybeHandle<NativeContext>();
704  receiver = Cast<JSReceiver>(target);
705  }
706  }
707 
708  if (!IsJSFunction(*receiver)) return MaybeHandle<NativeContext>();
709  return handle(Cast<JSFunction>(receiver)->native_context(), isolate);
710 }
711 
712 Maybe<PropertyAttributes> JSReceiver::GetPropertyAttributes(
713  LookupIterator* it) {
714  for (;; it->Next()) {
715  switch (it->state()) {
716  case LookupIterator::TRANSITION:
717  case LookupIterator::STRING_LOOKUP_START_OBJECT:
718  UNREACHABLE();
719  case LookupIterator::JSPROXY:
720  return JSProxy::GetPropertyAttributes(it);
721  case LookupIterator::WASM_OBJECT:
722  return Just(ABSENT);
723  case LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR: {
724  Maybe<PropertyAttributes> result =
725  JSObject::GetPropertyAttributesWithInterceptor(it);
726  if (result.IsNothing()) return result;
727  if (result.FromJust() != ABSENT) return result;
728  continue;
729  }
730  case LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK:
731  if (it->HasAccess()) continue;
732  return JSObject::GetPropertyAttributesWithFailedAccessCheck(it);
733  case LookupIterator::TYPED_ARRAY_INDEX_NOT_FOUND:
734  return Just(ABSENT);
735  case LookupIterator::ACCESSOR:
736  if (IsJSModuleNamespace(*it->GetHolder<Object>())) {
737  return JSModuleNamespace::GetPropertyAttributes(it);
738  } else {
739  return Just(it->property_attributes());
740  }
741  case LookupIterator::DATA:
742  return Just(it->property_attributes());
743  case LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND:
744  return Just(ABSENT);
745  }
746  UNREACHABLE();
747  }
748 }

750 namespace {
751 
752 Tagged<Object> SetHashAndUpdateProperties(Tagged<HeapObject> properties,
753  int hash) {
754  DCHECK_NE(PropertyArray::kNoHashSentinel, hash);
755  DCHECK(PropertyArray::HashField::is_valid(hash));
756 
757  ReadOnlyRoots roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
758  if (properties == roots.empty_fixed_array() ||
759  properties == roots.empty_property_array() ||
760  properties == roots.empty_property_dictionary() ||
761  properties == roots.empty_swiss_property_dictionary()) {
762  return Smi::FromInt(hash);
763  }
764 
765  if (IsPropertyArray(properties)) {
766  Cast<PropertyArray>(properties)->SetHash(hash);
767  DCHECK_LT(0, Cast<PropertyArray>(properties)->length());
768  return properties;
769  }
770 
771  if (IsGlobalDictionary(properties)) {
772  Cast<GlobalDictionary>(properties)->SetHash(hash);
773  return properties;
774  }
775 
776  DCHECK(IsPropertyDictionary(properties));
777  Cast<PropertyDictionary>(properties)->SetHash(hash);
778 
779  return properties;
780 }
781 
782 int GetIdentityHashHelper(Tagged<JSReceiver> object) {
783  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
784  Tagged<Object> properties = object->raw_properties_or_hash();
785  if (IsSmi(properties)) {
786  return Smi::ToInt(properties);
787  }
788 
789  if (IsPropertyArray(properties)) {
790  return Cast<PropertyArray>(properties)->Hash();
791  }
792 
793  if (IsPropertyDictionary(properties)) {
794  return Cast<PropertyDictionary>(properties)->Hash();
795  }
796 
797  if (IsGlobalDictionary(properties)) {
798  return Cast<GlobalDictionary>(properties)->Hash();
799  }
800 
801 #ifdef DEBUG
802  ReadOnlyRoots roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
803  DCHECK(properties == roots.empty_fixed_array() ||
804  properties == roots.empty_property_dictionary() ||
805  properties == roots.empty_swiss_property_dictionary());
806 #endif
807 
808  return PropertyArray::kNoHashSentinel;
809 }
810 } // namespace
811 
812 void JSReceiver::SetIdentityHash(int hash) {
813  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
814  DCHECK_NE(PropertyArray::kNoHashSentinel, hash);
815  DCHECK(PropertyArray::HashField::is_valid(hash));
816 
817  Tagged<HeapObject> existing_properties =
818  Cast<HeapObject>(raw_properties_or_hash());
819  Tagged<Object> new_properties =
820  SetHashAndUpdateProperties(existing_properties, hash);
821  set_raw_properties_or_hash(new_properties, kRelaxedStore);
822 }
823 
824 void JSReceiver::SetProperties(Tagged<HeapObject> properties) {
825  DCHECK_IMPLIES(IsPropertyArray(properties) &&
826  Cast<PropertyArray>(properties)->length() == 0,
827  properties == GetReadOnlyRoots().empty_property_array());
828  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
829  int hash = GetIdentityHashHelper(*this);
830  Tagged<Object> new_properties = properties;
831 
832  // TODO(cbruni): Make GetIdentityHashHelper return a bool so that we
833  // don't have to manually compare against kNoHashSentinel.
834  if (hash != PropertyArray::kNoHashSentinel) {
835  new_properties = SetHashAndUpdateProperties(properties, hash);
836  }
837 
838  set_raw_properties_or_hash(new_properties, kRelaxedStore);
839 }
840 
841 Tagged<Object> JSReceiver::GetIdentityHash() {
842  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
843 
844  int hash = GetIdentityHashHelper(*this);
845  if (hash == PropertyArray::kNoHashSentinel) {
846  return GetReadOnlyRoots().undefined_value();
847  }
848 
849  return Smi::FromInt(hash);
850 }
851 
852 // static
853 Tagged<Smi> JSReceiver::CreateIdentityHash(Isolate* isolate,
854  Tagged<JSReceiver> key) {
855  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
856  int hash = isolate->GenerateIdentityHash(PropertyArray::HashField::kMax);
857  DCHECK_NE(PropertyArray::kNoHashSentinel, hash);
858 
859  key->SetIdentityHash(hash);
860  return Smi::FromInt(hash);
861 }
862 
863 Tagged<Smi> JSReceiver::GetOrCreateIdentityHash(Isolate* isolate) {
864  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
865 
866  int hash = GetIdentityHashHelper(*this);
867  if (hash != PropertyArray::kNoHashSentinel) {
868  return Smi::FromInt(hash);
869  }
870 
871  return JSReceiver::CreateIdentityHash(isolate, *this);
872 }
873 
874 void JSReceiver::DeleteNormalizedProperty(DirectHandle<JSReceiver> object,
875  InternalIndex entry) {
876  DCHECK(!object->HasFastProperties());
877  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::Current();
878  DCHECK(entry.is_found());
879 
880  if (IsJSGlobalObject(*object)) {
881  // If we have a global object, invalidate the cell and remove it from the
882  // global object's dictionary.
883  DirectHandle<GlobalDictionary> dictionary(
884  Cast<JSGlobalObject>(*object)->global_dictionary(kAcquireLoad),
885  isolate);
886 
887  DirectHandle<PropertyCell> cell(dictionary->CellAt(entry), isolate);
888 
889  DirectHandle<GlobalDictionary> new_dictionary =
890  GlobalDictionary::DeleteEntry(isolate, dictionary, entry);
891  Cast<JSGlobalObject>(*object)->set_global_dictionary(*new_dictionary,
892  kReleaseStore);
893 
894  cell->ClearAndInvalidate(isolate);
895  } else {
896  if constexpr (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
897  DirectHandle<SwissNameDictionary> dictionary(
898  object->property_dictionary_swiss(), isolate);
899 
900  dictionary = SwissNameDictionary::DeleteEntry(isolate, dictionary, entry);
901  object->SetProperties(*dictionary);
902  } else {
903  DirectHandle<NameDictionary> dictionary(object->property_dictionary(),
904  isolate);
905 
906  dictionary = NameDictionary::DeleteEntry(isolate, dictionary, entry);
907  object->SetProperties(*dictionary);
908  }
909  }
910  if (object->map()->is_prototype_map()) {
911  // Invalidate prototype validity cell as this may invalidate transitioning
912  // store IC handlers.
913  JSObject::InvalidatePrototypeChains(object->map());
914  }
915 }
916 
917 Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::DeleteProperty(LookupIterator* it,
918  LanguageMode language_mode) {
919  it->UpdateProtector();
920 
921  Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
922 
923  if (it->state() == LookupIterator::JSPROXY) {
924  return JSProxy::DeletePropertyOrElement(it->GetHolder<JSProxy>(),
925  it->GetName(), language_mode);
926  }
927 
928  if (IsJSProxy(*it->GetReceiver())) {
929  if (it->state() != LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND) {
930  DCHECK_EQ(LookupIterator::DATA, it->state());
931  DCHECK(it->name()->IsPrivate());
932  it->Delete();
933  }
934  return Just(true);
935  }
936 
937  for (;; it->Next()) {
938  switch (it->state()) {
939  case LookupIterator::JSPROXY:
940  case LookupIterator::TRANSITION:
941  case LookupIterator::STRING_LOOKUP_START_OBJECT:
942  UNREACHABLE();
943  case LookupIterator::WASM_OBJECT:
944  RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, kThrowOnError,
945  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kWasmObjectsAreOpaque));
946  case LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK:
947  if (it->HasAccess()) continue;
948  RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
949  isolate,
950  isolate->ReportFailedAccessCheck(it->GetHolder<JSObject>()),
951  Nothing<bool>());
952  UNREACHABLE();
953  case LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR: {
954  ShouldThrow should_throw =
955  is_sloppy(language_mode) ? kDontThrow : kThrowOnError;
956  InterceptorResult result;
957  if (!JSObject::DeletePropertyWithInterceptor(it, should_throw)
958  .To(&result)) {
959  // An exception was thrown in the interceptor. Propagate.
960  return Nothing<bool>();
961  }
962  switch (result) {
963  case InterceptorResult::kFalse:
964  return Just(false);
965  case InterceptorResult::kTrue:
966  return Just(true);
967  case InterceptorResult::kNotIntercepted:
968  // Proceed lookup.
969  continue;
970  }
971  UNREACHABLE();
972  }
973  case LookupIterator::TYPED_ARRAY_INDEX_NOT_FOUND:
974  return Just(true);
975  case LookupIterator::DATA:
976  case LookupIterator::ACCESSOR: {
977  DirectHandle<JSObject> holder = it->GetHolder<JSObject>();
978  if (!it->IsConfigurable() ||
979  (IsJSTypedArray(*holder) && it->IsElement(*holder))) {
980  // Fail if the property is not configurable if the property is a
981  // TypedArray element.
982  if (is_strict(language_mode)) {
983  isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
984  MessageTemplate::kStrictDeleteProperty, it->GetName(),
985  it->GetReceiver()));
986  return Nothing<bool>();
987  }
988  return Just(false);
989  }
990 
991  it->Delete();
992 
993  return Just(true);
994  }
995  case LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND:
996  return Just(true);
997  }
998  UNREACHABLE();
999  }
1000 }

1004  uint32_t index,
1005  LanguageMode language_mode) {
1006  LookupIterator it(isolate, object, index, object, LookupIterator::OWN);

1034 // ES6 19.1.2.4
1035 // static
1036 Tagged<Object> JSReceiver::DefineProperty(Isolate* isolate,
1037  DirectHandle<Object> object,
1038  DirectHandle<Object> key,
1039  Handle<Object> attributes) {
1040  // 1. If Type(O) is not Object, throw a TypeError exception.
1041  if (!IsJSReceiver(*object)) {
1042  DirectHandle<String> fun_name =
1043  isolate->factory()->InternalizeUtf8String("Object.defineProperty");
1044  THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_FAILURE(
1045  isolate, NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kCalledOnNonObject, fun_name));
1046  }
1047  // 2. Let key be ToPropertyKey(P).
1048  // 3. ReturnIfAbrupt(key).
1049  ASSIGN_RETURN_FAILURE_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, key,
1050  Object::ToPropertyKey(isolate, key));
1051  // 4. Let desc be ToPropertyDescriptor(Attributes).
1052  // 5. ReturnIfAbrupt(desc).
1053  PropertyDescriptor desc;
1054  if (!PropertyDescriptor::ToPropertyDescriptor(
1055  isolate, Cast<JSAny>(attributes), &desc)) {
1056  return ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).exception();
1057  }
1058  // 6. Let success be DefinePropertyOrThrow(O,key, desc).
1059  Maybe<bool> success = DefineOwnProperty(isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(object),
1060  key, &desc, Just(kThrowOnError));
1061  // 7. ReturnIfAbrupt(success).
1062  MAYBE_RETURN(success, ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).exception());
1063  CHECK(success.FromJust());
1064  // 8. Return O.
1065  return *object;
1066 }
1067 
1068 // ES6 19.1.2.3.1
1069 // static
1070 MaybeDirectHandle<Object> JSReceiver::DefineProperties(
1071  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Object> object,
1072  DirectHandle<Object> properties) {
1073  // 1. If Type(O) is not Object, throw a TypeError exception.
1074  if (!IsJSReceiver(*object)) {
1075  DirectHandle<String> fun_name =
1076  isolate->factory()->InternalizeUtf8String("Object.defineProperties");
1077  THROW_NEW_ERROR(
1078  isolate, NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kCalledOnNonObject, fun_name));
1079  }
1080  // 2. Let props be ToObject(Properties).
1081  // 3. ReturnIfAbrupt(props).
1082  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> props;
1083  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, props,
1084  Object::ToObject(isolate, properties));
1085 
1086  // 4. Let keys be props.[[OwnPropertyKeys]]().
1087  // 5. ReturnIfAbrupt(keys).
1088  DirectHandle<FixedArray> keys;
1089  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
1090  isolate, keys,
1091  KeyAccumulator::GetKeys(isolate, props, KeyCollectionMode::kOwnOnly,
1092  ALL_PROPERTIES));
1093  // 6. Let descriptors be an empty List.s
1094  int capacity = keys->length();
1095  std::vector<PropertyDescriptor> descriptors(capacity);
1096  size_t descriptors_index = 0;
1097  // 7. Repeat for each element nextKey of keys in List order,
1098  for (int i = 0; i < keys->length(); ++i) {
1099  DirectHandle<JSAny> next_key(Cast<JSAny>(keys->get(i)), isolate);
1100  // 7a. Let propDesc be props.[[GetOwnProperty]](nextKey).
1101  // 7b. ReturnIfAbrupt(propDesc).
1102  PropertyKey key(isolate, next_key);
1103  LookupIterator it(isolate, props, key, LookupIterator::OWN);
1104  Maybe<PropertyAttributes> maybe = JSReceiver::GetPropertyAttributes(&it);
1105  if (maybe.IsNothing()) return MaybeDirectHandle<Object>();
1106  PropertyAttributes attrs = maybe.FromJust();
1107  // 7c. If propDesc is not undefined and propDesc.[[Enumerable]] is true:
1108  if (attrs == ABSENT) continue;
1109  if (attrs & DONT_ENUM) continue;
1110  // 7c i. Let descObj be Get(props, nextKey).
1111  // 7c ii. ReturnIfAbrupt(descObj).
1112  Handle<JSAny> desc_obj;
1113  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, desc_obj,
1114  Cast<JSAny>(Object::GetProperty(&it)));
1115  // 7c iii. Let desc be ToPropertyDescriptor(descObj).
1116  bool success = PropertyDescriptor::ToPropertyDescriptor(
1117  isolate, desc_obj, &descriptors[descriptors_index]);
1118  // 7c iv. ReturnIfAbrupt(desc).
1119  if (!success) return MaybeDirectHandle<Object>();
1120  // 7c v. Append the pair (a two element List) consisting of nextKey and
1121  // desc to the end of descriptors.
1122  descriptors[descriptors_index].set_name(next_key);
1123  descriptors_index++;
1124  }
1125  // 8. For each pair from descriptors in list order,
1126  for (size_t i = 0; i < descriptors_index; ++i) {
1127  PropertyDescriptor* desc = &descriptors[i];
1128  // 8a. Let P be the first element of pair.
1129  // 8b. Let desc be the second element of pair.
1130  // 8c. Let status be DefinePropertyOrThrow(O, P, desc).
1131  Maybe<bool> status =
1132  DefineOwnProperty(isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(object), desc->name(), desc,
1133  Just(kThrowOnError));
1134  // 8d. ReturnIfAbrupt(status).
1135  if (status.IsNothing()) return MaybeDirectHandle<Object>();
1136  CHECK(status.FromJust());
1137  }
1138  // 9. Return o.
1139  return object;
1140 }
1141 
1142 // static
1143 Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::DefineOwnProperty(Isolate* isolate,
1144  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> object,
1145  DirectHandle<Object> key,
1146  PropertyDescriptor* desc,
1147  Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
1148  if (IsJSArray(*object)) {
1149  return JSArray::DefineOwnProperty(isolate, Cast<JSArray>(object), key, desc,
1150  should_throw);
1151  }
1152  if (IsJSProxy(*object)) {
1153  return JSProxy::DefineOwnProperty(isolate, Cast<JSProxy>(object), key, desc,
1154  should_throw);
1155  }
1156  if (IsJSTypedArray(*object)) {
1157  return JSTypedArray::DefineOwnProperty(isolate, Cast<JSTypedArray>(object),
1158  key, desc, should_throw);
1159  }
1160  if (IsJSModuleNamespace(*object)) {
1161  return JSModuleNamespace::DefineOwnProperty(
1162  isolate, Cast<JSModuleNamespace>(object), key, desc, should_throw);
1163  }
1164  if (IsWasmObject(*object)) {
1165  RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, kThrowOnError,
1166  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kWasmObjectsAreOpaque));
1167  }
1168  if (IsAlwaysSharedSpaceJSObject(*object)) {
1169  return AlwaysSharedSpaceJSObject::DefineOwnProperty(
1170  isolate, Cast<AlwaysSharedSpaceJSObject>(object), key, desc,
1171  should_throw);
1172  }
1173 
1174  // OrdinaryDefineOwnProperty, by virtue of calling
1175  // DefineOwnPropertyIgnoreAttributes, can handle arguments
1176  // (ES#sec-arguments-exotic-objects-defineownproperty-p-desc).
1177  return OrdinaryDefineOwnProperty(isolate, Cast<JSObject>(object), key, desc,
1178  should_throw);
1179 }
1180 
1181 // static
1182 Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::OrdinaryDefineOwnProperty(
1183  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object, DirectHandle<Object> key,
1184  PropertyDescriptor* desc, Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
1185  DCHECK(IsName(*key) || IsNumber(*key)); // |key| is a PropertyKey.
1186  PropertyKey lookup_key(isolate, key);
1187  return OrdinaryDefineOwnProperty(isolate, object, lookup_key, desc,
1188  should_throw);
1189 }

1191 namespace {
1192 
1193 MaybeHandle<JSAny> GetPropertyWithInterceptorInternal(
1194  LookupIterator* it, DirectHandle<InterceptorInfo> interceptor, bool* done) {
1195  *done = false;
1196  Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
1197  // Make sure that the top context does not change when doing callbacks or
1198  // interceptor calls.
1199  AssertNoContextChange ncc(isolate);
1200 
1201  if (!interceptor->has_getter()) {
1202  return isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
1203  }
1204 
1205  DirectHandle<JSObject> holder = it->GetHolder<JSObject>();
1206  DirectHandle<JSAny> result;
1207  DirectHandle<Object> receiver = it->GetReceiver();
1208  if (!IsJSReceiver(*receiver)) {
1209  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, receiver,
1210  Object::ConvertReceiver(isolate, receiver));
1211  }
1212  PropertyCallbackArguments args(isolate, interceptor->data(), *receiver,
1213  *holder, Just(kDontThrow));
1214 
1215  if (it->IsElement(*holder)) {
1216  result = args.CallIndexedGetter(interceptor, it->array_index());
1217  } else {
1218  result = args.CallNamedGetter(interceptor, it->name());
1219  }
1220  // An exception was thrown in the interceptor. Propagate.
1221  RETURN_VALUE_IF_EXCEPTION_DETECTOR(isolate, args, kNullMaybeHandle);
1222  if (result.is_null()) return isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
1223  *done = true;
1224  args.AcceptSideEffects();
1225  // Rebox handle before return
1226  return handle(*result, isolate);
1227 }
1228 
1229 Maybe<PropertyAttributes> GetPropertyAttributesWithInterceptorInternal(
1230  LookupIterator* it, DirectHandle<InterceptorInfo> interceptor) {
1231  Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
1232  // Make sure that the top context does not change when doing
1233  // callbacks or interceptor calls.
1234  AssertNoContextChange ncc(isolate);
1235  HandleScope scope(isolate);
1236 
1237  DirectHandle<JSObject> holder = it->GetHolder<JSObject>();
1238  DCHECK_IMPLIES(!it->IsElement(*holder) && IsSymbol(*it->name()),
1239  interceptor->can_intercept_symbols());
1240  DirectHandle<Object> receiver = it->GetReceiver();
1241  if (!IsJSReceiver(*receiver)) {
1242  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate, receiver,
1243  Object::ConvertReceiver(isolate, receiver),
1244  Nothing<PropertyAttributes>());
1245  }
1246  PropertyCallbackArguments args(isolate, interceptor->data(), *receiver,
1247  *holder, Just(kDontThrow));
1248  if (interceptor->has_query()) {
1249  DirectHandle<Object> result;
1250  if (it->IsElement(*holder)) {
1251  result = args.CallIndexedQuery(interceptor, it->array_index());
1252  } else {
1253  result = args.CallNamedQuery(interceptor, it->name());
1254  }
1255  // An exception was thrown in the interceptor. Propagate.
1256  RETURN_VALUE_IF_EXCEPTION_DETECTOR(isolate, args,
1257  Nothing<PropertyAttributes>());
1258 
1259  if (!result.is_null()) {
1260  int32_t value;
1261  CHECK(Object::ToInt32(*result, &value));
1262  DCHECK_IMPLIES((value & ~PropertyAttributes::ALL_ATTRIBUTES_MASK) != 0,
1263  value == PropertyAttributes::ABSENT);
1264  // In case of absent property side effects are not allowed.
1265  // TODO(ishell): PropertyAttributes::ABSENT is not exposed in the Api,
1266  // so it can't be officially returned. We should fix the tests instead.
1267  if (value != PropertyAttributes::ABSENT) {
1268  args.AcceptSideEffects();
1269  }
1270  return Just(static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(value));
1271  }
1272  } else if (interceptor->has_getter()) {
1273  // TODO(verwaest): Use GetPropertyWithInterceptor?
1274  DirectHandle<Object> result;
1275  if (it->IsElement(*holder)) {
1276  result = args.CallIndexedGetter(interceptor, it->array_index());
1277  } else {
1278  result = args.CallNamedGetter(interceptor, it->name());
1279  }
1280  // An exception was thrown in the interceptor. Propagate.
1281  RETURN_VALUE_IF_EXCEPTION_DETECTOR(isolate, args,
1282  Nothing<PropertyAttributes>());
1283 
1284  if (!result.is_null()) {
1285  args.AcceptSideEffects();
1286  return Just(DONT_ENUM);
1287  }
1288  }
1289  return Just(ABSENT);
1290 }
1291 
1292 Maybe<InterceptorResult> SetPropertyWithInterceptorInternal(
1293  LookupIterator* it, DirectHandle<InterceptorInfo> interceptor,
1294  Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw, DirectHandle<Object> value) {
1295  Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
1296  // Make sure that the top context does not change when doing callbacks or
1297  // interceptor calls.
1298  AssertNoContextChange ncc(isolate);
1299 
1300  if (!interceptor->has_setter()) {
1301  return Just(InterceptorResult::kNotIntercepted);
1302  }
1303 
1304  DirectHandle<JSObject> holder = it->GetHolder<JSObject>();
1305  DirectHandle<Object> receiver = it->GetReceiver();
1306  if (!IsJSReceiver(*receiver)) {
1307  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate, receiver,
1308  Object::ConvertReceiver(isolate, receiver),
1309  Nothing<InterceptorResult>());
1310  }
1311  PropertyCallbackArguments args(isolate, interceptor->data(), *receiver,
1312  *holder, should_throw);
1313 
1314  v8::Intercepted intercepted =
1315  it->IsElement(*holder)
1316  ? args.CallIndexedSetter(interceptor, it->array_index(), value)
1317  : args.CallNamedSetter(interceptor, it->name(), value);
1318 
1319  return args.GetBooleanReturnValue(intercepted, "Setter");
1320 }
1321 
1322 Maybe<InterceptorResult> DefinePropertyWithInterceptorInternal(
1323  LookupIterator* it, DirectHandle<InterceptorInfo> interceptor,
1324  Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw, PropertyDescriptor* desc) {
1325  Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
1326  // Make sure that the top context does not change when doing callbacks or
1327  // interceptor calls.
1328  AssertNoContextChange ncc(isolate);
1329 
1330  if (!interceptor->has_definer()) {
1331  return Just(InterceptorResult::kNotIntercepted);
1332  }
1333 
1334  DirectHandle<JSObject> holder = it->GetHolder<JSObject>();
1335  DirectHandle<Object> receiver = it->GetReceiver();
1336  if (!IsJSReceiver(*receiver)) {
1337  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate, receiver,
1338  Object::ConvertReceiver(isolate, receiver),
1339  Nothing<InterceptorResult>());
1340  }
1341 
1342  std::unique_ptr<v8::PropertyDescriptor> descriptor(
1343  new v8::PropertyDescriptor());
1344  if (PropertyDescriptor::IsAccessorDescriptor(desc)) {
1345  DirectHandle<Object> getter = desc->get();
1346  if (!getter.is_null() && IsFunctionTemplateInfo(*getter)) {
1347  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
1348  isolate, getter,
1349  ApiNatives::InstantiateFunction(isolate,
1350  Cast<FunctionTemplateInfo>(getter),
1351  MaybeDirectHandle<Name>()),
1352  Nothing<InterceptorResult>());
1353  }
1354  DirectHandle<Object> setter = desc->set();
1355  if (!setter.is_null() && IsFunctionTemplateInfo(*setter)) {
1356  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
1357  isolate, setter,
1358  ApiNatives::InstantiateFunction(isolate,
1359  Cast<FunctionTemplateInfo>(setter),
1360  MaybeDirectHandle<Name>()),
1361  Nothing<InterceptorResult>());
1362  }
1363  descriptor.reset(new v8::PropertyDescriptor(v8::Utils::ToLocal(getter),
1364  v8::Utils::ToLocal(setter)));
1365  } else if (PropertyDescriptor::IsDataDescriptor(desc)) {
1366  if (desc->has_writable()) {
1367  descriptor.reset(new v8::PropertyDescriptor(
1368  v8::Utils::ToLocal(desc->value()), desc->writable()));
1369  } else {
1370  descriptor.reset(
1371  new v8::PropertyDescriptor(v8::Utils::ToLocal(desc->value())));
1372  }
1373  }
1374  if (desc->has_enumerable()) {
1375  descriptor->set_enumerable(desc->enumerable());
1376  }
1377  if (desc->has_configurable()) {
1378  descriptor->set_configurable(desc->configurable());
1379  }
1380 
1381  PropertyCallbackArguments args(isolate, interceptor->data(), *receiver,
1382  *holder, should_throw);
1383 
1384  v8::Intercepted intercepted =
1385  it->IsElement(*holder)
1386  ? args.CallIndexedDefiner(interceptor, it->array_index(), *descriptor)
1387  : args.CallNamedDefiner(interceptor, it->name(), *descriptor);
1388 
1389  return args.GetBooleanReturnValue(intercepted, "Definer");
1390 }
1391 
1392 } // namespace
1393 
1394 // ES6 9.1.6.1
1395 // static
1396 Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::OrdinaryDefineOwnProperty(
1397  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object, const PropertyKey& key,
1398  PropertyDescriptor* desc, Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
1399  LookupIterator it(isolate, object, key, LookupIterator::OWN);
1400 
1401  // Deal with access checks first.
1402  while (it.state() == LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK) {
1403  if (!it.HasAccess()) {
1404  RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
1405  isolate, isolate->ReportFailedAccessCheck(it.GetHolder<JSObject>()),
1406  Nothing<bool>());
1407  UNREACHABLE();
1408  }
1409  it.Next();
1410  }
1411 
1412  // 1. Let current be O.[[GetOwnProperty]](P).
1413  // 2. ReturnIfAbrupt(current).
1414  PropertyDescriptor current;
1415  MAYBE_RETURN(GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(&it, &current), Nothing<bool>());
1416 
1417  // TODO(jkummerow/verwaest): It would be nice if we didn't have to reset
1418  // the iterator every time. Currently, the reasons why we need it are because
1419  // GetOwnPropertyDescriptor can have side effects, namely:
1420  // - Interceptors
1421  // - Accessors (which might change the holder's map)
1422  it.Restart();
1423 
1424  // Skip over the access check after restarting -- we've already checked it.
1425  while (it.state() == LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK) {
1426  DCHECK(it.HasAccess());
1427  it.Next();
1428  }
1429 
1430  // Handle interceptor.
1431  if (it.state() == LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR) {
1432  if (it.HolderIsReceiverOrHiddenPrototype()) {
1433  InterceptorResult result;
1434  if (!DefinePropertyWithInterceptorInternal(&it, it.GetInterceptor(),
1435  should_throw, desc)
1436  .To(&result)) {
1437  // An exception was thrown in the interceptor. Propagate.
1438  return Nothing<bool>();
1439  }
1440  switch (result) {
1441  case InterceptorResult::kFalse:
1442  return Just(false);
1443  case InterceptorResult::kTrue:
1444  return Just(true);
1445 
1446  case InterceptorResult::kNotIntercepted:
1447  // Proceed lookup.
1448  break;
1449  }
1450  // We need to restart the lookup in case the interceptor ran with side
1451  // effects.
1452  it.Restart();
1453  }
1454  }
1455 
1456  // 3. Let extensible be the value of the [[Extensible]] internal slot of O.
1457  bool extensible = JSObject::IsExtensible(isolate, object);
1458 
1459  return ValidateAndApplyPropertyDescriptor(isolate, &it, extensible, desc,
1460  &current, should_throw, {});
1461 }
1462 
1463 // ES6 9.1.6.2
1464 // static
1465 Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::IsCompatiblePropertyDescriptor(
1466  Isolate* isolate, bool extensible, PropertyDescriptor* desc,
1467  PropertyDescriptor* current, DirectHandle<Name> property_name,
1468  Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
1469  // 1. Return ValidateAndApplyPropertyDescriptor(undefined, undefined,
1470  // Extensible, Desc, Current).
1471  return ValidateAndApplyPropertyDescriptor(
1472  isolate, nullptr, extensible, desc, current, should_throw, property_name);
1473 }
1474 
1475 // https://tc39.es/ecma262/#sec-validateandapplypropertydescriptor
1476 // static
1477 Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::ValidateAndApplyPropertyDescriptor(
1478  Isolate* isolate, LookupIterator* it, bool extensible,
1479  PropertyDescriptor* desc, PropertyDescriptor* current,
1480  Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw, DirectHandle<Name> property_name) {
1481  // We either need a LookupIterator, or a property name.
1482  DCHECK((it == nullptr) != property_name.is_null());
1483  bool desc_is_data_descriptor = PropertyDescriptor::IsDataDescriptor(desc);
1484  bool desc_is_accessor_descriptor =
1485  PropertyDescriptor::IsAccessorDescriptor(desc);
1486  bool desc_is_generic_descriptor =
1487  PropertyDescriptor::IsGenericDescriptor(desc);
1488  // 1. (Assert)
1489  // 2. If current is undefined, then
1490  if (current->is_empty()) {
1491  // 2a. If extensible is false, return false.
1492  if (!extensible) {
1493  RETURN_FAILURE(
1494  isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, should_throw),
1495  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kDefineDisallowed,
1496  it != nullptr ? it->GetName() : property_name));
1497  }
1498  // 2c. If IsGenericDescriptor(Desc) or IsDataDescriptor(Desc) is true, then:
1499  // (This is equivalent to !IsAccessorDescriptor(desc).)
1500  DCHECK_EQ(desc_is_generic_descriptor || desc_is_data_descriptor,
1501  !desc_is_accessor_descriptor);
1502  if (!desc_is_accessor_descriptor) {
1503  // 2c i. If O is not undefined, create an own data property named P of
1504  // object O whose [[Value]], [[Writable]], [[Enumerable]] and
1505  // [[Configurable]] attribute values are described by Desc. If the value
1506  // of an attribute field of Desc is absent, the attribute of the newly
1507  // created property is set to its default value.
1508  if (it != nullptr) {
1509  if (!desc->has_writable()) desc->set_writable(false);
1510  if (!desc->has_enumerable()) desc->set_enumerable(false);
1511  if (!desc->has_configurable()) desc->set_configurable(false);
1512  DirectHandle<Object> value(
1513  desc->has_value()
1514  ? desc->value()
1515  : Cast<Object>(isolate->factory()->undefined_value()));
1516  MaybeDirectHandle<Object> result =
1517  JSObject::DefineOwnPropertyIgnoreAttributes(it, value,
1518  desc->ToAttributes());
1519  if (result.is_null()) return Nothing<bool>();
1520  }
1521  } else {
1522  // 2d. Else Desc must be an accessor Property Descriptor,
1523  DCHECK(desc_is_accessor_descriptor);
1524  // 2d i. If O is not undefined, create an own accessor property named P
1525  // of object O whose [[Get]], [[Set]], [[Enumerable]] and
1526  // [[Configurable]] attribute values are described by Desc. If the value
1527  // of an attribute field of Desc is absent, the attribute of the newly
1528  // created property is set to its default value.
1529  if (it != nullptr) {
1530  if (!desc->has_enumerable()) desc->set_enumerable(false);
1531  if (!desc->has_configurable()) desc->set_configurable(false);
1532  DirectHandle<Object> getter(
1533  desc->has_get() ? desc->get()
1534  : Cast<Object>(isolate->factory()->null_value()));
1535  DirectHandle<Object> setter(
1536  desc->has_set() ? desc->set()
1537  : Cast<Object>(isolate->factory()->null_value()));
1538  MaybeDirectHandle<Object> result =
1539  JSObject::DefineOwnAccessorIgnoreAttributes(it, getter, setter,
1540  desc->ToAttributes());
1541  if (result.is_null()) return Nothing<bool>();
1542  }
1543  }
1544  // 2e. Return true.
1545  return Just(true);
1546  }
1547  // 3. If every field in Desc is absent, return true. (This also has a shortcut
1548  // not in the spec: if every field value matches the current value, return.)
1549  if ((!desc->has_enumerable() ||
1550  desc->enumerable() == current->enumerable()) &&
1551  (!desc->has_configurable() ||
1552  desc->configurable() == current->configurable()) &&
1553  !desc->has_value() &&
1554  (!desc->has_writable() ||
1555  (current->has_writable() && current->writable() == desc->writable())) &&
1556  (!desc->has_get() ||
1557  (current->has_get() &&
1558  Object::SameValue(*current->get(), *desc->get()))) &&
1559  (!desc->has_set() ||
1560  (current->has_set() &&
1561  Object::SameValue(*current->set(), *desc->set())))) {
1562  return Just(true);
1563  }
1564  // 4. If current.[[Configurable]] is false, then
1565  if (!current->configurable()) {
1566  // 4a. If Desc.[[Configurable]] is present and its value is true, return
1567  // false.
1568  if (desc->has_configurable() && desc->configurable()) {
1569  RETURN_FAILURE(
1570  isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, should_throw),
1571  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kRedefineDisallowed,
1572  it != nullptr ? it->GetName() : property_name));
1573  }
1574  // 4b. If Desc.[[Enumerable]] is present and
1575  // ! SameValue(Desc.[[Enumerable]], current.[[Enumerable]]) is false, return
1576  // false.
1577  if (desc->has_enumerable() && desc->enumerable() != current->enumerable()) {
1578  RETURN_FAILURE(
1579  isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, should_throw),
1580  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kRedefineDisallowed,
1581  it != nullptr ? it->GetName() : property_name));
1582  }
1583  }
1584 
1585  bool current_is_data_descriptor =
1586  PropertyDescriptor::IsDataDescriptor(current);
1587  // 5. If ! IsGenericDescriptor(Desc) is true, no further validation is
1588  // required.
1589  if (desc_is_generic_descriptor) {
1590  // Nothing to see here.
1591 
1592  // 6. Else if ! SameValue(!IsDataDescriptor(current),
1593  // !IsDataDescriptor(Desc)) is false, the
1594  } else if (current_is_data_descriptor != desc_is_data_descriptor) {
1595  // 6a. If current.[[Configurable]] is false, return false.
1596  if (!current->configurable()) {
1597  RETURN_FAILURE(
1598  isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, should_throw),
1599  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kRedefineDisallowed,
1600  it != nullptr ? it->GetName() : property_name));
1601  }
1602  // 6b. If IsDataDescriptor(current) is true, then:
1603  if (current_is_data_descriptor) {
1604  // 6b i. If O is not undefined, convert the property named P of object O
1605  // from a data property to an accessor property. Preserve the existing
1606  // values of the converted property's [[Configurable]] and [[Enumerable]]
1607  // attributes and set the rest of the property's attributes to their
1608  // default values.
1609  // --> Folded into step 9
1610  } else {
1611  // 6c i. If O is not undefined, convert the property named P of object O
1612  // from an accessor property to a data property. Preserve the existing
1613  // values of the converted property’s [[Configurable]] and [[Enumerable]]
1614  // attributes and set the rest of the property’s attributes to their
1615  // default values.
1616  // --> Folded into step 9
1617  }
1618 
1619  // 7. Else if IsDataDescriptor(current) and IsDataDescriptor(Desc) are both
1620  // true, then:
1621  } else if (current_is_data_descriptor && desc_is_data_descriptor) {
1622  // 7a. If current.[[Configurable]] is false and current.[[Writable]] is
1623  // false, then
1624  if (!current->configurable() && !current->writable()) {
1625  // 7a i. If Desc.[[Writable]] is present and Desc.[[Writable]] is true,
1626  // return false.
1627  if (desc->has_writable() && desc->writable()) {
1628  RETURN_FAILURE(
1629  isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, should_throw),
1630  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kRedefineDisallowed,
1631  it != nullptr ? it->GetName() : property_name));
1632  }
1633  // 7a ii. If Desc.[[Value]] is present and SameValue(Desc.[[Value]],
1634  // current.[[Value]]) is false, return false.
1635  if (desc->has_value()) {
1636  // We'll succeed applying the property, but the value is already the
1637  // same and the property is read-only, so skip actually writing the
1638  // property. Otherwise we may try to e.g., write to frozen elements.
1639  if (Object::SameValue(*desc->value(), *current->value()))
1640  return Just(true);
1641  RETURN_FAILURE(
1642  isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, should_throw),
1643  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kRedefineDisallowed,
1644  it != nullptr ? it->GetName() : property_name));
1645  }
1646  }
1647  } else {
1648  // 8. Else,
1649  // 8a. Assert: ! IsAccessorDescriptor(current) and
1650  // ! IsAccessorDescriptor(Desc) are both true.
1651  DCHECK(PropertyDescriptor::IsAccessorDescriptor(current) &&
1652  desc_is_accessor_descriptor);
1653  // 8b. If current.[[Configurable]] is false, then:
1654  if (!current->configurable()) {
1655  // 8a i. If Desc.[[Set]] is present and SameValue(Desc.[[Set]],
1656  // current.[[Set]]) is false, return false.
1657  if (desc->has_set() &&
1658  !Object::SameValue(*desc->set(), *current->set())) {
1659  RETURN_FAILURE(
1660  isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, should_throw),
1661  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kRedefineDisallowed,
1662  it != nullptr ? it->GetName() : property_name));
1663  }
1664  // 8a ii. If Desc.[[Get]] is present and SameValue(Desc.[[Get]],
1665  // current.[[Get]]) is false, return false.
1666  if (desc->has_get() &&
1667  !Object::SameValue(*desc->get(), *current->get())) {
1668  RETURN_FAILURE(
1669  isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, should_throw),
1670  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kRedefineDisallowed,
1671  it != nullptr ? it->GetName() : property_name));
1672  }
1673  }
1674  }
1675 
1676  // 9. If O is not undefined, then:
1677  if (it != nullptr) {
1678  // 9a. For each field of Desc that is present, set the corresponding
1679  // attribute of the property named P of object O to the value of the field.
1680  PropertyAttributes attrs = NONE;
1681 
1682  if (desc->has_enumerable()) {
1683  attrs = static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(
1684  attrs | (desc->enumerable() ? NONE : DONT_ENUM));
1685  } else {
1686  attrs = static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(
1687  attrs | (current->enumerable() ? NONE : DONT_ENUM));
1688  }
1689  if (desc->has_configurable()) {
1690  attrs = static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(
1691  attrs | (desc->configurable() ? NONE : DONT_DELETE));
1692  } else {
1693  attrs = static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(
1694  attrs | (current->configurable() ? NONE : DONT_DELETE));
1695  }
1696  if (desc_is_data_descriptor ||
1697  (desc_is_generic_descriptor && current_is_data_descriptor)) {
1698  if (desc->has_writable()) {
1699  attrs = static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(
1700  attrs | (desc->writable() ? NONE : READ_ONLY));
1701  } else {
1702  attrs = static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(
1703  attrs | (current->writable() ? NONE : READ_ONLY));
1704  }
1705  DirectHandle<Object> value(
1706  desc->has_value() ? desc->value()
1707  : current->has_value()
1708  ? current->value()
1709  : Cast<Object>(isolate->factory()->undefined_value()));
1710  return JSObject::DefineOwnPropertyIgnoreAttributes(it, value, attrs,
1711  should_throw);
1712  } else {
1713  DCHECK(desc_is_accessor_descriptor ||
1714  (desc_is_generic_descriptor &&
1715  PropertyDescriptor::IsAccessorDescriptor(current)));
1716  DirectHandle<Object> getter(
1717  desc->has_get() ? desc->get()
1718  : current->has_get()
1719  ? current->get()
1720  : Cast<Object>(isolate->factory()->null_value()));
1721  DirectHandle<Object> setter(
1722  desc->has_set() ? desc->set()
1723  : current->has_set()
1724  ? current->set()
1725  : Cast<Object>(isolate->factory()->null_value()));
1726  MaybeDirectHandle<Object> result =
1727  JSObject::DefineOwnAccessorIgnoreAttributes(it, getter, setter,
1728  attrs);
1729  if (result.is_null()) return Nothing<bool>();
1730  }
1731  }
1732 
1733  // 10. Return true.
1734  return Just(true);
1735 }

1742  Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {

1748 Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(Isolate* isolate,

1761 // static
1762 Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(Isolate* isolate,
1763  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> object,
1764  PropertyKey key,
1765  DirectHandle<Object> value,
1766  Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
1767  if (IsJSObject(*object)) {
1768  return JSObject::CreateDataProperty(isolate, Cast<JSObject>(object), key,
1769  value, should_throw); // Shortcut.
1770  }
1771 
1772  PropertyDescriptor new_desc;
1773  new_desc.set_value(Cast<JSAny>(value));
1774  new_desc.set_writable(true);
1775  new_desc.set_enumerable(true);
1776  new_desc.set_configurable(true);
1777 
1778  return JSReceiver::DefineOwnProperty(isolate, object, key.GetName(isolate),
1779  &new_desc, should_throw);
1780 }
1781 
1782 // static
1783 Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::AddPrivateField(LookupIterator* it,
1784  DirectHandle<Object> value,
1785  Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
1786  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver = Cast<JSReceiver>(it->GetReceiver());
1787  DCHECK(!IsAlwaysSharedSpaceJSObject(*receiver));
1788  Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
1789  DCHECK(it->GetName()->IsPrivateName());
1790  DirectHandle<Symbol> symbol = Cast<Symbol>(it->GetName());
1791 
1792  switch (it->state()) {
1793  case LookupIterator::JSPROXY: {
1794  PropertyDescriptor new_desc;
1795  new_desc.set_value(Cast<JSAny>(value));
1796  new_desc.set_writable(true);
1797  new_desc.set_enumerable(true);
1798  new_desc.set_configurable(true);
1799  return JSProxy::SetPrivateSymbol(isolate, Cast<JSProxy>(receiver), symbol,
1800  &new_desc, should_throw);
1801  }
1802  case LookupIterator::WASM_OBJECT:
1803  RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, kThrowOnError,
1804  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kWasmObjectsAreOpaque));
1805  case LookupIterator::DATA:
1806  case LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR:
1807  case LookupIterator::ACCESSOR:
1808  case LookupIterator::TYPED_ARRAY_INDEX_NOT_FOUND:
1809  case LookupIterator::STRING_LOOKUP_START_OBJECT:
1810  UNREACHABLE();
1811 
1812  case LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK: {
1813  if (!it->HasAccess()) {
1814  RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
1815  isolate,
1816  it->isolate()->ReportFailedAccessCheck(it->GetHolder<JSObject>()),
1817  Nothing<bool>());
1818  UNREACHABLE();
1819  }
1820  break;
1821  }
1822 
1823  case LookupIterator::TRANSITION:
1824  case LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND:
1825  break;
1826  }
1827 
1828  return Object::TransitionAndWriteDataProperty(it, value, NONE, should_throw,
1829  StoreOrigin::kMaybeKeyed);
1830 }
1831 
1832 // static
1833 Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(
1834  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> object, DirectHandle<Object> key,
1835  PropertyDescriptor* desc) {
1836  DCHECK(IsName(*key) || IsNumber(*key)); // |key| is a PropertyKey.
1837  PropertyKey lookup_key(isolate, key);
1838  LookupIterator it(isolate, object, lookup_key, LookupIterator::OWN);
1839  return GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(&it, desc);
1840 }
1841 
1842 namespace {
1843 
1844 Maybe<bool> GetPropertyDescriptorWithInterceptor(LookupIterator* it,
1845  PropertyDescriptor* desc) {
1846  DirectHandle<InterceptorInfo> interceptor;
1847 
1848  while (it->state() == LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK) {
1849  if (it->HasAccess()) {
1850  it->Next();
1851  } else {
1852  interceptor = it->GetInterceptorForFailedAccessCheck();
1853  if (interceptor.is_null()) {
1854  it->Restart();
1855  return Just(false);
1856  }
1857  CHECK(!interceptor.is_null());
1858  break;
1859  }
1860  }
1861  if (it->state() == LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR) {
1862  interceptor = it->GetInterceptor();
1863  }
1864  if (interceptor.is_null()) return Just(false);
1865  Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
1866  if (!interceptor->has_descriptor()) return Just(false);
1867 
1868  Handle<JSAny> result;
1869  DirectHandle<JSObject> holder = it->GetHolder<JSObject>();
1870 
1871  DirectHandle<Object> receiver = it->GetReceiver();
1872  if (!IsJSReceiver(*receiver)) {
1873  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate, receiver,
1874  Object::ConvertReceiver(isolate, receiver),
1875  Nothing<bool>());
1876  }
1877 
1878  PropertyCallbackArguments args(isolate, interceptor->data(), *receiver,
1879  *holder, Just(kDontThrow));
1880  if (it->IsElement(*holder)) {
1881  result = args.CallIndexedDescriptor(interceptor, it->array_index());
1882  } else {
1883  result = args.CallNamedDescriptor(interceptor, it->name());
1884  }
1885  // An exception was thrown in the interceptor. Propagate.
1886  RETURN_VALUE_IF_EXCEPTION_DETECTOR(isolate, args, Nothing<bool>());
1887  if (!result.is_null()) {
1888  // Request was successfully intercepted, try to set the property
1889  // descriptor.
1890  args.AcceptSideEffects();
1891  Utils::ApiCheck(
1892  PropertyDescriptor::ToPropertyDescriptor(isolate, result, desc),
1893  it->IsElement(*holder) ? "v8::IndexedPropertyDescriptorCallback"
1894  : "v8::NamedPropertyDescriptorCallback",
1895  "Invalid property descriptor.");
1896 
1897  return Just(true);
1898  }
1899 
1900  it->Next();
1901  return Just(false);
1902 }
1903 } // namespace
1904 
1905 // ES6 9.1.5.1
1906 // Returns true on success, false if the property didn't exist, nothing if
1907 // an exception was thrown.
1908 // static
1909 Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(LookupIterator* it,
1910  PropertyDescriptor* desc) {
1911  Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
1912  // "Virtual" dispatch.
1913  if (it->IsFound() && IsJSProxy(*it->GetHolder<JSReceiver>())) {
1914  return JSProxy::GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(isolate, it->GetHolder<JSProxy>(),
1915  it->GetName(), desc);
1916  }
1917 
1918  Maybe<bool> intercepted = GetPropertyDescriptorWithInterceptor(it, desc);
1919  MAYBE_RETURN(intercepted, Nothing<bool>());
1920  if (intercepted.FromJust()) {
1921  return Just(true);
1922  }
1923 
1924  // Request was not intercepted, continue as normal.
1925  // 1. (Assert)
1926  // 2. If O does not have an own property with key P, return undefined.
1927  Maybe<PropertyAttributes> maybe = JSObject::GetPropertyAttributes(it);
1928  MAYBE_RETURN(maybe, Nothing<bool>());
1929  PropertyAttributes attrs = maybe.FromJust();
1930  if (attrs == ABSENT) return Just(false);
1931  DCHECK(!isolate->has_exception());
1932 
1933  // 3. Let D be a newly created Property Descriptor with no fields.
1934  DCHECK(desc->is_empty());
1935  // 4. Let X be O's own property whose key is P.
1936  // 5. If X is a data property, then
1937  bool is_accessor_pair = it->state() == LookupIterator::ACCESSOR &&
1938  IsAccessorPair(*it->GetAccessors());
1939  if (!is_accessor_pair) {
1940  // 5a. Set D.[[Value]] to the value of X's [[Value]] attribute.
1941  DirectHandle<JSAny> value;
1942  if (!Cast<JSAny>(Object::GetProperty(it)).ToHandle(&value)) {
1943  DCHECK(isolate->has_exception());
1944  return Nothing<bool>();
1945  }
1946  desc->set_value(value);
1947  // 5b. Set D.[[Writable]] to the value of X's [[Writable]] attribute
1948  desc->set_writable((attrs & READ_ONLY) == 0);
1949  } else {
1950  // 6. Else X is an accessor property, so
1951  auto accessors = Cast<AccessorPair>(it->GetAccessors());
1952  DirectHandle<NativeContext> holder_realm(
1953  it->GetHolder<JSReceiver>()->GetCreationContext().value(), isolate);
1954  // 6a. Set D.[[Get]] to the value of X's [[Get]] attribute.
1955  desc->set_get(AccessorPair::GetComponent(isolate, holder_realm, accessors,
1956  ACCESSOR_GETTER));
1957  // 6b. Set D.[[Set]] to the value of X's [[Set]] attribute.
1958  desc->set_set(AccessorPair::GetComponent(isolate, holder_realm, accessors,
1959  ACCESSOR_SETTER));
1960  }
1961 
1962  // 7. Set D.[[Enumerable]] to the value of X's [[Enumerable]] attribute.
1963  desc->set_enumerable((attrs & DONT_ENUM) == 0);
1964  // 8. Set D.[[Configurable]] to the value of X's [[Configurable]] attribute.
1965  desc->set_configurable((attrs & DONT_DELETE) == 0);
1966  // 9. Return D.
1967  DCHECK(PropertyDescriptor::IsAccessorDescriptor(desc) !=
1968  PropertyDescriptor::IsDataDescriptor(desc));
1969  return Just(true);
1970 }
1971 
1972 Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::SetIntegrityLevel(Isolate* isolate,
1973  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver,
1974  IntegrityLevel level,
1975  ShouldThrow should_throw) {
1976  DCHECK(level == SEALED || level == FROZEN);
1977 
1978  if (IsJSObject(*receiver)) {
1979  DirectHandle<JSObject> object = Cast<JSObject>(receiver);
1980 
1981  if (!object->HasSloppyArgumentsElements() &&
1982  !IsJSModuleNamespace(*object)) { // Fast path.
1983  // Prevent memory leaks by not adding unnecessary transitions.
1984  Maybe<bool> test = JSObject::TestIntegrityLevel(isolate, object, level);
1985  MAYBE_RETURN(test, Nothing<bool>());
1986  if (test.FromJust()) return test;
1987 
1988  if (level == SEALED) {
1989  return JSObject::PreventExtensionsWithTransition<SEALED>(
1990  isolate, object, should_throw);
1991  } else {
1992  return JSObject::PreventExtensionsWithTransition<FROZEN>(
1993  isolate, object, should_throw);
1994  }
1995  }
1996  }
1997 
1998  MAYBE_RETURN(JSReceiver::PreventExtensions(isolate, receiver, should_throw),
1999  Nothing<bool>());
2000 
2001  DirectHandle<FixedArray> keys;
2002  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2003  isolate, keys, JSReceiver::OwnPropertyKeys(isolate, receiver),
2004  Nothing<bool>());
2005 
2006  PropertyDescriptor no_conf;
2007  no_conf.set_configurable(false);
2008 
2009  PropertyDescriptor no_conf_no_write;
2010  no_conf_no_write.set_configurable(false);
2011  no_conf_no_write.set_writable(false);
2012 
2013  if (level == SEALED) {
2014  for (int i = 0; i < keys->length(); ++i) {
2015  DirectHandle<Object> key(keys->get(i), isolate);
2016  MAYBE_RETURN(DefineOwnProperty(isolate, receiver, key, &no_conf,
2017  Just(kThrowOnError)),
2018  Nothing<bool>());
2019  }
2020  return Just(true);
2021  }
2022 
2023  for (int i = 0; i < keys->length(); ++i) {
2024  DirectHandle<Object> key(keys->get(i), isolate);
2025  PropertyDescriptor current_desc;
2026  Maybe<bool> owned = JSReceiver::GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(
2027  isolate, receiver, key, &current_desc);
2028  MAYBE_RETURN(owned, Nothing<bool>());
2029  if (owned.FromJust()) {
2030  PropertyDescriptor desc =
2031  PropertyDescriptor::IsAccessorDescriptor(&current_desc)
2032  ? no_conf
2033  : no_conf_no_write;
2034  MAYBE_RETURN(
2035  DefineOwnProperty(isolate, receiver, key, &desc, Just(kThrowOnError)),
2036  Nothing<bool>());
2037  }
2038  }
2039  return Just(true);
2040 }
2041 
2042 namespace {
2043 Maybe<bool> GenericTestIntegrityLevel(Isolate* isolate,
2044  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver,
2045  PropertyAttributes level) {
2046  DCHECK(level == SEALED || level == FROZEN);
2047 
2048  Maybe<bool> extensible = JSReceiver::IsExtensible(isolate, receiver);
2049  MAYBE_RETURN(extensible, Nothing<bool>());
2050  if (extensible.FromJust()) return Just(false);
2051 
2052  DirectHandle<FixedArray> keys;
2053  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2054  isolate, keys, JSReceiver::OwnPropertyKeys(isolate, receiver),
2055  Nothing<bool>());
2056 
2057  for (int i = 0; i < keys->length(); ++i) {
2058  DirectHandle<Object> key(keys->get(i), isolate);
2059  PropertyDescriptor current_desc;
2060  Maybe<bool> owned = JSReceiver::GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(
2061  isolate, receiver, key, &current_desc);
2062  MAYBE_RETURN(owned, Nothing<bool>());
2063  if (owned.FromJust()) {
2064  if (current_desc.configurable()) return Just(false);
2065  if (level == FROZEN &&
2066  PropertyDescriptor::IsDataDescriptor(&current_desc) &&
2067  current_desc.writable()) {
2068  return Just(false);
2069  }
2070  }
2071  }
2072  return Just(true);
2073 }
2074 
2075 } // namespace
2076 
2077 Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::TestIntegrityLevel(Isolate* isolate,
2078  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver,
2079  IntegrityLevel level) {
2080  if (!IsCustomElementsReceiverMap(receiver->map())) {
2081  return JSObject::TestIntegrityLevel(isolate, Cast<JSObject>(receiver),
2082  level);
2083  }
2084  return GenericTestIntegrityLevel(isolate, receiver, level);
2085 }

2087 Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::PreventExtensions(Isolate* isolate,
2088  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> object,
2089  ShouldThrow should_throw) {
2090  if (IsJSProxy(*object)) {
2091  return JSProxy::PreventExtensions(Cast<JSProxy>(object), should_throw);
2092  }
2093  if (IsWasmObject(*object)) {
2094  RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, kThrowOnError,
2095  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kWasmObjectsAreOpaque));
2096  }
2097  DCHECK(IsJSObject(*object));
2098  return JSObject::PreventExtensions(isolate, Cast<JSObject>(object),
2099  should_throw);
2100 }

2102 Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::IsExtensible(Isolate* isolate,
2103  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> object) {
2104  if (IsJSProxy(*object)) {
2105  return JSProxy::IsExtensible(Cast<JSProxy>(object));
2106  }
2107  if (IsWasmObject(*object)) {
2108  return Just(false);
2109  }
2110  return Just(JSObject::IsExtensible(isolate, Cast<JSObject>(object)));
