2113 // static
2114 template <template <typename> typename HandleType>
2115  requires(
2116  std::is_convertible_v<HandleType<JSReceiver>, DirectHandle<JSReceiver>>)
2117 typename HandleType<Object>::MaybeType JSReceiver::ToPrimitive(
2118  Isolate* isolate, HandleType<JSReceiver> receiver, ToPrimitiveHint hint) {
2119  DirectHandle<Object> exotic_to_prim;
2120  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
2121  isolate, exotic_to_prim,
2122  Object::GetMethod(isolate, receiver,
2123  isolate->factory()->to_primitive_symbol()));
2124  if (!IsUndefined(*exotic_to_prim, isolate)) {
2125  DirectHandle<Object> hint_string =
2126  isolate->factory()->ToPrimitiveHintString(hint);
2127  HandleType<Object> result;
2128  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
2129  isolate, result,
2130  Execution::Call(isolate, exotic_to_prim, receiver, {&hint_string, 1}));
2131  if (IsPrimitive(*result)) return result;
2132  THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate,
2133  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kCannotConvertToPrimitive));
2134  }
2135  return OrdinaryToPrimitive<HandleType>(
2136  isolate, receiver,
2137  (hint == ToPrimitiveHint::kString) ? OrdinaryToPrimitiveHint::kString
2138  : OrdinaryToPrimitiveHint::kNumber);
2139 }
2140 
2141 template MaybeDirectHandle<Object> JSReceiver::ToPrimitive(
2142  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver, ToPrimitiveHint hint);
2143 template MaybeIndirectHandle<Object> JSReceiver::ToPrimitive(
2144  Isolate* isolate, IndirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver,
2145  ToPrimitiveHint hint);
2146 
2147 // static
2148 template <template <typename> typename HandleType>
2149  requires(std::is_convertible_v<HandleType<Object>, DirectHandle<Object>>)
2150 typename HandleType<Object>::MaybeType JSReceiver::OrdinaryToPrimitive(
2151  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver,
2152  OrdinaryToPrimitiveHint hint) {
2153  DirectHandle<String> method_names[2];
2154  switch (hint) {
2155  case OrdinaryToPrimitiveHint::kNumber:
2156  method_names[0] = isolate->factory()->valueOf_string();
2157  method_names[1] = isolate->factory()->toString_string();
2158  break;
2159  case OrdinaryToPrimitiveHint::kString:
2160  method_names[0] = isolate->factory()->toString_string();
2161  method_names[1] = isolate->factory()->valueOf_string();
2162  break;
2163  }
2164  for (DirectHandle<String> name : method_names) {
2165  DirectHandle<Object> method;
2166  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
2167  isolate, method, JSReceiver::GetProperty(isolate, receiver, name));
2168  if (IsCallable(*method)) {
2169  HandleType<Object> result;
2170  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
2171  isolate, result, Execution::Call(isolate, method, receiver, {}));
2172  if (IsPrimitive(*result)) return result;
2173  }
2174  }
2175  THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate,
2176  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kCannotConvertToPrimitive));
2177 }
2178 
2179 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT Maybe<bool> FastGetOwnValuesOrEntries(
2180  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> receiver, bool get_entries,
2181  Handle<FixedArray>* result) {
2182  DirectHandle<Map> map(Cast<JSReceiver>(*receiver)->map(), isolate);
2183 
2184  if (!IsJSObjectMap(*map)) return Just(false);
2185  if (!map->OnlyHasSimpleProperties()) return Just(false);
2186 
2187  DirectHandle<JSObject> object(Cast<JSObject>(*receiver), isolate);
2188  DirectHandle<DescriptorArray> descriptors(map->instance_descriptors(isolate),
2189  isolate);
2190 
2191  int number_of_own_descriptors = map->NumberOfOwnDescriptors();
2192  size_t number_of_own_elements =
2193  object->GetElementsAccessor()->GetCapacity(*object, object->elements());
2194 
2195  if (number_of_own_elements >
2196  static_cast<size_t>(FixedArray::kMaxLength - number_of_own_descriptors)) {
2197  isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewRangeError(
2198  MessageTemplate::kInvalidArrayLength));
2199  return Nothing<bool>();
2200  }
2201  // The static cast is safe after the range check right above.
2202  Handle<FixedArray> values_or_entries = isolate->factory()->NewFixedArray(
2203  static_cast<int>(number_of_own_descriptors + number_of_own_elements));
2204  int count = 0;
2205 
2206  if (object->elements() != ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).empty_fixed_array()) {
2207  MAYBE_RETURN(object->GetElementsAccessor()->CollectValuesOrEntries(
2208  isolate, object, values_or_entries, get_entries, &count,
2209  ENUMERABLE_STRINGS),
2210  Nothing<bool>());
2211  }
2212 
2213  // We may have already lost stability, if CollectValuesOrEntries had
2214  // side-effects.
2215  bool stable = *map == object->map();
2216  if (stable) {
2217  descriptors.SetValue(map->instance_descriptors(isolate));
2218  }
2219 
2220  for (InternalIndex index : InternalIndex::Range(number_of_own_descriptors)) {
2221  HandleScope inner_scope(isolate);
2222 
2223  DirectHandle<Name> next_key(descriptors->GetKey(index), isolate);
2224  if (!IsString(*next_key)) continue;
2225  DirectHandle<Object> prop_value;
2226 
2227  // Directly decode from the descriptor array if |from| did not change shape.
2228  if (stable) {
2229  DCHECK_EQ(object->map(), *map);
2230  DCHECK_EQ(*descriptors, map->instance_descriptors(isolate));
2231 
2232  PropertyDetails details = descriptors->GetDetails(index);
2233  if (!details.IsEnumerable()) continue;
2234  if (details.kind() == PropertyKind::kData) {
2235  if (details.location() == PropertyLocation::kDescriptor) {
2236  prop_value =
2237  direct_handle(descriptors->GetStrongValue(index), isolate);
2238  } else {
2239  Representation representation = details.representation();
2240  FieldIndex field_index = FieldIndex::ForPropertyIndex(
2241  *map, details.field_index(), representation);
2242  prop_value = JSObject::FastPropertyAt(isolate, object, representation,
2243  field_index);
2244  }
2245  } else {
2246  LookupIterator it(isolate, object, next_key,
2247  LookupIterator::OWN_SKIP_INTERCEPTOR);
2248  DCHECK_EQ(LookupIterator::ACCESSOR, it.state());
2249  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2250  isolate, prop_value, Object::GetProperty(&it), Nothing<bool>());
2251  stable = object->map() == *map;
2252  descriptors.SetValue(map->instance_descriptors(isolate));
2253  }
2254  } else {
2255  // If the map did change, do a slower lookup. We are still guaranteed that
2256  // the object has a simple shape, and that the key is a name.
2257  LookupIterator it(isolate, object, next_key,
2258  LookupIterator::OWN_SKIP_INTERCEPTOR);
2259  if (!it.IsFound()) continue;
2260  DCHECK(it.state() == LookupIterator::DATA ||
2261  it.state() == LookupIterator::ACCESSOR);
2262  if (!it.IsEnumerable()) continue;
2263  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2264  isolate, prop_value, Object::GetProperty(&it), Nothing<bool>());
2265  }
2266 
2267  if (get_entries) {
2268  prop_value = MakeEntryPair(isolate, next_key, prop_value);
2269  }
2270 
2271  values_or_entries->set(count, *prop_value);
2272  count++;
2273  }
2274 
2275  DCHECK_LE(count, values_or_entries->length());
2276  *result = FixedArray::RightTrimOrEmpty(isolate, values_or_entries, count);
2277  return Just(true);
2278 }
2279 
2280 MaybeDirectHandle<FixedArray> GetOwnValuesOrEntries(
2281  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> object, PropertyFilter filter,
2282  bool try_fast_path, bool get_entries) {
2283  Handle<FixedArray> values_or_entries;
2284  if (try_fast_path && filter == ENUMERABLE_STRINGS) {
2285  Maybe<bool> fast_values_or_entries = FastGetOwnValuesOrEntries(
2286  isolate, object, get_entries, &values_or_entries);
2287  if (fast_values_or_entries.IsNothing())
2288  return MaybeDirectHandle<FixedArray>();
2289  if (fast_values_or_entries.FromJust()) return values_or_entries;
2290  }
2291 
2292  PropertyFilter key_filter =
2293  static_cast<PropertyFilter>(filter & ~ONLY_ENUMERABLE);
2294 
2295  DirectHandle<FixedArray> keys;
2296  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2297  isolate, keys,
2298  KeyAccumulator::GetKeys(isolate, object, KeyCollectionMode::kOwnOnly,
2299  key_filter, GetKeysConversion::kConvertToString),
2300  MaybeDirectHandle<FixedArray>());
2301 
2302  values_or_entries = isolate->factory()->NewFixedArray(keys->length());
2303  int length = 0;
2304 
2305  for (int i = 0; i < keys->length(); ++i) {
2306  DirectHandle<Name> key(Cast<Name>(keys->get(i)), isolate);
2307 
2308  if (filter & ONLY_ENUMERABLE) {
2309  PropertyDescriptor descriptor;
2310  Maybe<bool> did_get_descriptor = JSReceiver::GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(
2311  isolate, object, key, &descriptor);
2312  MAYBE_RETURN(did_get_descriptor, MaybeDirectHandle<FixedArray>());
2313  if (!did_get_descriptor.FromJust() || !descriptor.enumerable()) continue;
2314  }
2315 
2316  DirectHandle<Object> value;
2317  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
2318  isolate, value, Object::GetPropertyOrElement(isolate, object, key),
2319  MaybeDirectHandle<FixedArray>());
2320 
2321  if (get_entries) {
2322  DirectHandle<FixedArray> entry_storage =
2323  isolate->factory()->NewFixedArray(2);
2324  entry_storage->set(0, *key);
2325  entry_storage->set(1, *value);
2326  value = isolate->factory()->NewJSArrayWithElements(entry_storage,
2327  PACKED_ELEMENTS, 2);
2328  }
2329 
2330  values_or_entries->set(length, *value);
2331  length++;
2332  }
2333  DCHECK_LE(length, values_or_entries->length());
2334  return FixedArray::RightTrimOrEmpty(isolate, values_or_entries, length);
2335 }
2336 
2337 MaybeDirectHandle<FixedArray> JSReceiver::GetOwnValues(
2338  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> object, PropertyFilter filter,
2339  bool try_fast_path) {
2340  return GetOwnValuesOrEntries(isolate, object, filter, try_fast_path, false);
2341 }
2342 
2343 MaybeDirectHandle<FixedArray> JSReceiver::GetOwnEntries(
2344  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> object, PropertyFilter filter,
2345  bool try_fast_path) {
2346  return GetOwnValuesOrEntries(isolate, object, filter, try_fast_path, true);
2347 }
2348 
2349 Maybe<bool> JSReceiver::SetPrototype(Isolate* isolate,
2350  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> object,
2351  DirectHandle<Object> value,
2352  bool from_javascript,
2353  ShouldThrow should_throw) {
2354  if (IsWasmObject(*object)) {
2355  RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, should_throw,
2356  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kWasmObjectsAreOpaque));
2357  }
2358 
2359  if (IsJSProxy(*object)) {
2360  return JSProxy::SetPrototype(isolate, Cast<JSProxy>(object), value,
2361  from_javascript, should_throw);
2362  }
2363  return JSObject::SetPrototype(isolate, Cast<JSObject>(object), value,
2364  from_javascript, should_throw);
2365 }
2366 
2367 bool JSReceiver::HasProxyInPrototype(Isolate* isolate) {
2368  for (PrototypeIterator iter(isolate, *this, kStartAtReceiver,
2369  PrototypeIterator::END_AT_NULL);
2370  !iter.IsAtEnd(); iter.AdvanceIgnoringProxies()) {
2371  if (IsJSProxy(iter.GetCurrent())) return true;
2372  }
2373  return false;
2374 }
2375 
2376 bool JSReceiver::IsCodeLike(Isolate* isolate) const {
2377  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2378  Tagged<Object> maybe_constructor = map()->GetConstructor();
2379  if (!IsJSFunction(maybe_constructor)) return false;
2380  if (!Cast<JSFunction>(maybe_constructor)->shared()->IsApiFunction()) {
2381  return false;
2382  }
2383  Tagged<Object> instance_template = Cast<JSFunction>(maybe_constructor)
2384  ->shared()
2385  ->api_func_data()
2386  ->GetInstanceTemplate();
2387  if (IsUndefined(instance_template, isolate)) return false;
2388  return Cast<ObjectTemplateInfo>(instance_template)->code_like();
2389 }

2391 // static
2392 MaybeHandle<JSObject> JSObject::New(DirectHandle<JSFunction> constructor,
2393  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> new_target,
2394  DirectHandle<AllocationSite> site,
2395  NewJSObjectType new_js_object_type) {
2396  // If called through new, new.target can be:
2397  // - a subclass of constructor,
2398  // - a proxy wrapper around constructor, or
2399  // - the constructor itself.
2400  // If called through Reflect.construct, it's guaranteed to be a constructor.
2401  Isolate* const isolate = Isolate::Current();
2402  DCHECK(IsConstructor(*constructor));
2403  DCHECK(IsConstructor(*new_target));
2404  DCHECK(!constructor->has_initial_map() ||
2405  !InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSFunction(
2406  constructor->initial_map()->instance_type()));
2407 
2408  DirectHandle<Map> initial_map;
2409  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
2410  isolate, initial_map,
2411  JSFunction::GetDerivedMap(isolate, constructor, new_target));
2412  constexpr int initial_capacity = PropertyDictionary::kInitialCapacity;
2413  Handle<JSObject> result = isolate->factory()->NewFastOrSlowJSObjectFromMap(
2414  initial_map, initial_capacity, AllocationType::kYoung, site,
2415  new_js_object_type);
2416  return result;
2417 }
2418 
2419 // static
2420 MaybeDirectHandle<JSObject> JSObject::NewWithMap(
2421  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Map> initial_map,
2422  DirectHandle<AllocationSite> site, NewJSObjectType new_js_object_type) {
2423  constexpr int initial_capacity = PropertyDictionary::kInitialCapacity;
2424  DirectHandle<JSObject> result =
2425  isolate->factory()->NewFastOrSlowJSObjectFromMap(
2426  initial_map, initial_capacity, AllocationType::kYoung, site,
2427  new_js_object_type);
2428  return result;
2429 }

2431 // 9.1.12 ObjectCreate ( proto [ , internalSlotsList ] )
2432 // Notice: This is NOT 19.1.2.2 Object.create ( O, Properties )
2433 MaybeDirectHandle<JSObject> JSObject::ObjectCreate(
2434  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSPrototype> prototype) {
2435  // Generate the map with the specified {prototype} based on the Object
2436  // function's initial map from the current native context.
2437  // TODO(bmeurer): Use a dedicated cache for Object.create; think about
2438  // slack tracking for Object.create.
2439  DirectHandle<Map> map = Map::GetObjectCreateMap(isolate, prototype);
2440 
2441  // Actually allocate the object.
2442  return isolate->factory()->NewFastOrSlowJSObjectFromMap(map);
2443 }

2445 bool JSArray::HasReadOnlyLengthSlowPath(DirectHandle<JSArray> array) {
2446  // Look at the object.
2447  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::Current();
2448  LookupIterator it(isolate, array, isolate->factory()->length_string(), array,
2449  LookupIterator::OWN_SKIP_INTERCEPTOR);
2450  CHECK_EQ(LookupIterator::ACCESSOR, it.state());
2451  return it.IsReadOnly();
2452 }

2454 void JSObject::MakeElementsWritable(Isolate* isolate,
2455  DirectHandle<JSObject> object) {
2456  Tagged<FixedArray> raw_elems = Cast<FixedArray>(object->elements());
2457  DirectHandle<FixedArray> elems(raw_elems, isolate);
2458  DirectHandle<FixedArray> writable_elems =
2459  isolate->factory()->CopyFixedArrayWithMap(
2460  elems, isolate->factory()->fixed_array_map());
2461  object->set_elements(*writable_elems);
2462 }

2464 // For FATAL in JSObject::GetHeaderSize
2465 static const char* NonAPIInstanceTypeToString(InstanceType instance_type) {
2466  DCHECK(!InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSApiObject(instance_type));
2467  switch (instance_type) {
2468 #define WRITE_TYPE(TYPE) \
2469  case TYPE: \
2470  return #TYPE;
2471  INSTANCE_TYPE_LIST(WRITE_TYPE)
2472 #undef WRITE_TYPE
2473  }
2474  UNREACHABLE();
2475 }

2683 
2684 MaybeHandle<JSAny> JSObject::GetPropertyWithFailedAccessCheck(
2685  LookupIterator* it) {
2686  Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
2687  DirectHandle<JSObject> checked = it->GetHolder<JSObject>();
2688  DirectHandle<InterceptorInfo> interceptor =
2689  it->GetInterceptorForFailedAccessCheck();
2690  if (!interceptor.is_null()) {
2691  Handle<JSAny> result;
2692  bool done;
2693  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
2694  isolate, result,
2695  GetPropertyWithInterceptorInternal(it, interceptor, &done));
2696  if (done) return result;
2697  }
2698 
2699  // Cross-Origin [[Get]] of Well-Known Symbols does not throw, and returns
2700  // undefined.
2701  DirectHandle<Name> name = it->GetName();
2702  if (IsSymbol(*name) && Cast<Symbol>(*name)->is_well_known_symbol()) {
2703  return it->factory()->undefined_value();
2704  }
2705 
2706  RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, isolate->ReportFailedAccessCheck(checked));
2707  UNREACHABLE();
2708 }
2709 
2710 Maybe<PropertyAttributes> JSObject::GetPropertyAttributesWithFailedAccessCheck(
2711  LookupIterator* it) {
2712  Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
2713  DirectHandle<JSObject> checked = it->GetHolder<JSObject>();
2714  DirectHandle<InterceptorInfo> interceptor =
2715  it->GetInterceptorForFailedAccessCheck();
2716  if (!interceptor.is_null()) {
2717  Maybe<PropertyAttributes> result =
2718  GetPropertyAttributesWithInterceptorInternal(it, interceptor);
2719  if (isolate->has_exception()) return Nothing<PropertyAttributes>();
2720  if (result.FromMaybe(ABSENT) != ABSENT) return result;
2721  }
2722  RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate, isolate->ReportFailedAccessCheck(checked),
2723  Nothing<PropertyAttributes>());
2724  UNREACHABLE();
2725 }
2726 
2727 Maybe<bool> JSObject::SetPropertyWithFailedAccessCheck(
2728  LookupIterator* it, DirectHandle<Object> value,
2729  Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
2730  Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
2731  DirectHandle<JSObject> checked = it->GetHolder<JSObject>();
2732  DirectHandle<InterceptorInfo> interceptor =
2733  it->GetInterceptorForFailedAccessCheck();
2734  if (!interceptor.is_null()) {
2735  InterceptorResult result;
2736  if (!SetPropertyWithInterceptorInternal(it, interceptor, should_throw,
2737  value)
2738  .To(&result)) {
2739  // An exception was thrown in the interceptor. Propagate.
2740  return Nothing<bool>();
2741  }
2742  switch (result) {
2743  case InterceptorResult::kFalse:
2744  return Just(false);
2745  case InterceptorResult::kTrue:
2746  return Just(true);
2747  case InterceptorResult::kNotIntercepted:
2748  // Fall through to report failed access check.
2749  break;
2750  }
2751  }
2752  RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate, isolate->ReportFailedAccessCheck(checked),
2753  Nothing<bool>());
2754  UNREACHABLE();
2755 }
2756 
2757 void JSObject::SetNormalizedProperty(DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
2758  DirectHandle<Name> name,
2759  DirectHandle<Object> value,
2760  PropertyDetails details) {
2761  DCHECK(!object->HasFastProperties());
2762  DCHECK(IsUniqueName(*name));
2763  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::Current();
2764 
2765  uint32_t hash = name->hash();
2766 
2767  if (IsJSGlobalObject(*object)) {
2768  auto global_obj = Cast<JSGlobalObject>(object);
2769  DirectHandle<GlobalDictionary> dictionary(
2770  global_obj->global_dictionary(kAcquireLoad), isolate);
2771  ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
2772  InternalIndex entry = dictionary->FindEntry(isolate, roots, name, hash);
2773 
2774  if (entry.is_not_found()) {
2775  DCHECK_IMPLIES(global_obj->map()->is_prototype_map(),
2776  Map::IsPrototypeChainInvalidated(global_obj->map()));
2777  auto cell_type = IsUndefined(*value, roots) ? PropertyCellType::kUndefined
2778  : PropertyCellType::kConstant;
2779  details = details.set_cell_type(cell_type);
2780  auto cell = isolate->factory()->NewPropertyCell(name, details, value);
2781  dictionary =
2782  GlobalDictionary::Add(isolate, dictionary, name, cell, details);
2783  global_obj->set_global_dictionary(*dictionary, kReleaseStore);
2784  } else {
2785  PropertyCell::PrepareForAndSetValue(isolate, dictionary, entry, value,
2786  details);
2787  DCHECK_EQ(dictionary->CellAt(entry)->value(), *value);
2788  }
2789  } else {
2790  if constexpr (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
2791  DirectHandle<SwissNameDictionary> dictionary(
2792  object->property_dictionary_swiss(), isolate);
2793  InternalIndex entry = dictionary->FindEntry(isolate, *name);
2794  if (entry.is_not_found()) {
2795  DCHECK_IMPLIES(object->map()->is_prototype_map(),
2796  Map::IsPrototypeChainInvalidated(object->map()));
2797  dictionary =
2798  SwissNameDictionary::Add(isolate, dictionary, name, value, details);
2799  object->SetProperties(*dictionary);
2800  } else {
2801  dictionary->ValueAtPut(entry, *value);
2802  dictionary->DetailsAtPut(entry, details);
2803  }
2804  } else {
2805  DirectHandle<NameDictionary> dictionary(object->property_dictionary(),
2806  isolate);
2807  InternalIndex entry = dictionary->FindEntry(isolate, name);
2808  if (entry.is_not_found()) {
2809  DCHECK_IMPLIES(object->map()->is_prototype_map(),
2810  Map::IsPrototypeChainInvalidated(object->map()));
2811  dictionary =
2812  NameDictionary::Add(isolate, dictionary, name, value, details);
2813  object->SetProperties(*dictionary);
2814  } else {
2815  PropertyDetails original_details = dictionary->DetailsAt(entry);
2816  int enumeration_index = original_details.dictionary_index();
2817  DCHECK_GT(enumeration_index, 0);
2818  details = details.set_index(enumeration_index);
2819  dictionary->SetEntry(entry, *name, *value, details);
2820  }
2821  // TODO(pthier): Add flags to swiss dictionaries.
2822  if (name->IsInteresting(isolate)) {
2823  dictionary->set_may_have_interesting_properties(true);
2824  }
2825  }
2826  }
2827 }
2828 
2829 void JSObject::SetNormalizedElement(DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
2830  uint32_t index, DirectHandle<Object> value,
2831  PropertyDetails details) {
2832  DCHECK_EQ(object->GetElementsKind(), DICTIONARY_ELEMENTS);
2833 
2834  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::Current();
2835 
2836  DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> dictionary(
2837  Cast<NumberDictionary>(object->elements()), isolate);
2838  dictionary =
2839  NumberDictionary::Set(isolate, dictionary, index, value, object, details);
2840  object->set_elements(*dictionary);
2841 }
2842 
2843 void JSObject::JSObjectShortPrint(StringStream* accumulator) {
2844  switch (map()->instance_type()) {
2845  case JS_ARRAY_TYPE: {
2846  double length = IsUndefined(Cast<JSArray>(*this)->length())
2847  ? 0
2848  : Object::NumberValue(Cast<JSArray>(*this)->length());
2849  accumulator->Add("<JSArray[%u]>", static_cast<uint32_t>(length));
2850  break;
2851  }
2852  case JS_BOUND_FUNCTION_TYPE: {
2853  Tagged<JSBoundFunction> bound_function = Cast<JSBoundFunction>(*this);
2854  accumulator->Add("<JSBoundFunction");
2855  accumulator->Add(" (BoundTargetFunction %p)>",
2856  reinterpret_cast<void*>(
2857  bound_function->bound_target_function().ptr()));
2858  break;
2859  }
2860  case JS_WEAK_MAP_TYPE: {
2861  accumulator->Add("<JSWeakMap>");
2862  break;
2863  }
2864  case JS_WEAK_SET_TYPE: {
2865  accumulator->Add("<JSWeakSet>");
2866  break;
2867  }
2868  case JS_REG_EXP_TYPE: {
2869  accumulator->Add("<JSRegExp");
2870  Tagged<JSRegExp> regexp = Cast<JSRegExp>(*this);
2871  if (IsString(regexp->source())) {
2872  accumulator->Add(" ");
2873  Cast<String>(regexp->source())->StringShortPrint(accumulator);
2874  }
2875  accumulator->Add(">");
2876 
2877  break;
2878  }
2879  case JS_PROMISE_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
2880  case JS_REG_EXP_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
2881  case JS_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
2882 #define TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTORS_SWITCH(Type, type, TYPE, Ctype) \
2883  case TYPE##_TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
2884  TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTORS_SWITCH)
2885 #undef TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTORS_SWITCH
2886  case JS_CLASS_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
2887  case JS_FUNCTION_TYPE: {
2888  Tagged<JSFunction> function = Cast<JSFunction>(*this);
2889  std::unique_ptr<char[]> fun_name = function->shared()->DebugNameCStr();
2890  if (fun_name[0] != '\0') {
2891  accumulator->Add("<JSFunction ");
2892  accumulator->Add(fun_name.get());
2893  } else {
2894  accumulator->Add("<JSFunction");
2895  }
2896  if (v8_flags.trace_file_names) {
2897  Tagged<Object> source_name =
2898  Cast<Script>(function->shared()->script())->name();
2899  if (IsString(source_name)) {
2900  Tagged<String> str = Cast<String>(source_name);
2901  if (str->length() > 0) {
2902  accumulator->Add(" <");
2903  accumulator->Put(str);
2904  accumulator->Add(">");
2905  }
2906  }
2907  }
2908  accumulator->Add(" (sfi = %p)",
2909  reinterpret_cast<void*>(function->shared().ptr()));
2910  accumulator->Put('>');
2911  break;
2912  }
2913  case JS_GENERATOR_OBJECT_TYPE: {
2914  accumulator->Add("<JSGenerator>");
2915  break;
2916  }
2917  case JS_ASYNC_FUNCTION_OBJECT_TYPE: {
2918  accumulator->Add("<JSAsyncFunctionObject>");
2919  break;
2920  }
2921  case JS_ASYNC_GENERATOR_OBJECT_TYPE: {
2922  accumulator->Add("<JS AsyncGenerator>");
2923  break;
2924  }
2925  case JS_SHARED_ARRAY_TYPE:
2926  accumulator->Add("<JSSharedArray>");
2927  break;
2928  case JS_SHARED_STRUCT_TYPE:
2929  accumulator->Add("<JSSharedStruct>");
2930  break;
2931  case JS_ATOMICS_MUTEX_TYPE:
2932  accumulator->Add("<JSAtomicsMutex>");
2933  break;
2934  case JS_ATOMICS_CONDITION_TYPE:
2935  accumulator->Add("<JSAtomicsCondition>");
2936  break;
2937  case JS_MESSAGE_OBJECT_TYPE:
2938  accumulator->Add("<JSMessageObject>");
2939  break;
2940  case JS_EXTERNAL_OBJECT_TYPE:
2941  accumulator->Add("<JSExternalObject>");
2942  break;
2943  case CPP_HEAP_EXTERNAL_OBJECT_TYPE:
2944  accumulator->Add("<CppHeapExternalObject>");
2945  break;
2946 
2947  default: {
2948  Tagged<Map> map_of_this = map();
2949  Tagged<Object> constructor = map_of_this->GetConstructor();
2950  bool printed = false;
2951  bool is_global_proxy = IsJSGlobalProxy(*this);
2952  if (IsJSFunction(constructor)) {
2953  Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> sfi =
2954  Cast<JSFunction>(constructor)->shared();
2955  Tagged<String> constructor_name = sfi->Name();
2956  if (constructor_name->length() > 0) {
2957  accumulator->Add(is_global_proxy ? "<GlobalObject " : "<");
2958  accumulator->Put(constructor_name);
2959  accumulator->Add(" %smap = %p",
2960  map_of_this->is_deprecated() ? "deprecated-" : "",
2961  map_of_this);
2962  printed = true;
2963  }
2964  } else if (IsFunctionTemplateInfo(constructor)) {
2965  accumulator->Add("<RemoteObject>");
2966  printed = true;
2967  }
2968  if (!printed) {
2969  accumulator->Add("<JS");
2970  if (is_global_proxy) {
2971  accumulator->Add("GlobalProxy");
2972  } else if (IsJSGlobalObject(*this)) {
2973  accumulator->Add("GlobalObject");
2974  } else {
2975  accumulator->Add("Object");
2976  }
2977  }
2978  if (IsJSPrimitiveWrapper(*this)) {
2979  accumulator->Add(" value = ");
2980  ShortPrint(Cast<JSPrimitiveWrapper>(*this)->value(), accumulator);
2981  }
2982  accumulator->Put('>');
2983  break;
2984  }
2985  }
2986 }

2988 void JSObject::PrintElementsTransition(
2989  FILE* file, DirectHandle<JSObject> object, ElementsKind from_kind,
2990  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> from_elements, ElementsKind to_kind,

2995  << ElementsKindToString(to_kind) << "] in ";

2997  PrintF(file, " for ");
2998  ShortPrint(*object, file);
2999  PrintF(file, " from ");
3000  ShortPrint(*from_elements, file);

3007 void JSObject::PrintInstanceMigration(FILE* file, Tagged<Map> original_map,
3008  Tagged<Map> new_map) {
3009  if (new_map->is_dictionary_map()) {
3010  PrintF(file, "[migrating to slow]\n");
3011  return;
3012  }
3013  PrintF(file, "[migrating]");
3014  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::Current();
3015  Tagged<DescriptorArray> o = original_map->instance_descriptors(isolate);
3016  Tagged<DescriptorArray> n = new_map->instance_descriptors(isolate);
3017  for (InternalIndex i : original_map->IterateOwnDescriptors()) {
3018  Representation o_r = o->GetDetails(i).representation();
3019  Representation n_r = n->GetDetails(i).representation();
3020  if (!o_r.Equals(n_r)) {
3021  Cast<String>(o->GetKey(i))->PrintOn(file);
3022  PrintF(file, ":%s->%s ", o_r.Mnemonic(), n_r.Mnemonic());
3023  } else if (o->GetDetails(i).location() == PropertyLocation::kDescriptor &&
3024  n->GetDetails(i).location() == PropertyLocation::kField) {
3025  Tagged<Name> name = o->GetKey(i);
3026  if (IsString(name)) {
3027  Cast<String>(name)->PrintOn(file);
3028  } else {
3029  PrintF(file, "{symbol %p}", reinterpret_cast<void*>(name.ptr()));
3030  }
3031  PrintF(file, " ");
3032  }
3033  }
3034  if (original_map->elements_kind() != new_map->elements_kind()) {
3035  PrintF(file, "elements_kind[%i->%i]", original_map->elements_kind(),
3036  new_map->elements_kind());
3037  }
3038  PrintF(file, "\n");
3039 }

3041 // static
3042 bool JSObject::IsUnmodifiedApiObject(FullObjectSlot o) {
3043  Tagged<Object> object = *o;
3044  if (IsSmi(object)) return false;
3045  Tagged<HeapObject> heap_object = Cast<HeapObject>(object);
3046  Tagged<Map> map = heap_object->map();
3047  if (!InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSObject(map)) return false;
3048  if (!JSObject::IsDroppableApiObject(map)) return false;
3049  Tagged<Object> maybe_constructor = map->GetConstructor();
3050  if (!IsJSFunction(maybe_constructor)) return false;
3051  Tagged<JSObject> js_object = Cast<JSObject>(object);
3052  if (js_object->elements()->length() != 0) return false;
3053  // Check that the object is not a key in a WeakMap (over-approximation).
3054  if (!IsUndefined(js_object->GetIdentityHash())) return false;
3055 
3056  Tagged<JSFunction> constructor = Cast<JSFunction>(maybe_constructor);
3057  return constructor->initial_map() == map;
3058 }

3060 // static
3061 void JSObject::UpdatePrototypeUserRegistration(DirectHandle<Map> old_map,
3062  DirectHandle<Map> new_map,
3063  Isolate* isolate) {
3064  DCHECK(old_map->is_prototype_map());
3065  DCHECK(new_map->is_prototype_map());
3066  bool was_registered = JSObject::UnregisterPrototypeUser(old_map, isolate);
3067  new_map->set_prototype_info(old_map->prototype_info(), kReleaseStore);
3068  old_map->set_prototype_info(Smi::zero(), kReleaseStore);
3069  if (v8_flags.trace_prototype_users) {
3070  PrintF("Moving prototype_info %p from map %p to map %p.\n",
3071  reinterpret_cast<void*>(new_map->prototype_info().ptr()),
3072  reinterpret_cast<void*>(old_map->ptr()),
3073  reinterpret_cast<void*>(new_map->ptr()));
3074  }
3075  if (was_registered) {
3076  if (new_map->has_prototype_info()) {
3077  // The new map isn't registered with its prototype yet; reflect this fact
3078  // in the PrototypeInfo it just inherited from the old map.
3079  Cast<PrototypeInfo>(new_map->prototype_info())
3080  ->set_registry_slot(PrototypeInfo::UNREGISTERED);
3081  }
3082  JSObject::LazyRegisterPrototypeUser(new_map, isolate);
3083  }
3084 }
3085 
3086 // static
3087 void JSObject::NotifyMapChange(DirectHandle<Map> old_map,
3088  DirectHandle<Map> new_map, Isolate* isolate) {
3089  if (!old_map->is_prototype_map()) return;
3090 
3091  InvalidatePrototypeChains(*old_map);
3092 
3093  // If the map was registered with its prototype before, ensure that it
3094  // registers with its new prototype now. This preserves the invariant that
3095  // when a map on a prototype chain is registered with its prototype, then
3096  // all prototypes further up the chain are also registered with their
3097  // respective prototypes.
3098  UpdatePrototypeUserRegistration(old_map, new_map, isolate);
3099 }
3100 
3101 namespace {
3102 
3103 // To migrate a fast instance to a fast map:
3104 // - First check whether the instance needs to be rewritten. If not, simply
3105 // change the map.
3106 // - Otherwise, allocate a fixed array large enough to hold all fields, in
3107 // addition to unused space.
3108 // - Copy all existing properties in, in the following order: backing store
3109 // properties, unused fields, inobject properties.
3110 // - If all allocation succeeded, commit the state atomically:
3111 // * Copy inobject properties from the backing store back into the object.
3112 // * Trim the difference in instance size of the object. This also cleanly
3113 // frees inobject properties that moved to the backing store.
3114 // * If there are properties left in the backing store, trim of the space used
3115 // to temporarily store the inobject properties.
3116 // * If there are properties left in the backing store, install the backing
3117 // store.
3118 void MigrateFastToFast(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
3119  DirectHandle<Map> new_map) {
3120  DirectHandle<Map> old_map(object->map(), isolate);
3121  // In case of a regular transition.
3122  if (new_map->GetBackPointer(isolate) == *old_map) {
3123  // If the map does not add named properties, simply set the map.
3124  if (old_map->NumberOfOwnDescriptors() ==
3125  new_map->NumberOfOwnDescriptors()) {
3126  object->set_map(isolate, *new_map, kReleaseStore);
3127  return;
3128  }
3129 
3130  // If the map adds a new kDescriptor property, simply set the map.
3131  PropertyDetails details = new_map->GetLastDescriptorDetails(isolate);
3132  if (details.location() == PropertyLocation::kDescriptor) {
3133  object->set_map(isolate, *new_map, kReleaseStore);
3134  return;
3135  }
3136 
3137  // Check if we still have space in the {object}, in which case we
3138  // can also simply set the map (modulo a special case for mutable
3139  // double boxes).
3140  FieldIndex index = FieldIndex::ForDetails(*new_map, details);
3141  if (index.is_inobject() || index.outobject_array_index() <
3142  object->property_array(isolate)->length()) {
3143  // Allocate HeapNumbers for double fields.
3144  if (index.is_double()) {
3145  auto value = isolate->factory()->NewHeapNumberWithHoleNaN();
3146  object->FastPropertyAtPut(index, *value);
3147  }
3148  object->set_map(isolate, *new_map, kReleaseStore);
3149  return;
3150  }
3151 
3152  // This migration is a transition from a map that has run out of property
3153  // space. Extend the backing store.
3154  int grow_by = new_map->UnusedPropertyFields() + 1;
3155  DirectHandle<PropertyArray> old_storage(object->property_array(isolate),
3156  isolate);
3157  DirectHandle<PropertyArray> new_storage =
3158  isolate->factory()->CopyPropertyArrayAndGrow(old_storage, grow_by);
3159 
3160  // Properly initialize newly added property.
3161  DirectHandle<Object> value;
3162  if (details.representation().IsDouble()) {
3163  value = isolate->factory()->NewHeapNumberWithHoleNaN();
3164  } else {
3165  value = isolate->factory()->uninitialized_value();
3166  }
3167  DCHECK_EQ(PropertyLocation::kField, details.location());
3168  DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kData, details.kind());
3169  DCHECK(!index.is_inobject()); // Must be a backing store index.
3170  new_storage->set(index.outobject_array_index(), *value);
3171 
3172  // From here on we cannot fail and we shouldn't GC anymore.
3173  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3174 
3175  // Set the new property value and do the map transition.
3176  object->SetProperties(*new_storage);
3177  object->set_map(isolate, *new_map, kReleaseStore);
3178  return;
3179  }
3180 
3181  int old_number_of_fields;
3182  int number_of_fields = new_map->NumberOfFields(ConcurrencyMode::kSynchronous);
3183  int inobject = new_map->GetInObjectProperties();
3184  int unused = new_map->UnusedPropertyFields();
3185 
3186  // Nothing to do if no functions were converted to fields and no smis were
3187  // converted to doubles.
3188  if (!old_map->InstancesNeedRewriting(*new_map, number_of_fields, inobject,
3189  unused, &old_number_of_fields,
3190  ConcurrencyMode::kSynchronous)) {
3191  object->set_map(isolate, *new_map, kReleaseStore);
3192  return;
3193  }
3194 
3195  int total_size = number_of_fields + unused;
3196  int external = total_size - inobject;
3197  DirectHandle<PropertyArray> array =
3198  isolate->factory()->NewPropertyArray(external);
3199 
3200  // We use this array to temporarily store the inobject properties.
3201  DirectHandle<FixedArray> inobject_props =
3202  isolate->factory()->NewFixedArray(inobject);
3203 
3204  DirectHandle<DescriptorArray> old_descriptors(
3205  old_map->instance_descriptors(isolate), isolate);
3206  DirectHandle<DescriptorArray> new_descriptors(
3207  new_map->instance_descriptors(isolate), isolate);
3208  int old_nof = old_map->NumberOfOwnDescriptors();
3209  int new_nof = new_map->NumberOfOwnDescriptors();
3210 
3211  // This method only supports generalizing instances to at least the same
3212  // number of properties.
3213  DCHECK(old_nof <= new_nof);
3214 
3215  for (InternalIndex i : InternalIndex::Range(old_nof)) {
3216  PropertyDetails details = new_descriptors->GetDetails(i);
3217  if (details.location() != PropertyLocation::kField) continue;
3218  DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kData, details.kind());
3219  PropertyDetails old_details = old_descriptors->GetDetails(i);
3220  Representation old_representation = old_details.representation();
3221  Representation representation = details.representation();
3222  Handle<UnionOf<JSAny, Hole>> value;
3223  if (old_details.location() == PropertyLocation::kDescriptor) {
3224  if (old_details.kind() == PropertyKind::kAccessor) {
3225  // In case of kAccessor -> kData property reconfiguration, the property
3226  // must already be prepared for data of certain type.
3227  DCHECK(!details.representation().IsNone());
3228  if (details.representation().IsDouble()) {
3229  value = isolate->factory()->NewHeapNumberWithHoleNaN();
3230  } else {
3231  value = isolate->factory()->uninitialized_value();
3232  }
3233  } else {
3234  DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kData, old_details.kind());
3235  value = handle(Cast<JSAny>(old_descriptors->GetStrongValue(isolate, i)),
3236  isolate);
3237  DCHECK(!old_representation.IsDouble() && !representation.IsDouble());
3238  }
3239  } else {
3240  DCHECK_EQ(PropertyLocation::kField, old_details.location());
3241  FieldIndex index = FieldIndex::ForDetails(*old_map, old_details);
3242  value = handle(object->RawFastPropertyAt(isolate, index), isolate);
3243  if (!old_representation.IsDouble() && representation.IsDouble()) {
3244  DCHECK_IMPLIES(old_representation.IsNone(),
3245  IsUninitialized(*value, isolate));
3246  value = Object::NewStorageFor(isolate, value, representation);
3247  } else if (old_representation.IsDouble() && !representation.IsDouble()) {
3248  value = Object::WrapForRead(isolate, Cast<JSAny>(value),
3249  old_representation);
3250  }
3251  }
3252  DCHECK(!(representation.IsDouble() && IsSmi(*value)));
3253  int target_index = new_descriptors->GetFieldIndex(i);
3254  if (target_index < inobject) {
3255  inobject_props->set(target_index, *value);
3256  } else {
3257  array->set(target_index - inobject, *value);
3258  }
3259  }
3260 
3261  for (InternalIndex i : InternalIndex::Range(old_nof, new_nof)) {
3262  PropertyDetails details = new_descriptors->GetDetails(i);
3263  if (details.location() != PropertyLocation::kField) continue;
3264  DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kData, details.kind());
3265  DirectHandle<Object> value;
3266  if (details.representation().IsDouble()) {
3267  value = isolate->factory()->NewHeapNumberWithHoleNaN();
3268  } else {
3269  value = isolate->factory()->uninitialized_value();
3270  }
3271  int target_index = new_descriptors->GetFieldIndex(i);
3272  if (target_index < inobject) {
3273  inobject_props->set(target_index, *value);
3274  } else {
3275  array->set(target_index - inobject, *value);
3276  }
3277  }
3278 
3279  // From here on we cannot fail and we shouldn't GC anymore.
3280  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3281 
3282  Heap* heap = isolate->heap();
3283 
3284  // Copy (real) inobject properties. If necessary, stop at number_of_fields to
3285  // avoid overwriting |one_pointer_filler_map|.
3286  int limit = std::min(inobject, number_of_fields);
3287  for (int i = 0; i < limit; i++) {
3288  FieldIndex index = FieldIndex::ForPropertyIndex(*new_map, i);
3289  Tagged<Object> value = inobject_props->get(i);
3290  object->FastPropertyAtPut(index, value);
3291  }
3292 
3293  object->SetProperties(*array);
3294 
3295  // Create filler object past the new instance size.
3296  int old_instance_size = old_map->instance_size();
3297  int new_instance_size = new_map->instance_size();
3298  int instance_size_delta = old_instance_size - new_instance_size;
3299  DCHECK_GE(instance_size_delta, 0);
3300 
3301  if (instance_size_delta > 0) {
3302  heap->NotifyObjectSizeChange(*object, old_instance_size, new_instance_size,
3303  ClearRecordedSlots::kYes);
3304  }
3305 
3306  // We are storing the new map using release store after creating a filler for
3307  // the left-over space to avoid races with the sweeper thread.
3308  object->set_map(isolate, *new_map, kReleaseStore);
3309 }
3310 
3311 void MigrateFastToSlow(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
3312  DirectHandle<Map> new_map,
3313  int expected_additional_properties) {
3314  // The global object is always normalized.
3315  DCHECK(!IsJSGlobalObject(*object, isolate));
3316  // JSGlobalProxy must never be normalized
3317  DCHECK(!IsJSGlobalProxy(*object, isolate));
3318 
3319  DCHECK_IMPLIES(new_map->is_prototype_map(),
3320  Map::IsPrototypeChainInvalidated(*new_map));
3321 
3322  HandleScope scope(isolate);
3323  DirectHandle<Map> map(object->map(isolate), isolate);
3324 
3325  // Allocate new content.
3326  int real_size = map->NumberOfOwnDescriptors();
3327  int property_count = real_size;
3328  if (expected_additional_properties > 0) {
3329  property_count += expected_additional_properties;
3330  } else {
3331  // Make space for two more properties.
3332  constexpr int initial_capacity = PropertyDictionary::kInitialCapacity;
3333  property_count += initial_capacity;
3334  }
3335 
3336  DirectHandle<NameDictionary> dictionary;
3337  DirectHandle<SwissNameDictionary> ord_dictionary;
3338  if constexpr (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
3339  ord_dictionary = isolate->factory()->NewSwissNameDictionary(property_count);
3340  } else {
3341  dictionary = isolate->factory()->NewNameDictionary(property_count);
3342  }
3343 
3344  DirectHandle<DescriptorArray> descs(map->instance_descriptors(isolate),
3345  isolate);
3346  for (InternalIndex i : InternalIndex::Range(real_size)) {
3347  PropertyDetails details = descs->GetDetails(i);
3348  DirectHandle<Name> key(descs->GetKey(isolate, i), isolate);
3349  DirectHandle<Object> value;
3350  if (details.location() == PropertyLocation::kField) {
3351  FieldIndex index = FieldIndex::ForDetails(*map, details);
3352  if (details.kind() == PropertyKind::kData) {
3353  value =
3354  direct_handle(object->RawFastPropertyAt(isolate, index), isolate);
3355  if (details.representation().IsDouble()) {
3356  DCHECK(IsHeapNumber(*value, isolate));
3357  double old_value = Cast<HeapNumber>(value)->value();
3358  value = isolate->factory()->NewHeapNumber(old_value);
3359  }
3360  } else {
3361  DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kAccessor, details.kind());
3362  value =
3363  direct_handle(object->RawFastPropertyAt(isolate, index), isolate);
3364  }
3365 
3366  } else {
3367  DCHECK_EQ(PropertyLocation::kDescriptor, details.location());
3368  value = direct_handle(descs->GetStrongValue(isolate, i), isolate);
3369  }
3370  DCHECK(!value.is_null());
3371  PropertyConstness constness = V8_DICT_PROPERTY_CONST_TRACKING_BOOL
3372  ? details.constness()
3373  : PropertyConstness::kMutable;
3374  PropertyDetails d(details.kind(), details.attributes(), constness);
3375 
3376  if constexpr (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
3377  ord_dictionary =
3378  SwissNameDictionary::Add(isolate, ord_dictionary, key, value, d);
3379  } else {
3380  dictionary = NameDictionary::Add(isolate, dictionary, key, value, d);
3381  }
3382  }
3383 
3384  if constexpr (!V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
3385  // Copy the next enumeration index from instance descriptor.
3386  dictionary->set_next_enumeration_index(real_size + 1);
3387  // TODO(pthier): Add flags to swiss dictionaries.
3388  dictionary->set_may_have_interesting_properties(
3389  map->may_have_interesting_properties());
3390  }
3391 
3392  // From here on we cannot fail and we shouldn't GC anymore.
3393  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3394 
3395  Heap* heap = isolate->heap();
3396 
3397  // Resize the object in the heap if necessary.
3398  int old_instance_size = map->instance_size();
3399  int new_instance_size = new_map->instance_size();
3400  int instance_size_delta = old_instance_size - new_instance_size;
3401  DCHECK_GE(instance_size_delta, 0);
3402 
3403  if (instance_size_delta > 0) {
3404  heap->NotifyObjectSizeChange(*object, old_instance_size, new_instance_size,
3405  ClearRecordedSlots::kYes);
3406  }
3407 
3408  // We are storing the new map using release store after creating a filler for
3409  // the left-over space to avoid races with the sweeper thread.
3410  object->set_map(isolate, *new_map, kReleaseStore);
3411 
3412  if constexpr (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
3413  object->SetProperties(*ord_dictionary);
3414  } else {
3415  object->SetProperties(*dictionary);
3416  }
3417 
3418  // Ensure that in-object space of slow-mode object does not contain random
3419  // garbage.
3420  int inobject_properties = new_map->GetInObjectProperties();
3421  if (inobject_properties) {
3422  for (int i = 0; i < inobject_properties; i++) {
3423  FieldIndex index = FieldIndex::ForPropertyIndex(*new_map, i);
3424  object->FastPropertyAtPut(index, Smi::zero());
3425  }
3426  }
3427 
3428 #ifdef DEBUG
3429  if (v8_flags.trace_normalization) {
3430  StdoutStream os;
3431  os << "Object properties have been normalized:\n";
3432  Print(*object, os);
3433  }
3434 #endif
3435 }
3436 
3437 } // namespace
3438 
3439 void JSObject::MigrateToMap(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
3440  DirectHandle<Map> new_map,
3441  int expected_additional_properties) {
3442  if (object->map(isolate) == *new_map) return;
3443  DirectHandle<Map> old_map(object->map(isolate), isolate);
3444  NotifyMapChange(old_map, new_map, isolate);
3445 
3446  if (old_map->is_dictionary_map()) {
3447  // For slow-to-fast migrations JSObject::MigrateSlowToFast()
3448  // must be used instead.
3449  CHECK(new_map->is_dictionary_map());
3450 
3451  // Slow-to-slow migration is trivial.
3452  object->set_map(isolate, *new_map, kReleaseStore);
3453  } else if (!new_map->is_dictionary_map()) {
3454  MigrateFastToFast(isolate, object, new_map);
3455  if (old_map->is_prototype_map()) {
3456  DCHECK(!old_map->is_stable());
3457  DCHECK(new_map->is_stable());
3458  DCHECK(new_map->owns_descriptors());
3459  DCHECK(old_map->owns_descriptors());
3460  // Transfer ownership to the new map. Keep the descriptor pointer of the
3461  // old map intact because the concurrent marker might be iterating the
3462  // object with the old map.
3463  old_map->set_owns_descriptors(false);
3464  DCHECK(old_map->is_abandoned_prototype_map());
3465  // Ensure that no transition was inserted for prototype migrations.
3466  DCHECK_EQ(0,
3467  TransitionsAccessor(isolate, *old_map).NumberOfTransitions());
3468  DCHECK(IsUndefined(new_map->GetBackPointer(isolate), isolate));
3469  DCHECK(object->map(isolate) != *old_map);
3470  }
3471  } else {
3472  MigrateFastToSlow(isolate, object, new_map, expected_additional_properties);
3473  }
3474 
3475  // Careful: Don't allocate here!
3476  // For some callers of this method, |object| might be in an inconsistent
3477  // state now: the new map might have a new elements_kind, but the object's
3478  // elements pointer hasn't been updated yet. Callers will fix this, but in
3479  // the meantime, (indirectly) calling JSObjectVerify() must be avoided.
3480  // When adding code here, add a DisallowGarbageCollection too.
3481 }
3482 
3483 void JSObject::ForceSetPrototype(Isolate* isolate,
3484  DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
3485  DirectHandle<JSPrototype> proto) {
3486  // object.__proto__ = proto;
3487  DirectHandle<Map> old_map(object->map(), isolate);
3488  DirectHandle<Map> new_map = Map::Copy(isolate, old_map, "ForceSetPrototype");
3489  Map::SetPrototype(isolate, new_map, proto);
3490  JSObject::MigrateToMap(isolate, object, new_map);
3491 }

3498  should_throw, value);

3501 DirectHandle<Map> JSObject::GetElementsTransitionMap(
3502  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object, ElementsKind to_kind) {

3506 
3507 void JSObject::AllocateStorageForMap(Isolate* isolate,
3508  DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
3509  DirectHandle<Map> map) {
3510  DCHECK(object->map()->GetInObjectProperties() ==
3511  map->GetInObjectProperties());
3512  ElementsKind obj_kind = object->map()->elements_kind();
3513  ElementsKind map_kind = map->elements_kind();
3514  if (map_kind != obj_kind) {
3515  ElementsKind to_kind = GetMoreGeneralElementsKind(map_kind, obj_kind);
3516  if (IsDictionaryElementsKind(obj_kind)) {
3517  to_kind = obj_kind;
3518  }
3519  if (IsDictionaryElementsKind(to_kind)) {
3520  NormalizeElements(isolate, object);
3521  } else {
3522  TransitionElementsKind(isolate, object, to_kind);
3523  }
3524  map = MapUpdater{isolate, map}.ReconfigureElementsKind(to_kind);
3525  }
3526  int number_of_fields = map->NumberOfFields(ConcurrencyMode::kSynchronous);
3527  int inobject = map->GetInObjectProperties();
3528  int unused = map->UnusedPropertyFields();
3529  int total_size = number_of_fields + unused;
3530  int external = total_size - inobject;
3531  // Allocate mutable double boxes if necessary. It is always necessary if we
3532  // have external properties, but is also necessary if we only have inobject
3533  // properties but don't unbox double fields.
3534 
3535  DirectHandle<DescriptorArray> descriptors(map->instance_descriptors(isolate),
3536  isolate);
3537  DirectHandle<FixedArray> storage =
3538  isolate->factory()->NewFixedArray(inobject);
3539 
3540  DirectHandle<PropertyArray> array =
3541  isolate->factory()->NewPropertyArray(external);
3542 
3543  for (InternalIndex i : map->IterateOwnDescriptors()) {
3544  PropertyDetails details = descriptors->GetDetails(i);
3545  Representation representation = details.representation();
3546  if (!representation.IsDouble()) continue;
3547  FieldIndex index = FieldIndex::ForDetails(*map, details);
3548  auto box = isolate->factory()->NewHeapNumberWithHoleNaN();
3549  if (index.is_inobject()) {
3550  storage->set(index.property_index(), *box);
3551  } else {
3552  array->set(index.outobject_array_index(), *box);
3553  }
3554  }
3555 
3556  object->SetProperties(*array);
3557  for (int i = 0; i < inobject; i++) {
3558  FieldIndex index = FieldIndex::ForPropertyIndex(*map, i);
3559  Tagged<Object> value = storage->get(i);
3560  object->FastPropertyAtPut(index, value);
3561  }
3562  object->set_map(isolate, *map, kReleaseStore);
3563 }
3564 
3565 void JSObject::MigrateInstance(Isolate* isolate,
3566  DirectHandle<JSObject> object) {
3567  Handle<Map> original_map(object->map(), isolate);
3568  DirectHandle<Map> map = Map::Update(isolate, original_map);
3569  map->set_is_migration_target(true);
3570  JSObject::MigrateToMap(isolate, object, map);
3571  if (v8_flags.trace_migration) {
3572  object->PrintInstanceMigration(stdout, *original_map, *map);
3573  }
3574 #if VERIFY_HEAP
3575  if (v8_flags.verify_heap) {
3576  object->JSObjectVerify(isolate);
3577  }
3578 #endif
3579 }
3580 
3581 // static
3582 bool JSObject::TryMigrateInstance(Isolate* isolate,
3583  DirectHandle<JSObject> object) {
3584  DisallowDeoptimization no_deoptimization(isolate);
3585  Handle<Map> original_map(object->map(), isolate);
3586  DirectHandle<Map> new_map;
3587  if (!Map::TryUpdate(isolate, original_map).ToHandle(&new_map)) {
3588  return false;
3589  }
3590  JSObject::MigrateToMap(isolate, object, new_map);
3591  if (v8_flags.trace_migration && *original_map != object->map()) {
3592  object->PrintInstanceMigration(stdout, *original_map, object->map());
3593  }
3594 #if VERIFY_HEAP
3595  if (v8_flags.verify_heap) {
3596  object->JSObjectVerify(isolate);
3597  }
3598 #endif
3599  return true;
3600 }

3604 bool TryFastAddDataProperty(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
3605  DirectHandle<Name> name, DirectHandle<Object> value,
3606  PropertyAttributes attributes) {
3607  DCHECK(IsUniqueName(*name));
3608  Tagged<Map> map =
3609  TransitionsAccessor(isolate, object->map())
3610  .SearchTransition(*name, PropertyKind::kData, attributes);
3611  if (map.is_null()) return false;
3612  DCHECK(!map->is_dictionary_map());
3613 
3614  DirectHandle<Map> new_map(map, isolate);
3615  if (map->is_deprecated()) {
3616  new_map = Map::Update(isolate, new_map);
3617  if (new_map->is_dictionary_map()) return false;
3618  }
3619 
3620  InternalIndex descriptor = new_map->LastAdded();
3621  new_map = Map::PrepareForDataProperty(isolate, new_map, descriptor,
3622  PropertyConstness::kConst, value);
3623  JSObject::MigrateToMap(isolate, object, new_map);
3624  // TODO(leszeks): Avoid re-loading the property details, which we already
3625  // loaded in PrepareForDataProperty.
3626  object->WriteToField(descriptor,
3627  new_map->instance_descriptors()->GetDetails(descriptor),
3628  *value);
3629  return true;
3630 }

3634 void JSObject::AddProperty(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
3635  DirectHandle<Name> name, DirectHandle<Object> value,
3636  PropertyAttributes attributes) {
3637  name = isolate->factory()->InternalizeName(name);
3638  if (TryFastAddDataProperty(isolate, object, name, value, attributes)) {
3639  return;
3640  }
3641 
3642  LookupIterator it(isolate, object, name, object,
3643  LookupIterator::OWN_SKIP_INTERCEPTOR);
3644  CHECK_NE(LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK, it.state());
3645 #ifdef DEBUG
3646  uint32_t index;
3647  DCHECK(!IsJSProxy(*object));
3648  DCHECK(!IsWasmObject(*object));
3649  DCHECK(!name->AsArrayIndex(&index));
3650  Maybe<PropertyAttributes> maybe = GetPropertyAttributes(&it);
3651  DCHECK(maybe.IsJust());
3652  DCHECK(!it.IsFound());
3653  DCHECK(object->map()->is_extensible() || name->IsPrivate());
3654 #endif
3655  CHECK(Object::AddDataProperty(&it, value, attributes,
3656  Just(ShouldThrow::kThrowOnError),
3657  StoreOrigin::kNamed)
3658  .IsJust());
3659 }

3661 void JSObject::AddProperty(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
3662  const char* name, DirectHandle<Object> value,
3663  PropertyAttributes attributes) {
3664  JSObject::AddProperty(isolate, object,
3665  isolate->factory()->InternalizeUtf8String(name), value,
3666  attributes);
3667 }

3669 // Reconfigures a property to a data property with attributes, even if it is not
3670 // reconfigurable.
3671 // Requires a LookupIterator that does not look at the prototype chain beyond
3672 // hidden prototypes.
3673 Maybe<bool> JSObject::DefineOwnPropertyIgnoreAttributes(
3674  LookupIterator* it, DirectHandle<Object> value,
3675  PropertyAttributes attributes, Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw,
3676  AccessorInfoHandling handling, EnforceDefineSemantics semantics,
3677  StoreOrigin store_origin) {
3678  it->UpdateProtector();
3679 
3680  for (;; it->Next()) {
3681  switch (it->state()) {
3682  case LookupIterator::JSPROXY:
3683  case LookupIterator::TRANSITION:
3684  case LookupIterator::STRING_LOOKUP_START_OBJECT:
3685  UNREACHABLE();
3686  case LookupIterator::WASM_OBJECT:
3687  continue; // {AddDataProperty} will throw if no other case is hit.
3688 
3689  case LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK:
3690  if (!it->HasAccess()) {
3691  Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
3692  RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
3693  isolate,
3694  isolate->ReportFailedAccessCheck(it->GetHolder<JSObject>()),
3695  Nothing<bool>());
3696  UNREACHABLE();
3697  }
3698  continue;
3699 
3700  // If there's an interceptor, try to store the property with the
3701  // interceptor.
3702  // In case of success, the attributes will have been reset to the default
3703  // attributes of the interceptor, rather than the incoming attributes.
3704  //
3705  // TODO(verwaest): JSProxy afterwards verify the attributes that the
3706  // JSProxy claims it has, and verifies that they are compatible. If not,
3707  // they throw. Here we should do the same.
3708  case LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR: {
3709  InterceptorResult result;
3710  if (semantics == EnforceDefineSemantics::kDefine) {
3711  PropertyDescriptor descriptor;
3712  descriptor.set_configurable((attributes & DONT_DELETE) != 0);
3713  descriptor.set_enumerable((attributes & DONT_ENUM) != 0);
3714  descriptor.set_writable((attributes & READ_ONLY) != 0);
3715  descriptor.set_value(Cast<JSAny>(value));
3716  if (!DefinePropertyWithInterceptorInternal(it, it->GetInterceptor(),
3717  should_throw, &descriptor)
3718  .To(&result)) {
3719  // An exception was thrown in the interceptor. Propagate.
3720  return Nothing<bool>();
3721  }
3722  } else {
3723  DCHECK_EQ(semantics, EnforceDefineSemantics::kSet);
3724  if (handling == DONT_FORCE_FIELD) {
3725  if (!JSObject::SetPropertyWithInterceptor(it, should_throw, value)
3726  .To(&result)) {
3727  // An exception was thrown in the interceptor. Propagate.
3728  return Nothing<bool>();
3729  }
3730  } else {
3731  result = InterceptorResult::kNotIntercepted;
3732  }
3733  }
3734  switch (result) {
3735  case InterceptorResult::kFalse:
3736  return Just(false);
3737  case InterceptorResult::kTrue:
3738  return Just(true);
3739  case InterceptorResult::kNotIntercepted:
3740  // Proceed lookup.
3741  break;
3742  }
3743 
3744  if (semantics == EnforceDefineSemantics::kDefine) {
3745  it->Restart();
3746  Maybe<bool> can_define = JSObject::CheckIfCanDefineAsConfigurable(
3747  it->isolate(), it, value, should_throw);
3748  if (can_define.IsNothing() || !can_define.FromJust()) {
3749  return can_define;
3750  }
3751  }
3752 
3753  // The interceptor declined to handle the operation, so proceed defining
3754  // own property without the interceptor.
3755  Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
3756  DirectHandle<JSAny> receiver = it->GetReceiver();
3757  LookupIterator own_lookup(isolate, receiver, it->GetKey(),
3758  LookupIterator::OWN_SKIP_INTERCEPTOR);
3759  return JSObject::DefineOwnPropertyIgnoreAttributes(
3760  &own_lookup, value, attributes, should_throw, handling, semantics,
3761  store_origin);
3762  }
3763 
3764  case LookupIterator::ACCESSOR: {
3765  DirectHandle<Object> accessors = it->GetAccessors();
3766 
3767  // Special handling for AccessorInfo, which behaves like a data
3768  // property.
3769  if (IsAccessorInfo(*accessors) && handling == DONT_FORCE_FIELD) {
3770  PropertyAttributes current_attributes = it->property_attributes();
3771  // Ensure the context isn't changed after calling into accessors.
3772  AssertNoContextChange ncc(it->isolate());
3773 
3774  // Update the attributes before calling the setter. The setter may
3775  // later change the shape of the property.
3776  if (current_attributes != attributes) {
3777  it->TransitionToAccessorPair(accessors, attributes);
3778  }
3779 
3780  return Object::SetPropertyWithAccessor(it, value, should_throw);
3781  }
3782 
3783  it->ReconfigureDataProperty(value, attributes);
3784  return Just(true);
3785  }
3786  case LookupIterator::TYPED_ARRAY_INDEX_NOT_FOUND:
3787  return Object::RedefineIncompatibleProperty(
3788  it->isolate(), it->GetName(), value, should_throw);
3789 
3790  case LookupIterator::DATA: {
3791  // Regular property update if the attributes match.
3792  if (it->property_attributes() == attributes) {
3793  return Object::SetDataProperty(it, value);
3794  }
3795 
3796  // The non-matching attribute case for JSTypedArrays has already been
3797  // handled by JSTypedArray::DefineOwnProperty.
3798  DCHECK(!it->IsElement() ||
3799  !Cast<JSObject>(it->GetReceiver())
3800  ->HasTypedArrayOrRabGsabTypedArrayElements());
3801  // Reconfigure the data property if the attributes mismatch.
3802  it->ReconfigureDataProperty(value, attributes);
3803 
3804  return Just(true);
3805  }
3806 
3807  case LookupIterator::NOT_FOUND:
3808  return Object::AddDataProperty(it, value, attributes, should_throw,
3809  store_origin, semantics);
3810  }
3811  UNREACHABLE();
3812  }
3813 }

3847 void JSObject::NormalizeProperties(Isolate* isolate,
3848  DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
3849  PropertyNormalizationMode mode,
3850  int expected_additional_properties,
3851  bool use_cache, const char* reason) {

3856  {}, mode, use_cache, reason);

3859  expected_additional_properties);

3861 
3862 void JSObject::MigrateSlowToFast(DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
3863  int unused_property_fields,
3864  const char* reason) {
3865  if (object->HasFastProperties()) return;
3866  DCHECK(!IsJSGlobalObject(*object));
3867  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::Current();
3868  Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
3869 
3870  DirectHandle<NameDictionary> dictionary;
3871  DirectHandle<SwissNameDictionary> swiss_dictionary;
3872  int number_of_elements;
3873  if constexpr (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
3874  swiss_dictionary =
3875  direct_handle(object->property_dictionary_swiss(), isolate);
3876  number_of_elements = swiss_dictionary->NumberOfElements();
3877  } else {
3878  dictionary = direct_handle(object->property_dictionary(), isolate);
3879  number_of_elements = dictionary->NumberOfElements();
3880  }
3881 
3882  // Make sure we preserve dictionary representation if there are too many
3883  // descriptors.
3884  if (number_of_elements > kMaxNumberOfDescriptors) return;
3885 
3886  DirectHandle<FixedArray> iteration_order;
3887  int iteration_length;
3888  if constexpr (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
3889  // |iteration_order| remains empty handle, we don't need it.
3890  iteration_length = swiss_dictionary->UsedCapacity();
3891  } else {
3892  iteration_order = NameDictionary::IterationIndices(isolate, dictionary);
3893  iteration_length = dictionary->NumberOfElements();
3894  }
3895 
3896  int number_of_fields = 0;
3897 
3898  // Compute the length of the instance descriptor.
3899  ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
3900  for (int i = 0; i < iteration_length; i++) {
3901  PropertyKind kind;
3902  if constexpr (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
3903  InternalIndex index(swiss_dictionary->EntryForEnumerationIndex(i));
3904  Tagged<Object> key = swiss_dictionary->KeyAt(index);
3905  if (!SwissNameDictionary::IsKey(roots, key)) {
3906  // Ignore deleted entries.
3907  continue;
3908  }
3909  kind = swiss_dictionary->DetailsAt(index).kind();
3910  } else {
3911  InternalIndex index(Smi::ToInt(iteration_order->get(i)));
3912  DCHECK(dictionary->IsKey(roots, dictionary->KeyAt(isolate, index)));
3913  kind = dictionary->DetailsAt(index).kind();
3914  }
3915 
3916  if (kind == PropertyKind::kData) {
3917  number_of_fields += 1;
3918  }
3919  }
3920 
3921  DirectHandle<Map> old_map(object->map(), isolate);
3922 
3923  int inobject_props = old_map->GetInObjectProperties();
3924 
3925  // Allocate new map.
3926  DirectHandle<Map> new_map = Map::CopyDropDescriptors(isolate, old_map);
3927  // We should not only set this bit if we need to. We should not retain the
3928  // old bit because turning a map into dictionary always sets this bit.
3929  new_map->set_may_have_interesting_properties(
3930  new_map->has_named_interceptor() || new_map->is_access_check_needed());
3931  new_map->set_is_dictionary_map(false);
3932 
3933  NotifyMapChange(old_map, new_map, isolate);
3934 
3935  if (number_of_elements == 0) {
3936  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3937  DCHECK_LE(unused_property_fields, inobject_props);
3938  // Transform the object.
3939  new_map->SetInObjectUnusedPropertyFields(inobject_props);
3940  object->set_map(isolate, *new_map, kReleaseStore);
3941  object->SetProperties(ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).empty_fixed_array());
3942  // Check that it really works.
3943  DCHECK(object->HasFastProperties());
3944  if (v8_flags.log_maps) {
3945  LOG(isolate, MapEvent("SlowToFast", old_map, new_map, reason));
3946  }
3947  return;
3948  }
3949 
3950  // Allocate the instance descriptor.
3951  DirectHandle<DescriptorArray> descriptors =
3952  DescriptorArray::Allocate(isolate, number_of_elements, 0);
3953 
3954  int number_of_allocated_fields =
3955  number_of_fields + unused_property_fields - inobject_props;
3956  if (number_of_allocated_fields < 0) {
3957  // There is enough inobject space for all fields (including unused).
3958  number_of_allocated_fields = 0;
3959  unused_property_fields = inobject_props - number_of_fields;
3960  }
3961 
3962  // Allocate the property array for the fields.
3963  DirectHandle<PropertyArray> fields =
3964  factory->NewPropertyArray(number_of_allocated_fields);
3965 
3966  bool is_transitionable_elements_kind =
3967  IsTransitionableFastElementsKind(old_map->elements_kind());
3968 
3969  // Fill in the instance descriptor and the fields.
3970  int current_offset = 0;
3971  int descriptor_index = 0;
3972  for (int i = 0; i < iteration_length; i++) {
3973  Tagged<Name> k;
3974  Tagged<Object> value;
3975  PropertyDetails details = PropertyDetails::Empty();
3976 
3977  if constexpr (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
3978  InternalIndex index(swiss_dictionary->EntryForEnumerationIndex(i));
3979  Tagged<Object> key_obj = swiss_dictionary->KeyAt(index);
3980  if (!SwissNameDictionary::IsKey(roots, key_obj)) {
3981  continue;
3982  }
3983  k = Cast<Name>(key_obj);
3984 
3985  value = swiss_dictionary->ValueAt(index);
3986  details = swiss_dictionary->DetailsAt(index);
3987  } else {
3988  InternalIndex index(Smi::ToInt(iteration_order->get(i)));
3989  k = dictionary->NameAt(index);
3990 
3991  value = dictionary->ValueAt(index);
3992  details = dictionary->DetailsAt(index);
3993  }
3994 
3995  // Dictionary keys are internalized upon insertion.
3996  // TODO(jkummerow): Turn this into a DCHECK if it's not hit in the wild.
3997  CHECK(IsUniqueName(k));
3998  DirectHandle<Name> key(k, isolate);
3999 
4000  // Properly mark the {new_map} if the {key} is an "interesting symbol".
4001  if (key->IsInteresting(isolate)) {
4002  new_map->set_may_have_interesting_properties(true);
4003  }
4004 
4005  DCHECK_EQ(PropertyLocation::kField, details.location());
4006  DCHECK_IMPLIES(!V8_DICT_PROPERTY_CONST_TRACKING_BOOL,
4007  details.constness() == PropertyConstness::kMutable);
4008 
4009  Descriptor d;
4010  if (details.kind() == PropertyKind::kData) {
4011  // Ensure that we make constant field only when elements kind is not
4012  // transitionable.
4013  PropertyConstness constness = is_transitionable_elements_kind
4014  ? PropertyConstness::kMutable
4015  : PropertyConstness::kConst;
4016  // TODO(v8:11248): Consider always setting constness to kMutable
4017  // once all prototypes stay in dictionary mode and we are not interested
4018  // in tracking constness for fast mode properties anymore.
4019 
4020  d = Descriptor::DataField(
4021  key, current_offset, details.attributes(), constness,
4022  // TODO(verwaest): value->OptimalRepresentation();
4023  Representation::Tagged(),
4024  MaybeObjectDirectHandle(FieldType::Any(isolate)));
4025  } else {
4026  DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kAccessor, details.kind());
4027  d = Descriptor::AccessorConstant(key, direct_handle(value, isolate),
4028  details.attributes());
4029  }
4030  details = d.GetDetails();
4031  if (details.location() == PropertyLocation::kField) {
4032  if (current_offset < inobject_props) {
4033  object->InObjectPropertyAtPut(current_offset, value,
4034  UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER);
4035  } else {
4036  int offset = current_offset - inobject_props;
4037  fields->set(offset, value);
4038  }
4039  current_offset += details.field_width_in_words();
4040  }
4041  descriptors->Set(InternalIndex(descriptor_index++), &d);
4042  }
4043  DCHECK_EQ(current_offset, number_of_fields);
4044  DCHECK_EQ(descriptor_index, number_of_elements);
4045 
4046  descriptors->Sort();
4047 
4048  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4049  new_map->InitializeDescriptors(isolate, *descriptors);
4050  if (number_of_allocated_fields == 0) {
4051  new_map->SetInObjectUnusedPropertyFields(unused_property_fields);
4052  } else {
4053  new_map->SetOutOfObjectUnusedPropertyFields(unused_property_fields);
4054  }
4055 
4056  if (v8_flags.log_maps) {
4057  LOG(isolate, MapEvent("SlowToFast", old_map, new_map, reason));
4058  }
4059  // Transform the object.
4060  object->set_map(isolate, *new_map, kReleaseStore);
4061 
4062  object->SetProperties(*fields);
4063  DCHECK(IsJSObject(*object));
4064 
4065  // Check that it really works.
4066  DCHECK(object->HasFastProperties());
4067 }
4068 
4069 void JSObject::RequireSlowElements(Tagged<NumberDictionary> dictionary) {
4070  DCHECK_NE(dictionary,
4071  ReadOnlyRoots(Isolate::Current()).empty_slow_element_dictionary());
4072  if (dictionary->requires_slow_elements()) return;
4073  dictionary->set_requires_slow_elements();
4074  if (map()->is_prototype_map()) {
4075  // If this object is a prototype (the callee will check), invalidate any
4076  // prototype chains involving it.
4077  InvalidatePrototypeChains(map());
4078  }
4079 }
4080 
4081 DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> JSObject::NormalizeElements(
4082  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object) {
4083  DCHECK(!object->HasTypedArrayOrRabGsabTypedArrayElements());
4084  bool is_sloppy_arguments = object->HasSloppyArgumentsElements();
4085  {
4086  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4087  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> elements = object->elements();
4088 
4089  if (is_sloppy_arguments) {
4090  elements = Cast<SloppyArgumentsElements>(elements)->arguments();
4091  }
4092 
4093  if (IsNumberDictionary(elements)) {
4094  return direct_handle(Cast<NumberDictionary>(elements), isolate);
4095  }
4096  }
4097 
4098  DCHECK(object->HasSmiOrObjectElements() || object->HasDoubleElements() ||
4099  object->HasFastArgumentsElements() ||
4100  object->HasFastStringWrapperElements() ||
4101  object->HasSealedElements() || object->HasNonextensibleElements());
4102 
4103  DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> dictionary =
4104  object->GetElementsAccessor()->Normalize(isolate, object);
4105 
4106  // Switch to using the dictionary as the backing storage for elements.
4107  ElementsKind target_kind =
4108  is_sloppy_arguments ? SLOW_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS
4109  : object->HasFastStringWrapperElements() ? SLOW_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS
4110  : DICTIONARY_ELEMENTS;
4111  DirectHandle<Map> new_map =
4112  JSObject::GetElementsTransitionMap(isolate, object, target_kind);
4113  // Set the new map first to satisfy the elements type assert in
4114  // set_elements().
4115  JSObject::MigrateToMap(isolate, object, new_map);
4116 
4117  if (is_sloppy_arguments) {
4118  Cast<SloppyArgumentsElements>(object->elements())
4119  ->set_arguments(*dictionary);
4120  } else {
4121  object->set_elements(*dictionary);
4122  }
4123 
4124 #ifdef DEBUG
4125  if (v8_flags.trace_normalization) {
4126  StdoutStream os;
4127  os << "Object elements have been normalized:\n";
4128  Print(*object, os);
4129  }
4130 #endif
4131 
4132  DCHECK(object->HasDictionaryElements() ||
4133  object->HasSlowArgumentsElements() ||
4134  object->HasSlowStringWrapperElements());
4135  return dictionary;
4136 }
4137 
4138 Maybe<InterceptorResult> JSObject::DeletePropertyWithInterceptor(
4139  LookupIterator* it, ShouldThrow should_throw) {
4140  Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
4141  // Make sure that the top context does not change when doing callbacks or
4142  // interceptor calls.
4143  AssertNoContextChange ncc(isolate);
4144 
4145  DCHECK_EQ(LookupIterator::INTERCEPTOR, it->state());
4146  DirectHandle<InterceptorInfo> interceptor(it->GetInterceptor());
4147  if (!interceptor->has_deleter()) {
4148  return Just(InterceptorResult::kNotIntercepted);
4149  }
4150  DirectHandle<JSObject> holder = it->GetHolder<JSObject>();
4151  DirectHandle<Object> receiver = it->GetReceiver();
4152  if (!IsJSReceiver(*receiver)) {
4153  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate, receiver,
4154  Object::ConvertReceiver(isolate, receiver),
4155  Nothing<InterceptorResult>());
4156  }
4157 
4158  PropertyCallbackArguments args(isolate, interceptor->data(), *receiver,
4159  *holder, Just(should_throw));
4160 
4161  v8::Intercepted intercepted =
4162  it->IsElement(*holder)
4163  ? args.CallIndexedDeleter(interceptor, it->array_index())
4164  : args.CallNamedDeleter(interceptor, it->name());
4165 
4166  return args.GetBooleanReturnValue(intercepted, "Deleter");
4167 }

4169 Maybe<bool> JSObject::CreateDataProperty(Isolate* isolate,
4170  DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
4171  PropertyKey key,
4172  DirectHandle<Object> value,
4173  Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
4174  if (!key.is_element()) {
4175  if (TryFastAddDataProperty(isolate, object, key.name(), value, NONE)) {
4176  return Just(true);
4177  }
4178  }
4179 
4180  LookupIterator it(isolate, object, key, LookupIterator::OWN);
4181  Maybe<bool> can_define = JSObject::CheckIfCanDefineAsConfigurable(
4182  isolate, &it, value, should_throw);
4183  if (can_define.IsNothing() || !can_define.FromJust()) {
4184  return can_define;
4185  }
4186 
4187  RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate,
4188  DefineOwnPropertyIgnoreAttributes(&it, value, NONE),
4189  Nothing<bool>());
4190 
4191  return Just(true);
4192 }

4196 template <typename Dictionary>
4197 bool TestDictionaryPropertiesIntegrityLevel(Tagged<Dictionary> dict,
4198  ReadOnlyRoots roots,
4199  PropertyAttributes level) {
4200  DCHECK(level == SEALED || level == FROZEN);
4201 
4202  for (InternalIndex i : dict->IterateEntries()) {
4203  Tagged<Object> key;
4204  if (!dict->ToKey(roots, i, &key)) continue;
4205  if (Object::FilterKey(key, ALL_PROPERTIES)) continue;
4206  PropertyDetails details = dict->DetailsAt(i);
4207  if (details.IsConfigurable()) return false;
4208  if (level == FROZEN && details.kind() == PropertyKind::kData &&
4209  !details.IsReadOnly()) {
4210  return false;
4211  }
4212  }
4213  return true;
4214 }
4215 
4216 bool TestFastPropertiesIntegrityLevel(Tagged<Map> map,
4217  PropertyAttributes level) {
4218  DCHECK(level == SEALED || level == FROZEN);
4219  DCHECK(!IsCustomElementsReceiverMap(map));
4220  DCHECK(!map->is_dictionary_map());
4221 
4222  Tagged<DescriptorArray> descriptors = map->instance_descriptors();
4223  for (InternalIndex i : map->IterateOwnDescriptors()) {
4224  if (descriptors->GetKey(i)->IsPrivate()) continue;
4225  PropertyDetails details = descriptors->GetDetails(i);
4226  if (details.IsConfigurable()) return false;
4227  if (level == FROZEN && details.kind() == PropertyKind::kData &&
4228  !details.IsReadOnly()) {
4229  return false;
4230  }
4231  }
4232  return true;
4233 }
4234 
4235 bool TestPropertiesIntegrityLevel(Tagged<JSObject> object,
4236  PropertyAttributes level) {
4237  DCHECK(!IsCustomElementsReceiverMap(object->map()));
4238 
4239  if (object->HasFastProperties()) {
4240  return TestFastPropertiesIntegrityLevel(object->map(), level);
4241  }
4242 
4243  if constexpr (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
4244  return TestDictionaryPropertiesIntegrityLevel(
4245  object->property_dictionary_swiss(), GetReadOnlyRoots(), level);
4246  } else {
4247  return TestDictionaryPropertiesIntegrityLevel(object->property_dictionary(),
4248  GetReadOnlyRoots(), level);
4249  }
4250 }
4251 
4252 bool TestElementsIntegrityLevel(Isolate* isolate, Tagged<JSObject> object,
4253  PropertyAttributes level) {
4254  DCHECK(!object->HasSloppyArgumentsElements());
4255 
4256  ElementsKind kind = object->GetElementsKind();
4257 
4258  if (IsDictionaryElementsKind(kind)) {
4259  return TestDictionaryPropertiesIntegrityLevel(
4260  Cast<NumberDictionary>(object->elements()), GetReadOnlyRoots(), level);
4261  }
4262  if (IsTypedArrayOrRabGsabTypedArrayElementsKind(kind)) {
4263  if (level == FROZEN && Cast<JSArrayBufferView>(object)->byte_length() > 0) {
4264  return false; // TypedArrays with elements can't be frozen.
4265  }
4266  return TestPropertiesIntegrityLevel(object, level);
4267  }
4268  if (IsFrozenElementsKind(kind)) return true;
4269  if (IsSealedElementsKind(kind) && level != FROZEN) return true;
4270  if (IsNonextensibleElementsKind(kind) && level == NONE) return true;
4271 
4272  ElementsAccessor* accessor = ElementsAccessor::ForKind(kind);
4273  // Only DICTIONARY_ELEMENTS and SLOW_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS have
4274  // PropertyAttributes so just test if empty
4275  return accessor->NumberOfElements(isolate, object) == 0;
4276 }
4277 
4278 bool FastTestIntegrityLevel(Isolate* isolate, Tagged<JSObject> object,
4279  PropertyAttributes level) {
4280  DCHECK(!IsCustomElementsReceiverMap(object->map()));
4281 
4282  return !object->map()->is_extensible() &&
4283  TestElementsIntegrityLevel(isolate, object, level) &&
4284  TestPropertiesIntegrityLevel(object, level);
4285 }
4286 
4287 } // namespace
4288 
4289 Maybe<bool> JSObject::TestIntegrityLevel(Isolate* isolate,
4290  DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
4291  IntegrityLevel level) {
4292  if (!IsCustomElementsReceiverMap(object->map()) &&
4293  !object->HasSloppyArgumentsElements()) {
4294  return Just(FastTestIntegrityLevel(isolate, *object, level));
4295  }
4296  return GenericTestIntegrityLevel(isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(object), level);
4297 }
4298 
4299 Maybe<bool> JSObject::PreventExtensions(Isolate* isolate,
4300  DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
4301  ShouldThrow should_throw) {
4302  if (!object->HasSloppyArgumentsElements()) {
4303  return PreventExtensionsWithTransition<NONE>(isolate, object, should_throw);
4304  }
4305 
4306  if (IsAccessCheckNeeded(*object) &&
4307  !isolate->MayAccess(isolate->native_context(), object)) {
4308  RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate, isolate->ReportFailedAccessCheck(object),
4309  Nothing<bool>());
4310  UNREACHABLE();
4311  }
4312 
4313  if (!object->map()->is_extensible()) return Just(true);
4314 
4315  if (IsJSGlobalProxy(*object)) {
4316  PrototypeIterator iter(isolate, object);
4317  if (iter.IsAtEnd()) return Just(true);
4318  DCHECK(IsJSGlobalObject(*PrototypeIterator::GetCurrent(iter)));
4319  return PreventExtensions(
4320  isolate, PrototypeIterator::GetCurrent<JSObject>(iter), should_throw);
4321  }
4322 
4323  if (object->map()->has_named_interceptor() ||
4324  object->map()->has_indexed_interceptor()) {
4325  RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, should_throw,
4326  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kCannotPreventExt));
4327  }
4328 
4329  DCHECK(!object->HasTypedArrayOrRabGsabTypedArrayElements());
4330 
4331  // Normalize fast elements.
4332  DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> dictionary =
4333  NormalizeElements(isolate, object);
4334  DCHECK(object->HasDictionaryElements() || object->HasSlowArgumentsElements());
4335 
4336  // Make sure that we never go back to fast case.
4337  if (*dictionary != ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).empty_slow_element_dictionary()) {
4338  object->RequireSlowElements(*dictionary);
4339  }
4340 
4341  // Do a map transition, other objects with this map may still
4342  // be extensible.
4343  // TODO(adamk): Extend the NormalizedMapCache to handle non-extensible maps.
4344  DirectHandle<Map> new_map = Map::Copy(
4345  isolate, direct_handle(object->map(), isolate), "PreventExtensions");
4346 
4347  new_map->set_is_extensible(false);
4348  JSObject::MigrateToMap(isolate, object, new_map);
4349  DCHECK(!object->map()->is_extensible());
4350 
4351  return Just(true);
4352 }
4353 
4354 bool JSObject::IsExtensible(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object) {
4355  if (IsAccessCheckNeeded(*object) &&
4356  !isolate->MayAccess(isolate->native_context(), object)) {
4357  return true;
4358  }
4359  if (IsJSGlobalProxy(*object)) {
4360  PrototypeIterator iter(isolate, *object);
4361  if (iter.IsAtEnd()) return false;
4362  DCHECK(IsJSGlobalObject(iter.GetCurrent()));
4363  return iter.GetCurrent<JSObject>()->map()->is_extensible();
4364  }
4365  return object->map()->is_extensible();
4366 }

4369 MaybeDirectHandle<Object> JSObject::ReadFromOptionsBag(
4370  DirectHandle<Object> options, DirectHandle<String> option_name,
4371  Isolate* isolate) {
4372  if (IsJSReceiver(*options)) {
4373  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> js_options = Cast<JSReceiver>(options);
4374  return JSObject::GetProperty(isolate, js_options, option_name);
4375  }
4376  return MaybeDirectHandle<Object>(isolate->factory()->undefined_value());
4377 }
