4379 template <typename Dictionary>
4380 void JSObject::ApplyAttributesToDictionary(
4381  Isolate* isolate, ReadOnlyRoots roots, DirectHandle<Dictionary> dictionary,
4382  const PropertyAttributes attributes) {
4383  for (InternalIndex i : dictionary->IterateEntries()) {
4384  Tagged<Object> k;
4385  if (!dictionary->ToKey(roots, i, &k)) continue;
4386  if (Object::FilterKey(k, ALL_PROPERTIES)) continue;
4387  PropertyDetails details = dictionary->DetailsAt(i);
4388  int attrs = attributes;
4389  // READ_ONLY is an invalid attribute for JS setters/getters.
4390  if ((attributes & READ_ONLY) && details.kind() == PropertyKind::kAccessor) {
4391  Tagged<Object> v = dictionary->ValueAt(i);
4392  if (IsAccessorPair(v)) attrs &= ~READ_ONLY;
4393  }
4394  details = details.CopyAddAttributes(PropertyAttributesFromInt(attrs));
4395  dictionary->DetailsAtPut(i, details);
4396  }
4397 }
4398 
4399 template void JSObject::ApplyAttributesToDictionary(
4400  Isolate* isolate, ReadOnlyRoots roots,
4401  DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> dictionary,
4402  const PropertyAttributes attributes);
4403 
4404 DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> CreateElementDictionary(
4405  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object) {
4406  DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> new_element_dictionary;
4407  if (!object->HasTypedArrayOrRabGsabTypedArrayElements() &&
4408  !object->HasDictionaryElements() &&
4409  !object->HasSlowStringWrapperElements()) {
4410  int length = IsJSArray(*object)
4411  ? Smi::ToInt(Cast<JSArray>(object)->length())
4412  : object->elements()->length();
4413  new_element_dictionary =
4414  length == 0 ? isolate->factory()->empty_slow_element_dictionary()
4415  : object->GetElementsAccessor()->Normalize(isolate, object);
4416  }
4417  return new_element_dictionary;
4418 }
4419 
4420 template <PropertyAttributes attrs>
4421 Maybe<bool> JSObject::PreventExtensionsWithTransition(
4422  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object, ShouldThrow should_throw) {
4423  static_assert(attrs == NONE || attrs == SEALED || attrs == FROZEN);
4424 
4425  // Sealing/freezing sloppy arguments or namespace objects should be handled
4426  // elsewhere.
4427  DCHECK(!object->HasSloppyArgumentsElements());
4428  DCHECK_IMPLIES(IsJSModuleNamespace(*object), attrs == NONE);
4429 
4430  if (IsAccessCheckNeeded(*object) &&
4431  !isolate->MayAccess(isolate->native_context(), object)) {
4432  RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(isolate, isolate->ReportFailedAccessCheck(object),
4433  Nothing<bool>());
4434  UNREACHABLE();
4435  }
4436 
4437  if (attrs == NONE && !object->map()->is_extensible()) {
4438  return Just(true);
4439  }
4440 
4441  {
4442  ElementsKind old_elements_kind = object->map()->elements_kind();
4443  if (IsFrozenElementsKind(old_elements_kind)) return Just(true);
4444  if (attrs != FROZEN && IsSealedElementsKind(old_elements_kind)) {
4445  return Just(true);
4446  }
4447  }
4448 
4449  if (IsJSGlobalProxy(*object)) {
4450  PrototypeIterator iter(isolate, object);
4451  if (iter.IsAtEnd()) return Just(true);
4452  DCHECK(IsJSGlobalObject(*PrototypeIterator::GetCurrent(iter)));
4453  return PreventExtensionsWithTransition<attrs>(
4454  isolate, PrototypeIterator::GetCurrent<JSObject>(iter), should_throw);
4455  }
4456 
4457  // Shared objects are designed to have fixed layout, i.e. their maps are
4458  // effectively immutable. They are constructed seal, but the semantics of
4459  // ordinary ECMAScript objects allow sealed to be upgraded to frozen. This
4460  // upgrade violates the fixed layout invariant and is disallowed.
4461  if (IsAlwaysSharedSpaceJSObject(*object)) {
4462  DCHECK(FastTestIntegrityLevel(isolate, *object, SEALED));
4463  if (attrs != FROZEN) return Just(true);
4464  RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, should_throw,
4465  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kCannotFreeze));
4466  }
4467 
4468  if (object->map()->has_named_interceptor() ||
4469  object->map()->has_indexed_interceptor() ||
4470  (object->HasTypedArrayOrRabGsabTypedArrayElements() &&
4471  Cast<JSTypedArray>(*object)->IsVariableLength())) {
4472  MessageTemplate message = MessageTemplate::kNone;
4473  switch (attrs) {
4474  case NONE:
4475  message = MessageTemplate::kCannotPreventExt;
4476  break;
4477 
4478  case SEALED:
4479  message = MessageTemplate::kCannotSeal;
4480  break;
4481 
4482  case FROZEN:
4483  message = MessageTemplate::kCannotFreeze;
4484  break;
4485  }
4486  RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, should_throw, NewTypeError(message));
4487  }
4488 
4489  DirectHandle<Symbol> transition_marker;
4490  if (attrs == NONE) {
4491  transition_marker = isolate->factory()->nonextensible_symbol();
4492  } else if (attrs == SEALED) {
4493  transition_marker = isolate->factory()->sealed_symbol();
4494  } else {
4495  DCHECK(attrs == FROZEN);
4496  transition_marker = isolate->factory()->frozen_symbol();
4497  }
4498 
4499  // Currently, there are only have sealed/frozen Object element kinds and
4500  // Map::MigrateToMap doesn't handle properties' attributes reconfiguring and
4501  // elements kind change in one go. If seal or freeze with Smi or Double
4502  // elements kind, we will transition to Object elements kind first to make
4503  // sure of valid element access.
4504  switch (object->map()->elements_kind()) {
4505  case PACKED_SMI_ELEMENTS:
4506  case PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS:
4507  JSObject::TransitionElementsKind(isolate, object, PACKED_ELEMENTS);
4508  break;
4509  case HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS:
4510  case HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS:
4511  JSObject::TransitionElementsKind(isolate, object, HOLEY_ELEMENTS);
4512  break;
4513  default:
4514  break;
4515  }
4516 
4517  // Make sure we only use this element dictionary in case we can't transition
4518  // to sealed, frozen elements kind.
4519  DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> new_element_dictionary;
4520 
4521  DirectHandle<Map> old_map(object->map(), isolate);
4522  old_map = Map::Update(isolate, old_map);
4523  DirectHandle<Map> transition_map;
4524  MaybeDirectHandle<Map> maybe_transition_map =
4525  TransitionsAccessor::SearchSpecial(isolate, old_map, *transition_marker);
4526  if (maybe_transition_map.ToHandle(&transition_map)) {
4527  DCHECK(transition_map->has_dictionary_elements() ||
4528  transition_map->has_typed_array_or_rab_gsab_typed_array_elements() ||
4529  transition_map->elements_kind() == SLOW_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS ||
4530  transition_map->has_any_nonextensible_elements());
4531  DCHECK(!transition_map->is_extensible());
4532  if (!transition_map->has_any_nonextensible_elements()) {
4533  new_element_dictionary = CreateElementDictionary(isolate, object);
4534  }
4535  JSObject::MigrateToMap(isolate, object, transition_map);
4536  } else if (TransitionsAccessor::CanHaveMoreTransitions(isolate, old_map)) {
4537  // Create a new descriptor array with the appropriate property attributes
4538  DirectHandle<Map> new_map = Map::CopyForPreventExtensions(
4539  isolate, old_map, attrs, transition_marker, "CopyForPreventExtensions");
4540  if (!new_map->has_any_nonextensible_elements()) {
4541  new_element_dictionary = CreateElementDictionary(isolate, object);
4542  }
4543  JSObject::MigrateToMap(isolate, object, new_map);
4544  } else {
4545  DCHECK(old_map->is_dictionary_map() || !old_map->is_prototype_map());
4546  // Slow path: need to normalize properties for safety
4547  NormalizeProperties(isolate, object, CLEAR_INOBJECT_PROPERTIES, 0,
4548  "SlowPreventExtensions");
4549 
4550  // Create a new map, since other objects with this map may be extensible.
4551  // TODO(adamk): Extend the NormalizedMapCache to handle non-extensible maps.
4552  DirectHandle<Map> new_map =
4553  Map::Copy(isolate, direct_handle(object->map(), isolate),
4554  "SlowCopyForPreventExtensions");
4555  new_map->set_is_extensible(false);
4556  new_element_dictionary = CreateElementDictionary(isolate, object);
4557  if (!new_element_dictionary.is_null()) {
4558  ElementsKind new_kind =
4559  IsStringWrapperElementsKind(old_map->elements_kind())
4560  ? SLOW_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS
4561  : DICTIONARY_ELEMENTS;
4562  new_map->set_elements_kind(new_kind);
4563  }
4564  JSObject::MigrateToMap(isolate, object, new_map);
4565 
4566  if (attrs != NONE) {
4567  ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
4568  if (IsJSGlobalObject(*object)) {
4569  DirectHandle<GlobalDictionary> dictionary(
4570  Cast<JSGlobalObject>(*object)->global_dictionary(kAcquireLoad),
4571  isolate);
4572  JSObject::ApplyAttributesToDictionary(isolate, roots, dictionary,
4573  attrs);
4574  } else if constexpr (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
4575  DirectHandle<SwissNameDictionary> dictionary(
4576  object->property_dictionary_swiss(), isolate);
4577  JSObject::ApplyAttributesToDictionary(isolate, roots, dictionary,
4578  attrs);
4579  } else {
4580  DirectHandle<NameDictionary> dictionary(object->property_dictionary(),
4581  isolate);
4582  JSObject::ApplyAttributesToDictionary(isolate, roots, dictionary,
4583  attrs);
4584  }
4585  }
4586  }
4587 
4588  if (object->map()->has_any_nonextensible_elements()) {
4589  DCHECK(new_element_dictionary.is_null());
4590  return Just(true);
4591  }
4592 
4593  // PreventExtensions works without modifications to typed array elements if
4594  // the typed array is fixed length; see #sec-typedarray-preventextensions.
4595  // Seal and freeze work only if there are no actual elements, because
4596  // TypedArray elements cannot be reconfigured; see
4597  // #sec-typedarray-defineownproperty.
4598  if (object->HasTypedArrayOrRabGsabTypedArrayElements()) {
4599  DCHECK(new_element_dictionary.is_null());
4600  if (attrs != NONE && Cast<JSTypedArray>(*object)->GetLength() > 0) {
4601  isolate->Throw(*isolate->factory()->NewTypeError(
4602  attrs == SEALED ? MessageTemplate::kCannotSealArrayBufferView
4603  : MessageTemplate::kCannotFreezeArrayBufferView));
4604  return Nothing<bool>();
4605  }
4606  return Just(true);
4607  }
4608 
4609  DCHECK(object->map()->has_dictionary_elements() ||
4610  object->map()->elements_kind() == SLOW_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS);
4611  if (!new_element_dictionary.is_null()) {
4612  object->set_elements(*new_element_dictionary);
4613  }
4614 
4615  if (object->elements() !=
4616  ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).empty_slow_element_dictionary()) {
4617  DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> dictionary(object->element_dictionary(),
4618  isolate);
4619  // Make sure we never go back to the fast case
4620  object->RequireSlowElements(*dictionary);
4621  if (attrs != NONE) {
4622  JSObject::ApplyAttributesToDictionary(isolate, ReadOnlyRoots(isolate),
4623  dictionary, attrs);
4624  }
4625  }
4626 
4627  return Just(true);
4628 }
4629 
4630 Handle<JSAny> JSObject::FastPropertyAt(Isolate* isolate,
4631  DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
4632  Representation representation,
4633  FieldIndex index) {
4634  Handle<JSAny> raw_value(object->RawFastPropertyAt(index), isolate);
4635  return Object::WrapForRead(isolate, raw_value, representation);
4636 }

4661 // static
4662 std::optional<Tagged<Object>> JSObject::DictionaryPropertyAt(
4663  DirectHandle<JSObject> object, InternalIndex dict_index, Heap* heap) {
4664  Tagged<Object> backing_store = object->raw_properties_or_hash(kRelaxedLoad);
4665  if (!IsHeapObject(backing_store)) return {};
4666  if (heap->IsPendingAllocation(Cast<HeapObject>(backing_store))) return {};
4667 
4668  if (!IsPropertyDictionary(backing_store)) return {};
4669  std::optional<Tagged<Object>> maybe_obj =
4670  Cast<PropertyDictionary>(backing_store)->TryValueAt(dict_index);
4671 
4672  if (!maybe_obj) return {};
4673  return maybe_obj.value();
4674 }

4676 // TODO(cbruni/jkummerow): Consider moving this into elements.cc.
4677 bool JSObject::HasEnumerableElements() {
4678  // TODO(cbruni): cleanup
4679  Tagged<JSObject> object = *this;
4680  switch (object->GetElementsKind()) {
4681  case PACKED_SMI_ELEMENTS:
4682  case PACKED_ELEMENTS:
4683  case PACKED_FROZEN_ELEMENTS:
4684  case PACKED_SEALED_ELEMENTS:
4685  case PACKED_NONEXTENSIBLE_ELEMENTS:
4686  case PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS:
4687  case SHARED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS: {
4688  int length = IsJSArray(object)
4689  ? Smi::ToInt(Cast<JSArray>(object)->length())
4690  : object->elements()->length();
4691  return length > 0;
4692  }
4693  case HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS:
4694  case HOLEY_FROZEN_ELEMENTS:
4695  case HOLEY_SEALED_ELEMENTS:
4696  case HOLEY_NONEXTENSIBLE_ELEMENTS:
4697  case HOLEY_ELEMENTS: {
4698  Tagged<FixedArray> elements = Cast<FixedArray>(object->elements());
4699  int length = IsJSArray(object)
4700  ? Smi::ToInt(Cast<JSArray>(object)->length())
4701  : elements->length();
4702  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::Current();
4703  for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) {
4704  if (!elements->is_the_hole(isolate, i)) return true;
4705  }
4706  return false;
4707  }
4708  case HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS: {
4709  int length = IsJSArray(object)
4710  ? Smi::ToInt(Cast<JSArray>(object)->length())
4711  : object->elements()->length();
4712  // Zero-length arrays would use the empty FixedArray...
4713  if (length == 0) return false;
4714  // ...so only cast to FixedDoubleArray otherwise.
4715  Tagged<FixedDoubleArray> elements =
4716  Cast<FixedDoubleArray>(object->elements());
4717  for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) {
4718  if (!elements->is_the_hole(i)) return true;
4719  }
4720  return false;
4721  }
4722 #define TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Type, type, TYPE, ctype) case TYPE##_ELEMENTS:
4723 
4724  TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE) {
4725  size_t byte_length = Cast<JSTypedArray>(object)->byte_length();
4726  return byte_length > 0;
4727  }
4728 
4729  RAB_GSAB_TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)
4730 #undef TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
4731  {
4732  size_t length = Cast<JSTypedArray>(object)->GetLength();
4733  return length > 0;
4734  }
4735  case DICTIONARY_ELEMENTS: {
4736  Tagged<NumberDictionary> elements =
4737  Cast<NumberDictionary>(object->elements());
4738  return elements->NumberOfEnumerableProperties() > 0;
4739  }
4740  case FAST_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS:
4741  case SLOW_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS:
4742  // We're approximating non-empty arguments objects here.
4743  return true;
4744  case FAST_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS:
4745  case SLOW_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS:
4746  if (Cast<String>(Cast<JSPrimitiveWrapper>(object)->value())->length() >
4747  0) {
4748  return true;
4749  }
4750  return object->elements()->length() > 0;
4751  case WASM_ARRAY_ELEMENTS:
4752  UNIMPLEMENTED();
4753 
4754  case NO_ELEMENTS:
4755  return false;
4756  }
4757  UNREACHABLE();
4758 }

4760 MaybeDirectHandle<Object> JSObject::DefineOwnAccessorIgnoreAttributes(
4761  DirectHandle<JSObject> object, DirectHandle<Name> name,
4762  DirectHandle<Object> getter, DirectHandle<Object> setter,
4763  PropertyAttributes attributes) {
4764  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::Current();
4765 
4766  PropertyKey key(isolate, name);
4767  LookupIterator it(isolate, object, key, LookupIterator::OWN_SKIP_INTERCEPTOR);
4768  return DefineOwnAccessorIgnoreAttributes(&it, getter, setter, attributes);
4769 }
4770 
4771 MaybeDirectHandle<Object> JSObject::DefineOwnAccessorIgnoreAttributes(
4772  LookupIterator* it, DirectHandle<Object> getter,
4773  DirectHandle<Object> setter, PropertyAttributes attributes) {
4774  Isolate* isolate = it->isolate();
4775 
4776  it->UpdateProtector();
4777 
4778  while (it->state() == LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK) {
4779  if (!it->HasAccess()) {
4780  RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
4781  isolate, isolate->ReportFailedAccessCheck(it->GetHolder<JSObject>()));
4782  UNREACHABLE();
4783  }
4784  it->Next();
4785  }
4786 
4787  auto object = Cast<JSObject>(it->GetReceiver());
4788  // Ignore accessors on typed arrays.
4789  if (it->IsElement() && object->HasTypedArrayOrRabGsabTypedArrayElements()) {
4790  return it->factory()->undefined_value();
4791  }
4792 
4793  DCHECK(IsCallable(*getter) || IsUndefined(*getter, isolate) ||
4794  IsNull(*getter, isolate) || IsFunctionTemplateInfo(*getter));
4795  DCHECK(IsCallable(*setter) || IsUndefined(*setter, isolate) ||
4796  IsNull(*setter, isolate) || IsFunctionTemplateInfo(*setter));
4797  it->TransitionToAccessorProperty(getter, setter, attributes);
4798 
4799  return isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
4800 }
4801 
4802 MaybeDirectHandle<Object> JSObject::SetAccessor(DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
4803  DirectHandle<Name> name,
4804  DirectHandle<AccessorInfo> info,
4805  PropertyAttributes attributes) {
4806  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::Current();
4807 
4808  PropertyKey key(isolate, name);
4809  LookupIterator it(isolate, object, key, LookupIterator::OWN_SKIP_INTERCEPTOR);
4810 
4811  // Duplicate ACCESS_CHECK outside of GetPropertyAttributes for the case that
4812  // the FailedAccessCheckCallbackFunction doesn't throw an exception.
4813  while (it.state() == LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK) {
4814  if (!it.HasAccess()) {
4815  RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, isolate->ReportFailedAccessCheck(object));
4816  UNREACHABLE();
4817  }
4818  it.Next();
4819  }
4820 
4821  // Ignore accessors on typed arrays.
4822  if (it.IsElement() && object->HasTypedArrayOrRabGsabTypedArrayElements()) {
4823  return it.factory()->undefined_value();
4824  }
4825 
4826  Maybe<bool> can_define = JSObject::CheckIfCanDefineAsConfigurable(
4827  isolate, &it, info, Nothing<ShouldThrow>());
4828  MAYBE_RETURN_NULL(can_define);
4829  if (!can_define.FromJust()) return it.factory()->undefined_value();
4830 
4831  it.TransitionToAccessorPair(info, attributes);
4832 
4833  return object;
4834 }
4835 
4836 // static
4837 Maybe<bool> JSObject::CheckIfCanDefineAsConfigurable(
4838  Isolate* isolate, LookupIterator* it, DirectHandle<Object> value,
4839  Maybe<ShouldThrow> should_throw) {
4840  DCHECK(IsJSObject(*it->GetReceiver()));
4841  if (it->IsFound()) {
4842  Maybe<PropertyAttributes> attributes = GetPropertyAttributes(it);
4843  MAYBE_RETURN(attributes, Nothing<bool>());
4844  if (attributes.FromJust() != ABSENT) {
4845  if ((attributes.FromJust() & DONT_DELETE) != 0) {
4846  RETURN_FAILURE(
4847  isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, should_throw),
4848  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kRedefineDisallowed, it->GetName()));
4849  }
4850  return Just(true);
4851  }
4852  // Property does not exist, check object extensibility.
4853  }
4854  if (!JSObject::IsExtensible(isolate, Cast<JSObject>(it->GetReceiver()))) {
4855  RETURN_FAILURE(
4856  isolate, GetShouldThrow(isolate, should_throw),
4857  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kDefineDisallowed, it->GetName()));
4858  }
4859  return Just(true);
4860 }
4861 
4862 Tagged<Object> JSObject::SlowReverseLookup(Tagged<Object> value) {
4863  if (HasFastProperties()) {
4864  Tagged<DescriptorArray> descs = map()->instance_descriptors();
4865  bool value_is_number = IsNumber(value);
4866  for (InternalIndex i : map()->IterateOwnDescriptors()) {
4867  PropertyDetails details = descs->GetDetails(i);
4868  if (details.location() == PropertyLocation::kField) {
4869  DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kData, details.kind());
4870  FieldIndex field_index = FieldIndex::ForDetails(map(), details);
4871  Tagged<Object> property = RawFastPropertyAt(field_index);
4872  if (field_index.is_double()) {
4873  DCHECK(IsHeapNumber(property));
4874  if (value_is_number && Cast<HeapNumber>(property)->value() ==
4875  Object::NumberValue(Cast<Number>(value))) {
4876  return descs->GetKey(i);
4877  }
4878  } else if (property == value) {
4879  return descs->GetKey(i);
4880  }
4881  } else {
4882  DCHECK_EQ(PropertyLocation::kDescriptor, details.location());
4883  if (details.kind() == PropertyKind::kData) {
4884  if (descs->GetStrongValue(i) == value) {
4885  return descs->GetKey(i);
4886  }
4887  }
4888  }
4889  }
4890  return GetReadOnlyRoots().undefined_value();
4891  } else if (IsJSGlobalObject(*this)) {
4892  return Cast<JSGlobalObject>(*this)
4893  ->global_dictionary(kAcquireLoad)
4894  ->SlowReverseLookup(value);
4895  } else if constexpr (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
4896  return property_dictionary_swiss()->SlowReverseLookup(Isolate::Current(),
4897  value);
4898  } else {
4899  return property_dictionary()->SlowReverseLookup(value);
4900  }
4901 }
4902 
4903 void JSObject::PrototypeRegistryCompactionCallback(Tagged<HeapObject> value,
4904  int old_index,
4905  int new_index) {
4906  DCHECK(IsMap(value) && Cast<Map>(value)->is_prototype_map());
4907  Tagged<Map> map = Cast<Map>(value);
4908  DCHECK(IsPrototypeInfo(map->prototype_info()));
4909  Tagged<PrototypeInfo> proto_info = Cast<PrototypeInfo>(map->prototype_info());
4910  DCHECK_EQ(old_index, proto_info->registry_slot());
4911  proto_info->set_registry_slot(new_index);
4912 }

4914 // static
4915 void JSObject::MakePrototypesFast(DirectHandle<Object> receiver,
4916  WhereToStart where_to_start,
4917  Isolate* isolate) {
4918  if (!IsJSReceiver(*receiver)) return;
4919  if (IsWasmObject(*receiver)) where_to_start = kStartAtPrototype;
4920  for (PrototypeIterator iter(isolate, Cast<JSReceiver>(receiver),
4921  where_to_start);
4922  !iter.IsAtEnd(); iter.Advance()) {
4923  DirectHandle<Object> current = PrototypeIterator::GetCurrent(iter);
4924  if (!IsJSObjectThatCanBeTrackedAsPrototype(*current)) return;
4925  DirectHandle<JSObject> current_obj = Cast<JSObject>(current);
4926  Tagged<Map> current_map = current_obj->map();
4927  if (current_map->is_prototype_map()) {
4928  // If the map is already marked as should be fast, we're done. Its
4929  // prototypes will have been marked already as well.
4930  if (current_map->should_be_fast_prototype_map()) return;
4931  DirectHandle<Map> map(current_map, isolate);
4932  Map::SetShouldBeFastPrototypeMap(map, true, isolate);
4933  JSObject::OptimizeAsPrototype(current_obj);
4934  }
4935  }
4936 }
4937 
4938 static bool PrototypeBenefitsFromNormalization(Tagged<JSObject> object) {
4939  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4940  if (!object->HasFastProperties()) return false;
4941  if (IsJSGlobalProxy(object)) return false;
4942  // TODO(v8:11248) make bootstrapper create dict mode prototypes, too?
4943  if (Isolate::Current()->bootstrapper()->IsActive()) return false;
4944  if (V8_DICT_PROPERTY_CONST_TRACKING_BOOL) return true;
4945  return !object->map()->is_prototype_map() ||
4946  !object->map()->should_be_fast_prototype_map();
4947 }
4948 
4949 // static
4950 void JSObject::OptimizeAsPrototype(DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
4951  bool enable_setup_mode) {
4952  DCHECK(IsJSObjectThatCanBeTrackedAsPrototype(*object));
4953  if (IsJSGlobalObject(*object)) return;
4954  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::Current();
4955  if (object->map()->is_prototype_map()) {
4956  if (enable_setup_mode && PrototypeBenefitsFromNormalization(*object)) {
4957  // This is the only way PrototypeBenefitsFromNormalization can be true:
4958  DCHECK(!object->map()->should_be_fast_prototype_map());
4959  // First normalize to ensure all JSFunctions are DATA_CONSTANT.
4960  constexpr bool kUseCache = true;
4961  JSObject::NormalizeProperties(isolate, object, KEEP_INOBJECT_PROPERTIES,
4962  0, kUseCache, "NormalizeAsPrototype");
4963  }
4964  if (!V8_DICT_PROPERTY_CONST_TRACKING_BOOL &&
4965  object->map()->should_be_fast_prototype_map() &&
4966  !object->HasFastProperties()) {
4967  JSObject::MigrateSlowToFast(object, 0, "OptimizeAsPrototype");
4968  }
4969  } else {
4970  DirectHandle<Map> new_map;
4971  if (enable_setup_mode && PrototypeBenefitsFromNormalization(*object)) {
4972 #if DEBUG
4973  DirectHandle<Map> old_map(object->map(isolate), isolate);
4974 #endif // DEBUG
4975  // First normalize to ensure all JSFunctions are DATA_CONSTANT. Don't use
4976  // the cache, since we're going to use the normalized version directly,
4977  // without making a copy.
4978  constexpr bool kUseCache = false;
4979  JSObject::NormalizeProperties(isolate, object, KEEP_INOBJECT_PROPERTIES,
4980  0, kUseCache,
4981  "NormalizeAndCopyAsPrototype");
4982  // A new map was created.
4983  DCHECK_NE(*old_map, object->map(isolate));
4984 
4985  new_map = direct_handle(object->map(isolate), isolate);
4986  } else {
4987  new_map = Map::Copy(isolate, direct_handle(object->map(), isolate),
4988  "CopyAsPrototype");
4989  }
4990  new_map->set_is_prototype_map(true);
4991 
4992  // Replace the pointer to the exact constructor with the Object function
4993  // from the same context if undetectable from JS. This is to avoid keeping
4994  // memory alive unnecessarily.
4995  Tagged<Object> maybe_constructor = new_map->GetConstructorRaw();
4996  Tagged<Tuple2> tuple;
4997  if (IsTuple2(maybe_constructor)) {
4998  // Handle the {constructor, non-instance_prototype} tuple case if the map
4999  // has non-instance prototype.
5000  tuple = Cast<Tuple2>(maybe_constructor);
5001  maybe_constructor = tuple->value1();
5002  }
5003  if (IsJSFunction(maybe_constructor)) {
5004  Tagged<JSFunction> constructor = Cast<JSFunction>(maybe_constructor);
5005  if (!constructor->shared()->IsApiFunction()) {
5006  Tagged<NativeContext> context = constructor->native_context();
5007  Tagged<JSFunction> object_function = context->object_function();
5008  if (!tuple.is_null()) {
5009  tuple->set_value1(object_function);
5010  } else {
5011  new_map->SetConstructor(object_function);
5012  }
5013  }
5014  }
5015  JSObject::MigrateToMap(isolate, object, new_map);
5016 
5017  if (V8_DICT_PROPERTY_CONST_TRACKING_BOOL && !object->HasFastProperties()) {
5018  ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
5019  DisallowHeapAllocation no_gc;
5020 
5021  auto make_constant = [&](auto dict) {
5022  for (InternalIndex index : dict->IterateEntries()) {
5023  Tagged<Object> k;
5024  if (!dict->ToKey(roots, index, &k)) continue;
5025 
5026  PropertyDetails details = dict->DetailsAt(index);
5027  details = details.CopyWithConstness(PropertyConstness::kConst);
5028  dict->DetailsAtPut(index, details);
5029  }
5030  };
5031  if constexpr (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
5032  make_constant(object->property_dictionary_swiss());
5033  } else {
5034  make_constant(object->property_dictionary());
5035  }
5036  }
5037  }
5038 #ifdef DEBUG
5039  bool should_be_dictionary = V8_DICT_PROPERTY_CONST_TRACKING_BOOL &&
5040  enable_setup_mode && !IsJSGlobalProxy(*object) &&
5041  !isolate->bootstrapper()->IsActive();
5042  DCHECK_IMPLIES(should_be_dictionary,
5043  object->map(isolate)->is_dictionary_map());
5044 #endif
5045 }

5047 // static
5048 void JSObject::ReoptimizeIfPrototype(DirectHandle<JSObject> object) {
5049  {
5050  Tagged<Map> map = object->map();
5051  if (!map->is_prototype_map()) return;
5052  if (!map->should_be_fast_prototype_map()) return;
5053  }
5054  OptimizeAsPrototype(object);
5055 }
5056 
5057 // static
5058 void JSObject::LazyRegisterPrototypeUser(DirectHandle<Map> user,
5059  Isolate* isolate) {
5060  // Contract: In line with InvalidatePrototypeChains()'s requirements,
5061  // leaf maps don't need to register as users, only prototypes do.
5062  DCHECK(user->is_prototype_map());
5063 
5064  DirectHandle<Map> current_user = user;
5065  DirectHandle<PrototypeInfo> current_user_info =
5066  Map::GetOrCreatePrototypeInfo(user, isolate);
5067  for (PrototypeIterator iter(isolate, user); !iter.IsAtEnd(); iter.Advance()) {
5068  // Walk up the prototype chain as far as links haven't been registered yet.
5069  if (current_user_info->registry_slot() != PrototypeInfo::UNREGISTERED) {
5070  break;
5071  }
5072  DirectHandle<Object> maybe_proto = PrototypeIterator::GetCurrent(iter);
5073  // This checks for both proxies and shared objects.
5074  //
5075  // Proxies on the prototype chain are not supported. They make it
5076  // impossible to make any assumptions about the prototype chain anyway.
5077  //
5078  // Objects in the shared heap have fixed layouts and their maps never
5079  // change, so they don't need to be tracked as prototypes
5080  // anyway. Additionally, registering users of shared objects is not
5081  // threadsafe.
5082  if (!IsJSObjectThatCanBeTrackedAsPrototype(*maybe_proto)) continue;
5083  auto proto = Cast<JSObject>(maybe_proto);
5084  DirectHandle<PrototypeInfo> proto_info =
5085  Map::GetOrCreatePrototypeInfo(proto, isolate);
5086  Handle<Object> maybe_registry(proto_info->prototype_users(), isolate);
5087  Handle<WeakArrayList> registry =
5088  IsSmi(*maybe_registry)
5089  ? handle(ReadOnlyRoots(isolate->heap()).empty_weak_array_list(),
5090  isolate)
5091  : Cast<WeakArrayList>(maybe_registry);
5092  int slot = 0;
5093  Handle<WeakArrayList> new_array =
5094  PrototypeUsers::Add(isolate, registry, current_user, &slot);
5095  current_user_info->set_registry_slot(slot);
5096  if (!maybe_registry.is_identical_to(new_array)) {
5097  proto_info->set_prototype_users(*new_array);
5098  }
5099  if (v8_flags.trace_prototype_users) {
5100  PrintF("Registering %p as a user of prototype %p (map=%p).\n",
5101  reinterpret_cast<void*>(current_user->ptr()),
5102  reinterpret_cast<void*>(proto->ptr()),
5103  reinterpret_cast<void*>(proto->map().ptr()));
5104  }
5105 
5106  current_user = direct_handle(proto->map(), isolate);
5107  current_user_info = proto_info;
5108  }
5109 }
5110 
5111 // Can be called regardless of whether |user| was actually registered with
5112 // |prototype|. Returns true when there was a registration.
5113 // static
5114 bool JSObject::UnregisterPrototypeUser(DirectHandle<Map> user,
5115  Isolate* isolate) {
5116  DCHECK(user->is_prototype_map());
5117  // If it doesn't have a PrototypeInfo, it was never registered.
5118  if (!user->has_prototype_info()) return false;
5119  DCHECK(IsPrototypeInfo(user->prototype_info()));
5120  // If it had no prototype before, see if it had users that might expect
5121  // registration.
5122  if (!IsJSObject(user->prototype())) {
5123  Tagged<Object> users =
5124  Cast<PrototypeInfo>(user->prototype_info())->prototype_users();
5125  return IsWeakArrayList(users);
5126  }
5127  DirectHandle<JSObject> prototype(Cast<JSObject>(user->prototype()), isolate);
5128  DirectHandle<PrototypeInfo> user_info =
5129  Map::GetOrCreatePrototypeInfo(user, isolate);
5130  int slot = user_info->registry_slot();
5131  if (slot == PrototypeInfo::UNREGISTERED) return false;
5132  DCHECK(prototype->map()->is_prototype_map());
5133  Tagged<Object> maybe_proto_info = prototype->map()->prototype_info();
5134  // User knows its registry slot, prototype info and user registry must exist.
5135  DCHECK(IsPrototypeInfo(maybe_proto_info));
5136  DirectHandle<PrototypeInfo> proto_info(Cast<PrototypeInfo>(maybe_proto_info),
5137  isolate);
5138  DirectHandle<WeakArrayList> prototype_users(
5139  Cast<WeakArrayList>(proto_info->prototype_users()), isolate);
5140  DCHECK_EQ(prototype_users->Get(slot), MakeWeak(*user));
5141  PrototypeUsers::MarkSlotEmpty(*prototype_users, slot);
5142  if (v8_flags.trace_prototype_users) {
5143  PrintF("Unregistering %p as a user of prototype %p.\n",
5144  reinterpret_cast<void*>(user->ptr()),
5145  reinterpret_cast<void*>(prototype->ptr()));
5146  }
5147  return true;
5148 }

5150 namespace {
5151 
5152 // This function must be kept in sync with
5153 // AccessorAssembler::InvalidateValidityCellIfPrototype() which does pre-checks
5154 // before jumping here.
5155 void InvalidateOnePrototypeValidityCellInternal(Tagged<Map> map) {
5156  DCHECK(map->is_prototype_map());
5157  if (v8_flags.trace_prototype_users) {
5158  PrintF("Invalidating prototype map %p 's cell\n",
5159  reinterpret_cast<void*>(map.ptr()));
5160  }
5161  Tagged<Object> maybe_cell = map->prototype_validity_cell(kRelaxedLoad);
5162  if (IsCell(maybe_cell)) {
5163  // Just set the value; the cell will be replaced lazily.
5164  Tagged<Cell> cell = Cast<Cell>(maybe_cell);
5165  Tagged<Smi> invalid_value = Smi::FromInt(Map::kPrototypeChainInvalid);
5166  if (cell->value() != invalid_value) {
5167  cell->set_value(invalid_value, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
5168  }
5169  }
5170  Tagged<PrototypeInfo> prototype_info;
5171  if (map->TryGetPrototypeInfo(&prototype_info)) {
5172  prototype_info->set_prototype_chain_enum_cache(Smi::zero());
5173  // Previously created non-existent data handlers might no longer be valid,
5174  // ensure they are re-created if necessary.
5175  for (int i = 0; i < PrototypeInfo::kCachedHandlerCount; i++) {
5176  prototype_info->set_cached_handler(i, Smi::zero(), SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
5177  }
5178  }
5179 
5180  // We may inline accesses to constants stored in dictionary mode prototypes in
5181  // optimized code. When doing so, we install dependencies of group
5182  // |kPrototypeCheckGroup| on each prototype between the receiver's immediate
5183  // prototype and the holder of the constant property. This dependency is used
5184  // both to detect changes to the constant value itself, and other changes to
5185  // the prototype chain that invalidate the access to the given property from
5186  // the given receiver (like adding the property to another prototype between
5187  // the receiver and the (previous) holder). This works by de-opting this group
5188  // whenever the validity cell would be invalidated. However, the actual value
5189  // of the validity cell is not used. Therefore, we always trigger the de-opt
5190  // here, even if the cell was already invalid.
5191  if (V8_DICT_PROPERTY_CONST_TRACKING_BOOL && map->is_dictionary_map()) {
5192  // TODO(11527): pass Isolate as an argument.
5193  Isolate* isolate = GetIsolateFromWritableObject(map);
5194  DependentCode::DeoptimizeDependencyGroups(
5195  isolate, map, DependentCode::kPrototypeCheckGroup);
5196  }
5197 }
5198 
5199 void InvalidatePrototypeChainsInternal(Tagged<Map> map) {
5200  // We handle linear prototype chains by looping, and multiple children
5201  // by recursion, in order to reduce the likelihood of running into stack
5202  // overflows. So, conceptually, the outer loop iterates the depth of the
5203  // prototype tree, and the inner loop iterates the breadth of a node.
5204  Tagged<Map> next_map;
5205  for (; !map.is_null(); map = next_map, next_map = Map()) {
5206  InvalidateOnePrototypeValidityCellInternal(map);
5207 
5208  Tagged<PrototypeInfo> proto_info;
5209  if (!map->TryGetPrototypeInfo(&proto_info)) return;
5210  if (!IsWeakArrayList(proto_info->prototype_users())) {
5211  return;
5212  }
5213  Tagged<WeakArrayList> prototype_users =
5214  Cast<WeakArrayList>(proto_info->prototype_users());
5215  // For now, only maps register themselves as users.
5216  for (int i = PrototypeUsers::kFirstIndex; i < prototype_users->length();
5217  ++i) {
5218  Tagged<HeapObject> heap_object;
5219  if (prototype_users->Get(i).GetHeapObjectIfWeak(&heap_object) &&
5220  IsMap(heap_object)) {
5221  // Walk the prototype chain (backwards, towards leaf objects) if
5222  // necessary.
5223  if (next_map.is_null()) {
5224  next_map = Cast<Map>(heap_object);
5225  } else {
5226  InvalidatePrototypeChainsInternal(Cast<Map>(heap_object));
5227  }
5228  }
5229  }
5230  }
5231 }
5232 
5233 } // namespace
5234 
5235 // static
5236 Tagged<Map> JSObject::InvalidatePrototypeChains(Tagged<Map> map) {
5237  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5238  InvalidatePrototypeChainsInternal(map);
5239  return map;
5240 }
5241 
5242 // We also invalidate global objects validity cell when a new lexical
5243 // environment variable is added. This is necessary to ensure that
5244 // Load/StoreGlobalIC handlers that load/store from global object's prototype
5245 // get properly invalidated.
5246 // Note, that the normal Load/StoreICs that load/store through the global object
5247 // in the prototype chain are not affected by appearance of a new lexical
5248 // variable and therefore we don't propagate invalidation down.
5249 // static
5250 void JSObject::InvalidatePrototypeValidityCell(Tagged<JSGlobalObject> global) {
5251  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5252  InvalidateOnePrototypeValidityCellInternal(global->map());
5253 }
5254 
5255 Maybe<bool> JSObject::SetPrototype(Isolate* isolate,
5256  DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
5257  DirectHandle<Object> value_obj,
5258  bool from_javascript,
5259  ShouldThrow should_throw) {
5260 #ifdef DEBUG
5261  int size = object->Size();
5262 #endif
5263 
5264  if (from_javascript) {
5265  if (IsAccessCheckNeeded(*object) &&
5266  !isolate->MayAccess(isolate->native_context(), object)) {
5267  RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
5268  isolate, isolate->ReportFailedAccessCheck(object), Nothing<bool>());
5269  UNREACHABLE();
5270  }
5271  } else {
5272  DCHECK(!IsAccessCheckNeeded(*object));
5273  }
5274 
5275  // Silently ignore the change if value is not a JSReceiver or null.
5276  // SpiderMonkey behaves this way.
5277  DirectHandle<JSPrototype> value;
5278  if (!TryCast(value_obj, &value)) return Just(true);
5279 
5280  bool all_extensible = object->map()->is_extensible();
5281  DirectHandle<JSObject> real_receiver = object;
5282  if (from_javascript) {
5283  // Find the first object in the chain whose prototype object is not
5284  // hidden.
5285  PrototypeIterator iter(isolate, real_receiver, kStartAtPrototype,
5286  PrototypeIterator::END_AT_NON_HIDDEN);
5287  while (!iter.IsAtEnd()) {
5288  // Casting to JSObject is fine because hidden prototypes are never
5289  // JSProxies.
5290  real_receiver = PrototypeIterator::GetCurrent<JSObject>(iter);
5291  iter.Advance();
5292  all_extensible = all_extensible && real_receiver->map()->is_extensible();
5293  }
5294  }
5295  DirectHandle<Map> map(real_receiver->map(), isolate);
5296 
5297  // Nothing to do if prototype is already set.
5298  if (map->prototype() == *value) return Just(true);
5299 
5300  bool immutable_proto = map->is_immutable_proto();
5301  if (immutable_proto) {
5302  DirectHandle<Object> msg;
5303  if (IsJSObjectPrototype(*object)) { // is [[Object.prototype]]
5304  msg = isolate->factory()->Object_prototype_string();
5305  } else {
5306  msg = object;
5307  }
5308  RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, should_throw,
5309  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kImmutablePrototypeSet, msg));
5310  }
5311 
5312  // From 6.1.7.3 Invariants of the Essential Internal Methods
5313  //
5314  // [[SetPrototypeOf]] ( V )
5315  // * ...
5316  // * If target is non-extensible, [[SetPrototypeOf]] must return false,
5317  // unless V is the SameValue as the target's observed [[GetPrototypeOf]]
5318  // value.
5319  if (!all_extensible) {
5320  RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, should_throw,
5321  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kNonExtensibleProto, object));
5322  }
5323 
5324  // Before we can set the prototype we need to be sure prototype cycles are
5325  // prevented. It is sufficient to validate that the receiver is not in the
5326  // new prototype chain.
5327  if (Tagged<JSReceiver> receiver; TryCast<JSReceiver>(*value, &receiver)) {
5328  for (PrototypeIterator iter(isolate, receiver, kStartAtReceiver);
5329  !iter.IsAtEnd(); iter.Advance()) {
5330  if (iter.GetCurrent<JSReceiver>() == *object) {
5331  // Cycle detected.
5332  RETURN_FAILURE(isolate, should_throw,
5333  NewTypeError(MessageTemplate::kCyclicProto));
5334  }
5335  }
5336  }
5337 
5338  // Set the new prototype of the object.
5339 
5340  isolate->UpdateProtectorsOnSetPrototype(real_receiver, value);
5341 
5342  DirectHandle<Map> new_map =
5343  v8_flags.move_prototype_transitions_first
5344  ? MapUpdater(isolate, map).ApplyPrototypeTransition(value)
5345  : Map::TransitionToUpdatePrototype(isolate, map, value);
5346 
5347  DCHECK(new_map->prototype() == *value);
5348  JSObject::MigrateToMap(isolate, real_receiver, new_map);
5349 
5350  DCHECK_IMPLIES(!new_map->is_dictionary_map() && !map->is_deprecated() &&
5351  !IsUndefined(new_map->GetBackPointer()),
5352  size == object->Size());
5353  return Just(true);
5354 }
5355 
5356 // static
5357 void JSObject::SetImmutableProto(Isolate* isolate,
5358  DirectHandle<JSObject> object) {
5359  DirectHandle<Map> map(object->map(), isolate);
5360 
5361  // Nothing to do if prototype is already set.
5362  if (map->is_immutable_proto()) return;
5363 
5364  DirectHandle<Map> new_map = Map::TransitionToImmutableProto(isolate, map);
5365  object->set_map(isolate, *new_map, kReleaseStore);
5366 }

5379 #ifdef ENABLE_SLOW_DCHECKS

5385 
5386 bool JSObject::WouldConvertToSlowElements(uint32_t index) {
5387  if (!HasFastElements()) return false;
5388  uint32_t capacity = static_cast<uint32_t>(elements()->length());
5389  uint32_t new_capacity;
5390  return ShouldConvertToSlowElements(*this, capacity, index, &new_capacity);
5391 }
5392 
5393 static bool ShouldConvertToFastElements(Tagged<JSObject> object,
5394  Tagged<NumberDictionary> dictionary,
5395  uint32_t index,
5396  uint32_t* new_capacity) {
5397  // If properties with non-standard attributes or accessors were added, we
5398  // cannot go back to fast elements.
5399  if (dictionary->requires_slow_elements()) return false;
5400 
5401  // Adding a property with this index will require slow elements.
5402  if (index >= static_cast<uint32_t>(Smi::kMaxValue)) return false;
5403 
5404  if (IsJSArray(object)) {
5405  Tagged<Object> length = Cast<JSArray>(object)->length();
5406  if (!IsSmi(length)) return false;
5407  *new_capacity = static_cast<uint32_t>(Smi::ToInt(length));
5408  } else if (IsJSArgumentsObject(object)) {
5409  return false;
5410  } else {
5411  *new_capacity = dictionary->max_number_key() + 1;
5412  }
5413  *new_capacity = std::max(index + 1, *new_capacity);
5414 
5415  uint32_t dictionary_size = static_cast<uint32_t>(dictionary->Capacity()) *
5416  NumberDictionary::kEntrySize;
5417 
5418  // Turn fast if the dictionary only saves 50% space.
5419  return 2 * dictionary_size >= *new_capacity;
5420 }
5421 
5422 static ElementsKind BestFittingFastElementsKind(Tagged<JSObject> object) {
5423  if (!object->map()->CanHaveFastTransitionableElementsKind()) {
5424  return HOLEY_ELEMENTS;
5425  }
5426  if (object->HasSloppyArgumentsElements()) {
5427  return FAST_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS;
5428  }
5429  if (object->HasStringWrapperElements()) {
5430  return FAST_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS;
5431  }
5432  DCHECK(object->HasDictionaryElements());
5433  Tagged<NumberDictionary> dictionary = object->element_dictionary();
5434  ElementsKind kind = HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS;
5435  for (InternalIndex i : dictionary->IterateEntries()) {
5436  Tagged<Object> key = dictionary->KeyAt(i);
5437  if (IsNumber(key)) {
5438  Tagged<Object> value = dictionary->ValueAt(i);
5439  if (!IsNumber(value)) return HOLEY_ELEMENTS;
5440  if (!IsSmi(value)) {
5441  if (!v8_flags.unbox_double_arrays) return HOLEY_ELEMENTS;
5442  kind = HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS;
5443  }
5444  }
5445  }
5446  return kind;
5447 }
5448 
5449 // static
5450 Maybe<bool> JSObject::AddDataElement(Isolate* isolate,
5451  DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
5452  uint32_t index, DirectHandle<Object> value,
5453  PropertyAttributes attributes) {
5454  DCHECK(object->map(isolate)->is_extensible());
5455 
5456  uint32_t old_length = 0;
5457  uint32_t new_capacity = 0;
5458 
5459  if (IsJSArray(*object, isolate)) {
5460  CHECK(Object::ToArrayLength(Cast<JSArray>(*object)->length(), &old_length));
5461  }
5462 
5463  ElementsKind kind = object->GetElementsKind(isolate);
5464  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> elements = object->elements(isolate);
5465  ElementsKind dictionary_kind = DICTIONARY_ELEMENTS;
5466  if (IsSloppyArgumentsElementsKind(kind)) {
5467  elements = Cast<SloppyArgumentsElements>(elements)->arguments();
5468  dictionary_kind = SLOW_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS;
5469  } else if (IsStringWrapperElementsKind(kind)) {
5470  dictionary_kind = SLOW_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS;
5471  }
5472 
5473  if (attributes != NONE) {
5474  kind = dictionary_kind;
5475  } else if (IsNumberDictionary(elements, isolate)) {
5476  kind = ShouldConvertToFastElements(
5477  *object, Cast<NumberDictionary>(elements), index, &new_capacity)
5478  ? BestFittingFastElementsKind(*object)
5479  : dictionary_kind;
5480  } else if (ShouldConvertToSlowElements(
5481  *object, static_cast<uint32_t>(elements->length()), index,
5482  &new_capacity)) {
5483  kind = dictionary_kind;
5484  }
5485 
5486  ElementsKind to = Object::OptimalElementsKind(*value, isolate);
5487  if (IsHoleyElementsKind(kind) || !IsJSArray(*object, isolate) ||
5488  index > old_length) {
5489  to = GetHoleyElementsKind(to);
5490  kind = GetHoleyElementsKind(kind);
5491  }
5492  to = GetMoreGeneralElementsKind(kind, to);
5493  ElementsAccessor* accessor = ElementsAccessor::ForKind(to);
5494  MAYBE_RETURN(
5495  accessor->Add(isolate, object, index, value, attributes, new_capacity),
5496  Nothing<bool>());
5497 
5498  if (IsJSArray(*object, isolate) && index >= old_length) {
5499  DirectHandle<Number> new_length =
5500  isolate->factory()->NewNumberFromUint(index + 1);
5501  Cast<JSArray>(*object)->set_length(*new_length);
5502  }
5503  return Just(true);
5504 }
5505 
5506 template <AllocationSiteUpdateMode update_or_check>
5507 bool JSObject::UpdateAllocationSite(Isolate* isolate,
5508  DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
5509  ElementsKind to_kind) {
5510  if (!IsJSArray(*object)) return false;
5511 
5512  if (!HeapLayout::InYoungGeneration(*object)) return false;
5513 
5514  if (Heap::IsLargeObject(*object)) return false;
5515 
5516  DirectHandle<AllocationSite> site;
5517  {
5518  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5519 
5520  Heap* heap = isolate->heap();
5521  Tagged<AllocationMemento> memento =
5522  PretenuringHandler::FindAllocationMemento<
5523  PretenuringHandler::kForRuntime>(heap, object->map(), *object);
5524  if (memento.is_null()) return false;
5525 
5526  // Walk through to the Allocation Site
5527  site = direct_handle(memento->GetAllocationSite(), heap->isolate());
5528  }
5529  return AllocationSite::DigestTransitionFeedback<update_or_check>(
5530  isolate, site, to_kind);
5531 }
5532 
5533 template bool
5534 JSObject::UpdateAllocationSite<AllocationSiteUpdateMode::kCheckOnly>(
5535  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object, ElementsKind to_kind);
5536 
5537 template bool JSObject::UpdateAllocationSite<AllocationSiteUpdateMode::kUpdate>(
5538  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> object, ElementsKind to_kind);
5539 
5540 void JSObject::TransitionElementsKind(Isolate* isolate,
5541  DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
5542  ElementsKind to_kind) {
5543  ElementsKind from_kind = object->GetElementsKind();
5544 
5545  if (IsHoleyElementsKind(from_kind)) {
5546  to_kind = GetHoleyElementsKind(to_kind);
5547  }
5548 
5549  if (from_kind == to_kind) return;
5550 
5551  // This method should never be called for any other case.
5552  DCHECK(IsFastElementsKind(from_kind) ||
5553  IsNonextensibleElementsKind(from_kind));
5554  DCHECK(IsFastElementsKind(to_kind) || IsNonextensibleElementsKind(to_kind));
5555  DCHECK_NE(TERMINAL_FAST_ELEMENTS_KIND, from_kind);
5556 
5557  UpdateAllocationSite(isolate, object, to_kind);
5558  if (object->elements() == ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).empty_fixed_array() ||
5559  IsDoubleElementsKind(from_kind) == IsDoubleElementsKind(to_kind)) {
5560  // No change is needed to the elements() buffer, the transition
5561  // only requires a map change.
5562  DirectHandle<Map> new_map =
5563  GetElementsTransitionMap(isolate, object, to_kind);
5564  JSObject::MigrateToMap(isolate, object, new_map);
5565  if (v8_flags.trace_elements_transitions) {
5566  DirectHandle<FixedArrayBase> elms(object->elements(), isolate);
5567  PrintElementsTransition(stdout, object, from_kind, elms, to_kind, elms);
5568  }
5569  } else {
5570  DCHECK((IsSmiElementsKind(from_kind) && IsDoubleElementsKind(to_kind)) ||
5571  (IsDoubleElementsKind(from_kind) && IsObjectElementsKind(to_kind)));
5572  uint32_t c = static_cast<uint32_t>(object->elements()->length());
5573  if (ElementsAccessor::ForKind(to_kind)
5574  ->GrowCapacityAndConvert(isolate, object, c)
5575  .IsNothing()) {
5576  // TODO(victorgomes): Temporarily forcing a fatal error here in case of
5577  // overflow, until all users of TransitionElementsKind can handle
5578  // exceptions.
5579  FATAL(
5580  "Fatal JavaScript invalid size error when transitioning elements "
5581  "kind");
5582  UNREACHABLE();
5583  }
5584  }
5585 }
5586 
5587 template <typename BackingStore>
5588 static int HoleyElementsUsage(Tagged<JSObject> object,
5589  Tagged<BackingStore> store) {
5590  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::Current();
5591  int limit = IsJSArray(object) ? Smi::ToInt(Cast<JSArray>(object)->length())
5592  : store->length();
5593  int used = 0;
5594  for (int i = 0; i < limit; ++i) {
5595  if (!store->is_the_hole(isolate, i)) ++used;
5596  }
5597  return used;
5598 }
5599 
5600 int JSObject::GetFastElementsUsage() {
5601  Tagged<FixedArrayBase> store = elements();
5602  switch (GetElementsKind()) {
5603  case PACKED_SMI_ELEMENTS:
5604  case PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS:
5605  case PACKED_ELEMENTS:
5606  case PACKED_FROZEN_ELEMENTS:
5607  case PACKED_SEALED_ELEMENTS:
5608  case PACKED_NONEXTENSIBLE_ELEMENTS:
5609  case SHARED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS:
5610  return IsJSArray(*this) ? Smi::ToInt(Cast<JSArray>(*this)->length())
5611  : store->length();
5612  case FAST_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS:
5613  store = Cast<SloppyArgumentsElements>(store)->arguments();
5614  [[fallthrough]];
5615  case HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS:
5616  case HOLEY_ELEMENTS:
5617  case HOLEY_FROZEN_ELEMENTS:
5618  case HOLEY_SEALED_ELEMENTS:
5619  case HOLEY_NONEXTENSIBLE_ELEMENTS:
5620  case FAST_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS:
5621  return HoleyElementsUsage(*this, Cast<FixedArray>(store));
5622  case HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS:
5623  if (elements()->length() == 0) return 0;
5624  return HoleyElementsUsage(*this, Cast<FixedDoubleArray>(store));
5625 
5626  case SLOW_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS:
5627  case SLOW_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS:
5628  case DICTIONARY_ELEMENTS:
5629  case WASM_ARRAY_ELEMENTS:
5630  case NO_ELEMENTS:
5631 #define TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Type, type, TYPE, ctype) case TYPE##_ELEMENTS:
5632 
5633  TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)
5634  RAB_GSAB_TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)
5635 #undef TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
5636  UNREACHABLE();
5637  }
5638  return 0;
5639 }

5685 void JSGlobalObject::InvalidatePropertyCell(DirectHandle<JSGlobalObject> global,
5686  DirectHandle<Name> name) {
5687  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::Current();
5688  // Regardless of whether the property is there or not invalidate
5689  // Load/StoreGlobalICs that load/store through global object's prototype.
5690  JSObject::InvalidatePrototypeValidityCell(*global);
5691  DCHECK(!global->HasFastProperties());
5692  auto dictionary =
5693  direct_handle(global->global_dictionary(kAcquireLoad), isolate);
5694  InternalIndex entry = dictionary->FindEntry(isolate, name);
5695  if (entry.is_not_found()) return;
5696 
5697  DirectHandle<PropertyCell> cell(dictionary->CellAt(entry), isolate);
5698  DirectHandle<Object> value(cell->value(), isolate);
5699  PropertyDetails details = cell->property_details();
5700  details = details.set_cell_type(PropertyCellType::kMutable);
5701  PropertyCell::InvalidateAndReplaceEntry(isolate, dictionary, entry, details,
5702  value);
5703 }

5713  Cast<JSDate>(JSObject::New(constructor, new_target, {})));
5714  if (DateCache::TryTimeClip(&tv)) {
5715  result->SetValue(isolate, tv);
5716  } else {
5717  result->SetNanValue();
5718  }
5719  return result;

5722 // static
5723 int64_t JSDate::CurrentTimeValue(Isolate* isolate) {
5724  if (v8_flags.log_timer_events) LOG(isolate, CurrentTimeEvent());
5725  if (v8_flags.correctness_fuzzer_suppressions) return 4;
5726 
5727  // According to ECMA-262, section 15.9.1, page 117, the precision of
5728  // the number in a Date object representing a particular instant in
5729  // time is milliseconds. Therefore, we floor the result of getting
5730  // the OS time.
5731  return V8::GetCurrentPlatform()->CurrentClockTimeMilliseconds();
5732 }

5748 
5749 Tagged<Object> JSDate::DoGetField(Isolate* isolate, FieldIndex index) {
5750  DateCache* date_cache = isolate->date_cache();
5751 
5752  if (index < kFirstUncachedField) {
5753  Tagged<Object> stamp = cache_stamp();
5754  if (stamp != isolate->date_cache_stamp() && IsSmi(stamp)) {
5755  // Since the stamp is not NaN, the value is also not NaN.
5756  int64_t local_time_ms =
5757  date_cache->ToLocal(static_cast<int64_t>(value()));
5758  SetCachedFields(isolate, local_time_ms, date_cache);
5759  }
5760  switch (index) {
5761  case kYear:
5762  return year();
5763  case kMonth:
5764  return month();
5765  case kDay:
5766  return day();
5767  case kWeekday:
5768  return weekday();
5769  case kHour:
5770  return hour();
5771  case kMinute:
5772  return min();
5773  case kSecond:
5774  return sec();
5775  default:
5776  UNREACHABLE();
5777  }
5778  }
5779 
5780  if (index >= kFirstUTCField) {
5781  return GetUTCField(index, value(), date_cache);
5782  }
5783 
5784  double time = value();
5785  if (std::isnan(time)) return GetReadOnlyRoots().nan_value();
5786 
5787  int64_t local_time_ms = date_cache->ToLocal(static_cast<int64_t>(time));
5788  int days = DateCache::DaysFromTime(local_time_ms);
5789 
5790  if (index == kDays) return Smi::FromInt(days);
5791 
5792  int time_in_day_ms = DateCache::TimeInDay(local_time_ms, days);
5793  if (index == kMillisecond) return Smi::FromInt(time_in_day_ms % 1000);
5794  DCHECK_EQ(index, kTimeInDay);
5795  return Smi::FromInt(time_in_day_ms);
5796 }
5797 
5798 Tagged<Object> JSDate::GetUTCField(FieldIndex index, double value,
5799  DateCache* date_cache) {
5800  DCHECK_GE(index, kFirstUTCField);
5801 
5802  if (std::isnan(value)) return GetReadOnlyRoots().nan_value();
5803 
5804  int64_t time_ms = static_cast<int64_t>(value);
5805 
5806  if (index == kTimezoneOffset) {
5807  return Smi::FromInt(date_cache->TimezoneOffset(time_ms));
5808  }
5809 
5810  int days = DateCache::DaysFromTime(time_ms);
5811 
5812  if (index == kWeekdayUTC) return Smi::FromInt(date_cache->Weekday(days));
5813 
5814  if (index <= kDayUTC) {
5815  int year, month, day;
5816  date_cache->YearMonthDayFromDays(days, &year, &month, &day);
5817  if (index == kYearUTC) return Smi::FromInt(year);
5818  if (index == kMonthUTC) return Smi::FromInt(month);
5819  DCHECK_EQ(index, kDayUTC);
5820  return Smi::FromInt(day);
5821  }
5822 
5823  int time_in_day_ms = DateCache::TimeInDay(time_ms, days);
5824  switch (index) {
5825  case kHourUTC:
5826  return Smi::FromInt(time_in_day_ms / (60 * 60 * 1000));
5827  case kMinuteUTC:
5828  return Smi::FromInt((time_in_day_ms / (60 * 1000)) % 60);
5829  case kSecondUTC:
5830  return Smi::FromInt((time_in_day_ms / 1000) % 60);
5831  case kMillisecondUTC:
5832  return Smi::FromInt(time_in_day_ms % 1000);
5833  case kDaysUTC:
5834  return Smi::FromInt(days);
5835  case kTimeInDayUTC:
5836  return Smi::FromInt(time_in_day_ms);
5837  default:
5838  UNREACHABLE();
5839  }
5840 
5841  UNREACHABLE();
5842 }
5843 
5844 // static
5845 void JSDate::SetValue(Isolate* isolate, double value) {
5846 #ifdef DEBUG
5847  DCHECK(!std::isnan(value));
5848  double clipped_value = value;
5849  DCHECK(DateCache::TryTimeClip(&clipped_value));
5850  DCHECK_EQ(value, clipped_value);
5851 #endif
5852  set_value(value);
5853 
5854  DateCache* date_cache = isolate->date_cache();
5855  // Since the stamp is not NaN, the value is also not NaN.
5856  int64_t local_time_ms = date_cache->ToLocal(static_cast<int64_t>(value));
5857  SetCachedFields(isolate, local_time_ms, date_cache);
5858 }
5859 
5860 void JSDate::SetNanValue() {
5861  set_value(std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN());
5862 
5863  Tagged<HeapNumber> nan = GetReadOnlyRoots().nan_value();
5864  set_cache_stamp(nan, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
5865  set_year(nan, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
5866  set_month(nan, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
5867  set_day(nan, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
5868  set_hour(nan, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
5869  set_min(nan, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
5870  set_sec(nan, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
5871  set_weekday(nan, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
5872 }
5873 
5874 void JSDate::UpdateFieldsAfterDeserialization(Isolate* isolate) {
5875  double time = value();
5876  if (std::isnan(time)) {
5877  // In this case all the cached fields are set to NaNs, thus no updates
5878  // necessary.
5879  return;
5880  }
5881  DateCache* date_cache = isolate->date_cache();
5882  int64_t local_time_ms = date_cache->ToLocal(static_cast<int64_t>(time));
5883  SetCachedFields(isolate, local_time_ms, date_cache);
5884 }
5885 
5886 void JSDate::SetCachedFields(Isolate* isolate, int64_t local_time_ms,
5887  DateCache* date_cache) {
5888  int days = DateCache::DaysFromTime(local_time_ms);
5889  int time_in_day_ms = DateCache::TimeInDay(local_time_ms, days);
5890  int year, month, day;
5891  date_cache->YearMonthDayFromDays(days, &year, &month, &day);
5892  int weekday = date_cache->Weekday(days);
5893  int hour = time_in_day_ms / (60 * 60 * 1000);
5894  int min = (time_in_day_ms / (60 * 1000)) % 60;
5895  int sec = (time_in_day_ms / 1000) % 60;
5896  set_cache_stamp(isolate->GetDateCacheStampAndRecordUsage(),
5897  SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
5898  set_year(Smi::FromInt(year), SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
5899  set_month(Smi::FromInt(month), SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
5900  set_day(Smi::FromInt(day), SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
5901  set_weekday(Smi::FromInt(weekday), SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
5902  set_hour(Smi::FromInt(hour), SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
5903  set_min(Smi::FromInt(min), SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
5904  set_sec(Smi::FromInt(sec), SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
5905 }
5906 
5907 // static
5908 void JSMessageObject::InitializeSourcePositions(
5909  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSMessageObject> message) {
5910  DCHECK(!message->DidEnsureSourcePositionsAvailable());
5911  Script::InitLineEnds(isolate, direct_handle(message->script(), isolate));
5912  if (message->shared_info() == Smi::FromInt(-1)) {
5913  message->set_shared_info(Smi::zero());
5914  return;
5915  }
5916  DCHECK(IsSharedFunctionInfo(message->shared_info()));
5917  DCHECK_GE(message->bytecode_offset().value(), kFunctionEntryBytecodeOffset);
5918  Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info(
5919  Cast<SharedFunctionInfo>(message->shared_info()), isolate);
5920  IsCompiledScope is_compiled_scope;
5921  SharedFunctionInfo::EnsureBytecodeArrayAvailable(
5922  isolate, shared_info, &is_compiled_scope, CreateSourcePositions::kYes);
5923  SharedFunctionInfo::EnsureSourcePositionsAvailable(isolate, shared_info);
5924  DCHECK(shared_info->HasBytecodeArray());
5925  int position = shared_info->abstract_code(isolate)->SourcePosition(
5926  isolate, message->bytecode_offset().value());
5927  DCHECK_GE(position, 0);
5928  message->set_start_position(position);
5929  message->set_end_position(position + 1);
5930  message->set_shared_info(Smi::zero());
5931 }
5932 
5933 int JSMessageObject::GetLineNumber() const {
5934  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5935  DCHECK(DidEnsureSourcePositionsAvailable());
5936  if (start_position() == -1) return Message::kNoLineNumberInfo;
5937 
5938  DCHECK(script()->has_line_ends());
5939  DirectHandle<Script> the_script(script(), Isolate::Current());
5940  Script::PositionInfo info;
5941  if (!script()->GetPositionInfo(start_position(), &info)) {
5942  return Message::kNoLineNumberInfo;
5943  }
5944  return info.line + 1;
5945 }
5946 
5947 int JSMessageObject::GetColumnNumber() const {
5948  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5949  DCHECK(DidEnsureSourcePositionsAvailable());
5950  if (start_position() == -1) return -1;
5951 
5952  DCHECK(script()->has_line_ends());
5953  DirectHandle<Script> the_script(script(), Isolate::Current());
5954  Script::PositionInfo info;
5955  if (!script()->GetPositionInfo(start_position(), &info)) {
5956  return -1;
5957  }
5958  return info.column; // Note: No '+1' in contrast to GetLineNumber.
5959 }
5960 
5961 Tagged<String> JSMessageObject::GetSource() const {
5962  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5963  Tagged<Script> script_object = script();
5964  if (script_object->HasValidSource()) {
5965  Tagged<Object> source = script_object->source();
5966  if (IsString(source)) return Cast<String>(source);
5967  }
5968  return ReadOnlyRoots(Isolate::Current()).empty_string();
5969 }
5970 
5971 DirectHandle<String> JSMessageObject::GetSourceLine() const {
5972  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::Current();
5973 
5974 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
5975  if (script()->type() == Script::Type::kWasm) {
5976  return isolate->factory()->empty_string();
5977  }
5978 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
5979  Script::PositionInfo info;
5980  {
5981  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5982  DCHECK(DidEnsureSourcePositionsAvailable());
5983  DCHECK(script()->has_line_ends());
5984  if (!script()->GetPositionInfo(start_position(), &info)) {
5985  return isolate->factory()->empty_string();
5986  }
5987  }
5988 
5989  Handle<String> src(Cast<String>(script()->source()), isolate);
5990  return isolate->factory()->NewSubString(src, info.line_start, info.line_end);
5991 }
